WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:28.840
Psalm 1 Blessed is the man that walketh not in the council of the ungodly, nor standeth

00:00:28.840 --> 00:00:32.640
in the way of sinners, nor siteth in the seat of this corn-full.

00:00:33.640 --> 00:00:39.420
But his delight is in the law of the Lord, and in his law doth he meditate day and night.

00:00:40.540 --> 00:00:46.200
And he shall be like a tree planted by the rivers of water, that bringeth forth his fruit

00:00:46.200 --> 00:00:47.040
in his season.

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:52.700
His leaf also shall not wither, and whatsoever he doeth shall prosper.

00:00:53.680 --> 00:00:58.740
The ungodly are not so, for alike a chaff which the wind drieth away.

00:01:00.020 --> 00:01:05.120
Therefore the ungodly shall not stand in the judgments, nor sinners in the congregation

00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:06.040
of the righteous.

00:01:07.220 --> 00:01:12.720
For the Lord knoweth the way of the righteous, for the way of the ungodly shall perish.

00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:21.560
Why do the heathen rage, and the people imagine a vain thing?

00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:27.680
The kings of the earth set themselves, and the rulers take counsel together, against

00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:32.960
the Lord and against his anointed, saying, Let us break their ban to sender, and cast

00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:34.480
away their courts from us.

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:40.240
He that sitteth in the heavens shall laugh, the Lord shall have him in direction.

00:01:41.280 --> 00:01:46.020
Then shall I speak unto them in his wrath, and vex them in his story of displeasure.

00:01:46.900 --> 00:01:50.340
Yes, have I set my king upon my holy hill of Zion.

00:01:51.820 --> 00:01:53.360
I will declare the decree.

00:01:53.960 --> 00:02:00.140
The Lord hath said unto me, Thou art my son, this day have I begotten thee.

00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:06.200
Ask of me, and I shall give thee the heathen for thine inheritance, and the uttermost

00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:08.020
parts of the earth for thy possession.

00:02:09.160 --> 00:02:11.320
Thou shalt break them with a rod of iron.

00:02:11.320 --> 00:02:14.780
Thou shalt dash them in pieces like a potter's vessel.

00:02:16.060 --> 00:02:18.660
Be wise now, therefore, O ye kings.

00:02:19.300 --> 00:02:21.720
He instructed the ejections of the earth.

00:02:22.580 --> 00:02:25.400
Serve the Lord with fear, and rejoice with trembling.

00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:31.780
Kiss the sun, lest ye be angry, and be perished from the way, when his wrath was kindled

00:02:31.780 --> 00:02:32.580
but a little.

00:02:33.440 --> 00:02:36.160
Blessed are all they that put their trust in him.

00:02:38.560 --> 00:02:39.520
Chapter 3

00:02:40.120 --> 00:02:42.800
Lord, how are they increased that trouble me?

00:02:43.260 --> 00:02:45.540
Many are they that rise up against me.

00:02:46.260 --> 00:02:50.500
Many there be which say of my soul, There is no help for him in God.

00:02:51.600 --> 00:02:52.080
Selah.

00:02:52.460 --> 00:02:57.580
That thou, O Lord, art the shield for me, My glory, and the blister up of mine head.

00:02:58.420 --> 00:03:02.500
I cried unto the Lord with my voice, And he heard me out of his holy hill.

00:03:03.400 --> 00:03:03.880
Selah.

00:03:03.880 --> 00:03:06.260
I laid me down and slept.

00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:09.180
I awaked for the Lord to save me.

00:03:09.880 --> 00:03:14.360
I will not be afraid of ten thousands of people that have set themselves against me round

00:03:14.360 --> 00:03:14.780
about.

00:03:16.020 --> 00:03:16.980
Arise, O Lord.

00:03:17.320 --> 00:03:21.980
Save me, O my God, for thou hast smitten all mine enemies upon their cheekbone.

00:03:22.560 --> 00:03:24.960
Thou hast broken the teeth of the ungodly.

00:03:26.620 --> 00:03:28.540
Salvation belongeth unto the Lord.

00:03:29.080 --> 00:03:30.880
Thy blessing is upon thy people.

00:03:31.400 --> 00:03:31.960
Selah.

00:03:34.220 --> 00:03:35.260
Chapter 4

00:03:36.280 --> 00:03:39.080
Hear me when I call, O God of my righteousness.

00:03:40.120 --> 00:03:42.700
Thou hast enlarged me when I was in distress.

00:03:43.600 --> 00:03:46.040
Have mercy upon me and hear my prayer.

00:03:47.260 --> 00:03:51.620
O ye sons of men, how long will ye turn my glory into shame?

00:03:52.560 --> 00:03:55.460
How long will ye allow vanity and seek out releasing?

00:03:56.700 --> 00:03:57.220
Selah.

00:03:58.740 --> 00:04:02.020
But know that the Lord hath set apart for him that is godly for himself.

00:04:02.020 --> 00:04:05.180
The Lord will hear when I call unto him.

00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:08.020
Stand and not and sin not.

00:04:09.280 --> 00:04:12.240
Commune with your own heart upon your bed and be still.

00:04:13.940 --> 00:04:14.460
Selah.

00:04:15.120 --> 00:04:18.620
Offer the sacrifice of the righteousness and put your trust in the Lord.

00:04:19.460 --> 00:04:22.740
There be many that say, He will show us any good.

00:04:23.700 --> 00:04:26.880
Lord, lift thou up the light of thy countenance upon us.

00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:32.760
Thou hast put gladness in my heart more than in a time that their horn and their wine increased.

00:04:33.860 --> 00:04:36.580
I will both lay me down in peace and sleep.

00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:40.160
For thou, Lord, only makest me dwell in safety.

00:04:43.100 --> 00:04:44.140
Chapter 5

00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:46.460
Give yield to my words, O Lord.

00:04:46.640 --> 00:04:48.220
Consider my meditation.

00:04:49.340 --> 00:04:54.240
Hearken unto the voice of my cry, my King and my God, for unto thee will I pray.

00:04:54.940 --> 00:04:58.100
My voice shalt thou hear in the morning, O Lord.

00:04:58.640 --> 00:05:02.000
In the morning will I direct my prayer unto thee and will look up.

00:05:03.040 --> 00:05:06.180
For thou art not a god that hath pleasure and wickedness.

00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:08.440
Neither shall evil dwell with thee.

00:05:09.160 --> 00:05:11.240
The foolish shall not stand in thy sight.

00:05:11.720 --> 00:05:14.080
Thou hast distraught workers of iniquity.

00:05:15.080 --> 00:05:17.180
Thou shalt destroy them that speak leasing.

00:05:17.660 --> 00:05:20.320
The Lord will abhor the bloody and deceitful man.

00:05:21.140 --> 00:05:25.380
But as for me, I will come into thy house in the multitude of thy mercy.

00:05:25.720 --> 00:05:28.560
And in thy fear will I worship toward thy holy temple.

00:05:29.740 --> 00:05:32.780
Lead me, O Lord, in thy righteousness because of mine enemies.

00:05:33.400 --> 00:05:35.460
Make thy way straight before my face.

00:05:36.060 --> 00:05:38.080
For there is no faithfulness in their mouth.

00:05:38.580 --> 00:05:40.700
Their inward part is very wickedness.

00:05:41.080 --> 00:05:42.760
Their throat is an open sopacher.

00:05:43.220 --> 00:05:44.520
They flatter with their tongue.

00:05:45.480 --> 00:05:47.060
Destroy thou them, O God.

00:05:47.300 --> 00:05:49.260
Let them fall by their own counsels.

00:05:49.260 --> 00:05:51.980
Cast them out in the multitude of their transgressions.

00:05:52.100 --> 00:05:53.800
For they have rebelled against thee.

00:05:55.380 --> 00:05:57.920
But let all those out that their trust in thee rejoice.

00:05:58.380 --> 00:06:01.360
Let them ever shout for joy because thou defendest them.

00:06:01.940 --> 00:06:04.820
Let them also that love thy name be joyful in thee.

00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:07.580
For that, O Lord, wilt bless the righteous.

00:06:08.200 --> 00:06:10.980
With favor wilt thou compass him as with the shield.

00:06:15.200 --> 00:06:18.060
O Lord, repute me not in thy anger.

00:06:18.060 --> 00:06:20.800
Neither chasten me in thy hot displeasure.

00:06:21.620 --> 00:06:24.280
Have mercy upon me, O Lord, for I am weak.

00:06:24.960 --> 00:06:27.780
O Lord, heal me, for my bones are vexed.

00:06:28.120 --> 00:06:30.160
My soul is also sore vexed.

00:06:30.220 --> 00:06:32.500
But thou, O Lord, how long?

00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:36.540
Be torn, O Lord, deliver my soul.

00:06:37.260 --> 00:06:39.380
O, save me for thy mercy's sake.

00:06:40.080 --> 00:06:42.660
For in death there is no remembrance of thee.

00:06:42.920 --> 00:06:44.880
And the great face shall give thee thanks.

00:06:45.720 --> 00:06:47.500
I am weary with my groaning.

00:06:47.500 --> 00:06:50.220
All the night I make on my bed is swim.

00:06:50.700 --> 00:06:52.560
I water my couch with my tears.

00:06:53.520 --> 00:06:55.500
My night is consumed because of grief.

00:06:55.900 --> 00:06:58.080
It waxeth all because of all mine enemies.

00:06:58.340 --> 00:07:00.680
Depart from me, all ye workers of iniquity.

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.180
For the Lord hath heard the voice of my weeping.

00:07:04.060 --> 00:07:05.940
The Lord hath heard my supplication.

00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:08.040
The Lord will receive my prayer.

00:07:09.160 --> 00:07:11.700
Let all mine enemies be ashamed in store of acts.

00:07:12.140 --> 00:07:14.200
Let them return and be ashamed suddenly.

00:07:19.280 --> 00:07:22.320
O Lord, my God, in thee do I put my trust.

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:26.260
Save me from all them that persecute me and deliver me.

00:07:26.580 --> 00:07:28.380
Lest ye tear my soul like a lion,

00:07:28.900 --> 00:07:31.440
running it in pieces while there is none to deliver.

00:07:32.420 --> 00:07:35.300
O Lord, my God, if I have done this,

00:07:35.640 --> 00:07:37.820
if there be iniquity in my hands,

00:07:39.100 --> 00:07:42.720
if I have rewarded evil unto him that was at peace with me,

00:07:43.260 --> 00:07:46.500
yea, I have delivered him that without cause is my enemy.

00:07:47.400 --> 00:07:50.500
Let the enemy persecute my soul and take it.

00:07:50.800 --> 00:07:53.380
Yea, let him trap down my life upon the earth

00:07:53.380 --> 00:07:55.180
and lay mine honor in the dust.

00:07:57.020 --> 00:07:57.540
Selah.

00:07:58.380 --> 00:07:59.940
Arise, O Lord, and on anger.

00:08:00.520 --> 00:08:03.020
Lift up thyself because of the rage of mine enemies

00:08:03.020 --> 00:08:05.960
and await for me to the judgment that thou hast commanded.

00:08:07.340 --> 00:08:10.500
So shall the congregation of the people compass thee about.

00:08:11.220 --> 00:08:13.820
For their sakes, therefore, return thou on high.

00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:16.740
The Lord shall judge the people.

00:08:17.420 --> 00:08:19.740
Judge me, O Lord, according to my righteousness

00:08:19.740 --> 00:08:22.960
and according to mine integrity that is in me.

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:26.640
O, let the wickedness of the wicked come to an end,

00:08:26.960 --> 00:08:28.260
but establish adjust,

00:08:28.960 --> 00:08:31.820
for the righteous God trieth the hearts and reigns.

00:08:33.140 --> 00:08:36.800
By defenses of God, which saveth the upright in heart.

00:08:37.900 --> 00:08:39.320
God judgeeth the righteous,

00:08:39.560 --> 00:08:41.940
and God is angry with the wicked every day.

00:08:41.940 --> 00:08:45.080
If he turn not, he will wet his sword.

00:08:45.600 --> 00:08:47.920
He hath bent his bow and made it ruddy.

00:08:48.580 --> 00:08:51.220
He hath also prepared for him the instruments of death.

00:08:51.980 --> 00:08:54.680
He ordaineth his arrows against the prosecutors.

00:08:55.980 --> 00:08:58.380
Behold, he too vileth with iniquity,

00:08:58.760 --> 00:09:00.120
and hath conceived mischief,

00:09:00.280 --> 00:09:01.780
and brought forth falsehood.

00:09:02.360 --> 00:09:04.140
He made a pit and digged it,

00:09:04.180 --> 00:09:06.440
and has fallen into the ditch which he made.

00:09:07.360 --> 00:09:09.640
His mischief shall return upon his own head,

00:09:09.640 --> 00:09:12.980
and his violent dealing shall come down upon his own pate.

00:09:13.900 --> 00:09:16.140
I will praise the Lord according to his righteousness,

00:09:16.500 --> 00:09:19.340
and will sing praise to the name of the Lord most high.

00:09:24.460 --> 00:09:28.800
O Lord, our Lord, how excellent is thy name in all the earth!

00:09:29.340 --> 00:09:31.600
Who hast set thy glory above the heavens?

00:09:32.620 --> 00:09:34.360
Out of the mouth of babes and sucklings

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:36.780
hast thou obeying strength because of thine enemies,

00:09:36.780 --> 00:09:39.980
that thou might distill the enemy and the avenger.

00:09:40.800 --> 00:09:43.620
When I consider thy heavens, the work of thy fingers,

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:46.720
the moon and the stars which thou hast ordained,

00:09:47.180 --> 00:09:49.460
what is mean that thou art mindful of him,

00:09:49.980 --> 00:09:52.200
and the son of man that thou visitest him?

00:09:52.820 --> 00:09:55.580
For thou hast made him a little lower than the angels,

00:09:56.040 --> 00:09:58.100
and hast crowned him with glory and honor.

00:09:58.760 --> 00:10:01.740
Thou hast made him to have dominion over the works of thy hands.

00:10:02.220 --> 00:10:04.380
Thou hast put all things under his feet.

00:10:11.040 --> 00:10:18.820
O Lord, our Lord, how excellent is thy name in all the earth!

00:10:23.080 --> 00:10:25.460
I will praise thee, O Lord, with my whole heart.

00:10:25.680 --> 00:10:28.300
I will show forth all thy marvelous works.

00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:31.180
I will be glad and rejoice in thee.

00:10:31.180 --> 00:10:34.480
I will sing praise to thy name, O thou Most High.

00:10:35.140 --> 00:10:36.800
When my enemies are turned back,

00:10:37.160 --> 00:10:39.480
they shall fall and perish at thy presence.

00:10:40.120 --> 00:10:42.780
For thou hast maintained my right to my cause.

00:10:43.480 --> 00:10:45.740
Thou saddest in the throne judging right.

00:10:46.780 --> 00:10:50.080
Thou hast rebuked the heathen. Thou hast destroyed the wicked.

00:10:50.740 --> 00:10:53.200
Thou hast put out their name for ever and ever.

00:10:54.360 --> 00:10:55.380
O thou enemy,

00:10:55.800 --> 00:10:58.020
destructions are come to a perpetual end,

00:10:58.020 --> 00:11:00.320
and thou hast destroyed cities.

00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:02.920
Their memorial is perished with them.

00:11:04.320 --> 00:11:06.240
But the Lord shall endure forever.

00:11:06.900 --> 00:11:08.940
He hath prepared his throne for judgment,

00:11:09.840 --> 00:11:11.720
and he shall judge the world of righteousness.

00:11:12.280 --> 00:11:15.280
He shall minister judgment to the people in uprightness.

00:11:16.260 --> 00:11:18.860
The Lord also will be a refuge for the oppressed,

00:11:19.460 --> 00:11:21.100
a refuge in times of trouble.

00:11:22.100 --> 00:11:24.780
And they that know thy name will put their trust in thee.

00:11:24.780 --> 00:11:28.420
For thou, Lord, hast not forsaken them that seek thee.

00:11:30.320 --> 00:11:33.020
Sing praises to the Lord, which welleth in Zion.

00:11:33.580 --> 00:11:36.240
Declare among the people his doings.

00:11:36.240 --> 00:11:39.500
When he maketh inquisition for blood, he remembereth them.

00:11:40.020 --> 00:11:42.180
He forgeteth not the cry of the humble.

00:11:43.440 --> 00:11:45.480
Have mercy upon me, O Lord.

00:11:45.780 --> 00:11:48.940
Consider my trouble which I suffer, other than that hate me.

00:11:49.400 --> 00:11:51.800
Thou that leftest me up in the gates of death,

00:11:51.800 --> 00:11:56.260
that I may show forth all thy praise in the gates of the Doctrine of Zion,

00:11:56.700 --> 00:11:58.000
I will rejoice in thy salvation.

00:11:59.680 --> 00:12:02.300
The heathen are struck down in the pit that they made,

00:12:02.920 --> 00:12:05.460
and the net which they hid is their own foot taken.

00:12:06.380 --> 00:12:09.020
The Lord is known by the judgment which he executeth.

00:12:09.340 --> 00:12:11.900
The wicked is snared in the work of his own hands.

00:12:13.560 --> 00:12:14.520
Hegarim, Seila.

00:12:15.840 --> 00:12:17.680
The wicked shall be turned into hell,

00:12:17.960 --> 00:12:19.900
and all the nations that forget God.

00:12:20.520 --> 00:12:23.120
For the needy shall not always be forgotten.

00:12:23.760 --> 00:12:26.720
The expectation of the poor shall not perish forever.

00:12:28.120 --> 00:12:30.200
Arise, O Lord. Let not male prevail.

00:12:30.760 --> 00:12:32.860
Let the heathen be judged in thy sight.

00:12:33.520 --> 00:12:37.580
Put them in fear, O Lord, that the nations may know themselves to be but men.

00:12:37.580 --> 00:12:37.840
Put them in fear, O Lord, that the nations may know themselves to be but men.

00:12:39.220 --> 00:12:39.740
Seila.

00:12:42.200 --> 00:12:43.240
Chapter 10

00:12:43.700 --> 00:12:45.800
Why standest thou afar off, O Lord?

00:12:45.800 --> 00:12:48.920
Why hidest thou with thyself in times of trouble?

00:12:49.800 --> 00:12:52.300
The wicked in his pride doth persecute the poor.

00:12:52.980 --> 00:12:55.900
Let them be taken into devices that they have imagined.

00:12:56.720 --> 00:12:59.020
For the wicked boasteth of his heart's desire,

00:12:59.220 --> 00:13:02.000
and blessed the covetous, and the Lord abhorreth.

00:13:02.840 --> 00:13:05.020
The wicked, through the pride of his countenance,

00:13:05.120 --> 00:13:06.380
will not seek after God.

00:13:06.880 --> 00:13:08.600
God is not in all of his thoughts.

00:13:09.460 --> 00:13:11.080
His ways are always grievous.

00:13:11.080 --> 00:13:14.300
Thy judgments are far above out of his sight.

00:13:14.880 --> 00:13:17.080
As for all his enemies, he puffeth at them.

00:13:18.200 --> 00:13:19.680
He hath said in his heart,

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:23.560
I shall not be moved, for I shall never be in adversity.

00:13:24.660 --> 00:13:27.480
His mouth is full of cursing and deceit and fraud.

00:13:27.940 --> 00:13:30.020
Under his tongue is mischief and vanity.

00:13:31.460 --> 00:13:34.040
He sitteth in the lurking places of the villages.

00:13:34.680 --> 00:13:37.380
In the secret places doth he murder the innocents.

00:13:37.780 --> 00:13:39.860
His eyes are provably set against the poor.

00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:43.980
He lieth and waits secretly, as a lion in his den.

00:13:44.500 --> 00:13:46.360
He lieth and waits to catch the poor.

00:13:46.860 --> 00:13:50.080
He doth catch the poor when he doth him into his net.

00:13:51.120 --> 00:13:53.140
He croucheth and humbleeth himself,

00:13:53.560 --> 00:13:55.560
that the poor may fall by his strong ones.

00:13:56.440 --> 00:13:57.800
He hath said in his heart,

00:13:58.180 --> 00:14:00.920
God hath forgotten. He hath hideth his face.

00:14:01.240 --> 00:14:02.740
He will never see it.

00:14:03.920 --> 00:14:07.460
Arise, O Lord! O God, what's with thine hands?

00:14:07.460 --> 00:14:08.900
Forget not the humble.

00:14:10.180 --> 00:14:12.060
Wherefore doth the wicked contemn God?

00:14:12.640 --> 00:14:16.000
He hath said in his heart, Thou wilt not require it.

00:14:16.820 --> 00:14:20.120
Thou hast seen it, for thou beholdest mischief and spikes,

00:14:20.360 --> 00:14:21.980
to equate it with thy hands.

00:14:22.820 --> 00:14:25.080
The poor committeth themselves unto thee.

00:14:25.360 --> 00:14:27.460
Thou art the helper of the fatherless.

00:14:28.240 --> 00:14:30.700
Break thou the arm of the wicked and the evil man.

00:14:31.420 --> 00:14:33.620
Seek out his wickedness till thou find none.

00:14:33.620 --> 00:14:36.600
The Lord is king for ever and ever.

00:14:36.960 --> 00:14:38.940
The heathen are perished out of his land.

00:14:40.480 --> 00:14:43.080
Lord, thou hast heard the desire of the humble.

00:14:43.420 --> 00:14:44.920
Thou wilt prepare their hearts.

00:14:45.480 --> 00:14:47.180
Thou wilt cause thine ear to hear,

00:14:47.360 --> 00:14:49.240
to judge the fatherless and the oppressed,

00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:52.080
that the man of the earth may no more oppress.

00:14:54.140 --> 00:14:55.260
Chapter 11

00:14:55.900 --> 00:14:58.040
And the Lord put on my trust.

00:14:58.040 --> 00:15:01.520
How say ye to my soul, flee as a bird to your mountain?

00:15:02.280 --> 00:15:04.740
For lo, the wicked bend their bow.

00:15:05.300 --> 00:15:07.640
They make ready their arrow upon the strain,

00:15:07.840 --> 00:15:10.440
that they may privilege shoot at their uprightened hearts.

00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:13.340
If the foundations be destroyed,

00:15:13.500 --> 00:15:14.860
what can the righteous do?

00:15:15.760 --> 00:15:17.460
The Lord is in his holy temple.

00:15:17.900 --> 00:15:19.520
The Lord's throne is in heaven.

00:15:20.340 --> 00:15:23.980
His eyes behold, his eyelids try, the children of men.

00:15:24.900 --> 00:15:26.980
The Lord trieth the righteous,

00:15:27.400 --> 00:15:30.180
but the wicked in him that loveth violence is all hated.

00:15:31.420 --> 00:15:33.420
Upon the wicked he shall win snares,

00:15:33.660 --> 00:15:36.160
fire, and brimstone, and a horrible tempest.

00:15:36.640 --> 00:15:38.620
They shall be the portion of their cup.

00:15:38.920 --> 00:15:41.220
For the righteous Lord loveth righteousness.

00:15:41.680 --> 00:15:43.620
His countenance doth behold their upright.

00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:48.860
And the Psalms 1-11.

00:15:55.520 --> 00:15:56.920
Thank you.

00:15:58.920 --> 00:16:24.920
Psalm 12 Help, Lord, for the godly man ceaseth for

00:16:24.920 --> 00:16:27.460
the faithful fail from among the children of men.

00:16:28.020 --> 00:16:33.400
They speak vanity, everyone with his neighbor, with flattering lips and with a double heart

00:16:33.400 --> 00:16:34.200
do they speak.

00:16:34.840 --> 00:16:39.460
The Lord shall cut off all flattering lips, and the tongue that speaketh proud things.

00:16:40.380 --> 00:16:46.560
Who have said, with our tongue will we prevail, our lips are our own, who is Lord over us?

00:16:47.640 --> 00:16:52.760
For the oppression of the poor, for the sighing of the needy, now will I arise, sayeth the

00:16:52.760 --> 00:16:52.980
Lord.

00:16:52.980 --> 00:16:56.880
I will set him in safety, from him that puffeth at him.

00:16:57.340 --> 00:17:02.940
The words of the Lord are pure words, a silver tried in a furnace of earth, purified seven

00:17:02.940 --> 00:17:03.500
times.

00:17:04.280 --> 00:17:09.100
Thou shalt keep them, O Lord, thou shalt preserve them from this generation forever.

00:17:10.080 --> 00:17:13.900
The wicked walk on every side, when the vilest men are exalted.

00:17:15.820 --> 00:17:21.040
Psalm 13 How long wilt thou forget me, O Lord, forever?

00:17:21.720 --> 00:17:24.100
How long wilt thou hide thy face from me?

00:17:24.960 --> 00:17:29.300
How long shall I take counsel in my soul, having sorrow in my heart daily?

00:17:29.980 --> 00:17:32.500
How long shall mine enemy be exalted over me?

00:17:33.400 --> 00:17:39.160
Consider and hear me, O Lord my God, lighten mine eyes, lest I sleep the sleep of death.

00:17:39.720 --> 00:17:44.820
Lest mine enemy say, I have prevailed against him, and those that trouble me rejoice when

00:17:44.820 --> 00:17:45.500
I am moved.

00:17:45.500 --> 00:17:50.520
But I have trusted in thy mercy, my heart shall rejoice in thy salvation.

00:17:51.080 --> 00:17:55.100
I will sing unto the Lord, because he hath dealt bountifully with me.

00:17:57.360 --> 00:18:02.080
Psalm 14 The fool hath said in his heart, There is no

00:18:02.080 --> 00:18:02.400
God.

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:07.700
They are corrupt, they have done abominable works, there is none that doeth good.

00:18:08.240 --> 00:18:12.420
The Lord looked down from heaven upon the children of men, to see if there were any

00:18:12.420 --> 00:18:14.280
that did understand and seek God.

00:18:15.020 --> 00:18:18.700
They are all gone aside, they are all together become filthy.

00:18:19.480 --> 00:18:22.300
There is none that doeth good, no, not one.

00:18:23.680 --> 00:18:25.760
Have all the workers of iniquity no knowledge?

00:18:26.740 --> 00:18:30.320
Who eat up my people as they eat bread, and call not upon the Lord?

00:18:30.720 --> 00:18:34.600
There were they in great fear, for God is in the generation of the righteous.

00:18:35.700 --> 00:18:39.340
Ye have shamed the counsel of the poor, because the Lord is his refuge.

00:18:40.320 --> 00:18:43.040
O that the salvation of Israel were come out of Zion!

00:18:43.640 --> 00:18:49.060
When the Lord bringeth back the captivity of his people, Jacob shall rejoice, and Israel

00:18:49.060 --> 00:18:49.960
shall be glad.

00:18:51.880 --> 00:18:56.420
Psalm 15 Lord, who shall abide in thy tabernacle?

00:18:56.660 --> 00:18:58.200
Who shall dwell in thy holy hill?

00:18:59.100 --> 00:19:03.760
He that walketh uprightly, and worketh righteousness, and speaketh the truth in his heart.

00:19:04.260 --> 00:19:09.680
He that backbiteeth not with his tongue, nor doeth evil to his neighbour, nor taketh up

00:19:09.680 --> 00:19:11.100
a reproach against his neighbour.

00:19:11.100 --> 00:19:16.680
In whose eyes a vile person is contemned, but he honoreth them that fear the Lord.

00:19:17.500 --> 00:19:20.440
He that sweareth to his own hurt, and changeth not.

00:19:21.140 --> 00:19:25.320
He that putteth not out his money to usury, nor taketh reward against the innocent.

00:19:25.940 --> 00:19:28.620
He that doeth these things shall never be moved.

00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:35.440
Psalm 16 Preserve me, O God, for in thee do I put my

00:19:35.440 --> 00:19:35.880
trust.

00:19:35.880 --> 00:19:42.500
O my soul, thou hast said unto the Lord, Thou art my Lord, my goodness extendeth not to

00:19:42.500 --> 00:19:47.780
thee, but to the saints that are in the earth, and to the excellent in whom is all my delight.

00:19:48.640 --> 00:19:51.500
Their sorrows shall be multiplied that hasten after another God.

00:19:51.960 --> 00:19:56.560
Their drink offerings of blood will I not offer, nor take up their names into my lips.

00:19:57.300 --> 00:20:02.340
The Lord is the portion of mine inheritance, and of my cup thou maintainest my lot.

00:20:02.880 --> 00:20:07.900
The lines have fallen unto me in pleasant places, yea, I have a goodly heritage.

00:20:08.800 --> 00:20:11.300
I will bless the Lord, who hath given me counsel.

00:20:11.980 --> 00:20:14.340
My reigns also instruct me in the night's seasons.

00:20:15.320 --> 00:20:20.120
I have set the Lord always before me, because he is at my right hand I shall not be moved.

00:20:21.040 --> 00:20:24.000
Therefore my heart is glad, and my glory rejoiceth.

00:20:24.460 --> 00:20:26.380
My flesh also shall rest in hope.

00:20:27.280 --> 00:20:31.840
For thou wilt not leave my soul in hell, neither wilt thou suffer thine holy wand to

00:20:31.840 --> 00:20:32.400
the corruption.

00:20:33.300 --> 00:20:37.520
Thou wilt shew me the path of life, in thy presence is fullness of joy.

00:20:38.060 --> 00:20:40.540
At thy right hand there are pleasures for evermore.

00:20:42.680 --> 00:20:43.720
Psalm 17.

00:20:44.880 --> 00:20:51.200
Hear the right, O Lord, attend unto my cry, give ear unto my prayer, that goeth not out

00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:52.080
of feigned lips.

00:20:52.640 --> 00:20:57.500
Let my sentence come forth from thy presence, let thine eyes behold the things that are

00:20:57.500 --> 00:20:57.840
equal.

00:20:58.400 --> 00:21:04.120
Thou hast proved mine heart, thou hast visited me in the night, thou hast tried me and shalt

00:21:04.120 --> 00:21:04.740
find nothing.

00:21:05.680 --> 00:21:08.200
I am purposed that my mouth shall not transgress.

00:21:09.320 --> 00:21:14.000
Concerning the works of men, by the word of thy lips, I have kept me from the paths of

00:21:14.000 --> 00:21:14.760
the destroyer.

00:21:15.240 --> 00:21:19.000
Hold my goings in thy paths, that my footsteps slip not.

00:21:19.680 --> 00:21:25.720
I have called upon thee, for thou wilt hear me, O God, incline thy near unto me, and hear

00:21:25.720 --> 00:21:26.400
my speech.

00:21:26.980 --> 00:21:32.880
Shew thy marvellous loving-kindness, O thou that savest by thy right hand, them which

00:21:32.880 --> 00:21:36.160
put their trust in thee, from those that rise up against them.

00:21:36.980 --> 00:21:41.020
Keep me as the apple of the eye, hide me under the shadow of thy wings.

00:21:41.860 --> 00:21:48.000
From the wicked that oppress me, from my deadly enemies who compass me about, they are enclosed

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:48.880
in their own fat.

00:21:49.460 --> 00:21:51.120
With their mouth they speak proudly.

00:21:51.840 --> 00:21:53.740
They have now compassed us in our steps.

00:21:54.260 --> 00:21:56.820
They have set their eyes bowing down to the earth.

00:21:57.880 --> 00:22:03.320
Like as a lion that is greedy of his prey, and as it were a young lion lurking in secret

00:22:03.320 --> 00:22:03.920
places.

00:22:04.780 --> 00:22:11.040
Arise, O Lord, disappoint him, cast him down, deliver my soul from the wicked, which is

00:22:11.040 --> 00:22:11.640
thy sword.

00:22:12.260 --> 00:22:17.120
From men which are thy hand, O Lord, from men of the world, which have their portion

00:22:17.120 --> 00:22:22.420
in this life, and whose belly thou fillest with thy hid treasure, they are full of children,

00:22:22.420 --> 00:22:25.780
and leave the rest of their substance to their babes.

00:22:26.020 --> 00:22:28.860
As for me, I will behold thy face in righteousness.

00:22:29.640 --> 00:22:33.740
I shall be satisfied, when I awake, with thy likeness.

00:22:35.220 --> 00:22:35.920
Psalm 18.

00:22:36.780 --> 00:22:42.560
I will love thee, O Lord, my strength, for Lord is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer.

00:22:43.160 --> 00:22:49.020
My God, my strength, in whom I will trust, my buckler, and the horn of my salvation,

00:22:49.220 --> 00:22:50.220
and my high tower.

00:22:50.920 --> 00:22:54.320
I will call upon the Lord, who is worthy to be praised.

00:22:54.760 --> 00:22:56.640
So shall I be saved from mine enemies.

00:22:57.540 --> 00:23:01.880
The sorrows of death compassed me, and the floods of ungodly men made me afraid.

00:23:02.560 --> 00:23:04.440
The sorrows of hell compassed me about.

00:23:05.140 --> 00:23:06.980
The snares of death prevented me.

00:23:07.800 --> 00:23:11.720
In my distress I called upon the Lord, and cried unto my God.

00:23:12.520 --> 00:23:18.060
He heard my voice out of his temple, and my cry came before him, even into his ears.

00:23:18.060 --> 00:23:23.780
Then the earth shook and trembled, the foundations also of the hills moved, and were shaken,

00:23:24.200 --> 00:23:25.400
because he was wroth.

00:23:26.300 --> 00:23:31.420
There went up a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth devoured, coals

00:23:31.420 --> 00:23:32.760
were kindled by it.

00:23:33.400 --> 00:23:38.400
He bowed in the heavens also, and came down, and darkness was under his feet.

00:23:39.240 --> 00:23:44.220
And he rode upon a cherub, and did fly, yea, he did fly upon the wings of the wind.

00:23:44.980 --> 00:23:50.820
He made darkness his secret place, his pavilion round about him were dark waters, and thick

00:23:50.820 --> 00:23:51.880
clouds of the skies.

00:23:52.940 --> 00:23:57.820
At the brightness that was before him, his thick clouds passed, hailstones and coals

00:23:57.820 --> 00:23:58.340
of fire.

00:23:59.660 --> 00:24:05.080
The Lord also thundered in the heavens, and the highest gave his voice, hailstones and

00:24:05.080 --> 00:24:06.200
coals of fire.

00:24:06.880 --> 00:24:12.460
Yea, he sent out his arrows, and scattered them, and he shot out lightnings, and discomforted

00:24:12.460 --> 00:24:12.800
them.

00:24:13.220 --> 00:24:17.320
Then the channels of water were seen, and the foundations of the world were discovered

00:24:17.320 --> 00:24:21.140
at thy rebuke, O Lord, at the blast of the breath of thy nostrils.

00:24:22.260 --> 00:24:28.500
He sent from above, he took me, he drew me out of many waters, he delivered me from my

00:24:28.500 --> 00:24:32.860
strong enemy, and from them which hated me, for they were too strong for me.

00:24:33.280 --> 00:24:37.120
They prevented me in the day of my calamity, but the Lord was my stay.

00:24:37.700 --> 00:24:43.520
He brought me forth also into a large place, he delivered me because he delighted in me.

00:24:44.080 --> 00:24:49.560
The Lord rewarded me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands hath

00:24:49.560 --> 00:24:50.760
he recompensed me.

00:24:51.120 --> 00:24:55.480
For I have kept the ways of the Lord, and have not wickedly departed from my God.

00:24:56.520 --> 00:25:01.020
For all his judgments were before me, and I did not put away his statutes from me.

00:25:01.460 --> 00:25:05.960
I was also upright before him, and I kept myself from mine iniquity.

00:25:05.960 --> 00:25:11.460
Therefore hath the Lord recompensed me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness

00:25:11.460 --> 00:25:12.900
of my hands in his eyesight.

00:25:14.220 --> 00:25:19.280
With the merciful thou wilt shew thyself merciful, with an upright man thou wilt shew thyself

00:25:19.280 --> 00:25:24.520
upright, with the pure thou wilt shew thyself pure, and with the forward thou wilt shew

00:25:24.520 --> 00:25:25.460
thyself forward.

00:25:26.160 --> 00:25:30.000
For thou wilt save the afflicted people, but wilt bring down high looks.

00:25:30.480 --> 00:25:34.640
For thou wilt light my candle, the Lord my God will enlighten my darkness.

00:25:35.240 --> 00:25:40.180
For by thee I have run through a troop, and by my God have I leaped over a wall.

00:25:41.340 --> 00:25:46.000
As for God, his way is perfect, the word of the Lord is tried.

00:25:46.500 --> 00:25:48.840
He is a buckler to all those that trust in him.

00:25:49.300 --> 00:25:53.160
For who is God, saith the Lord, or who is a rock, saith our God?

00:25:53.700 --> 00:25:57.440
It is God that girdeth me with strength, and maketh my way perfect.

00:25:58.080 --> 00:26:02.200
He maketh my feet like hind's feet, and setteth me upon my high places.

00:26:02.820 --> 00:26:07.660
He teacheth my hands to war, so that a bow of steel is broken by mine arms.

00:26:08.420 --> 00:26:13.400
Thou hast also given me the shield of thy salvation, and thy right hand hath holden

00:26:13.400 --> 00:26:16.360
me up, and thy gentleness hath made me great.

00:26:17.040 --> 00:26:20.760
Thou hast enlarged my steps under me, that my feet did not slip.

00:26:21.380 --> 00:26:24.260
I have pursued mine enemies, and overtaken them.

00:26:24.880 --> 00:26:27.280
Neither did I turn again till they were consumed.

00:26:27.840 --> 00:26:30.720
I have wounded them, that they were not able to rise.

00:26:30.720 --> 00:26:32.780
They are fallen under my feet.

00:26:33.280 --> 00:26:35.820
For thou hast girded me with strength unto the battle.

00:26:36.400 --> 00:26:39.180
Thou hast subdued under me those that rose up against me.

00:26:40.120 --> 00:26:44.720
Thou hast also given me the necks of mine enemies, that I might destroy them that hate

00:26:44.720 --> 00:26:45.300
me.

00:26:45.520 --> 00:26:50.980
They cried, but there was none to save them, even unto the Lord, but he answered them not.

00:26:51.580 --> 00:26:54.240
Then did I beat them small as the dust before the wind.

00:26:54.800 --> 00:26:57.340
I did cast them out as the dirt in the streets.

00:26:57.820 --> 00:27:02.380
Thou hast delivered me from the strivings of the people, and thou hast made me the head

00:27:02.380 --> 00:27:03.200
of the heathen.

00:27:03.520 --> 00:27:06.300
A people whom I have not known shall serve me.

00:27:06.720 --> 00:27:09.400
As soon as they hear of me, they shall obey me.

00:27:09.680 --> 00:27:12.120
The strangers shall submit themselves unto me.

00:27:12.480 --> 00:27:16.280
The strangers shall fade away, and be afraid out of their close places.

00:27:16.960 --> 00:27:22.460
The Lord liveth, and blessed be my rock, and let the God of my salvation be exalted.

00:27:23.460 --> 00:27:27.640
It is God that avengeth me, and subdueth the people under me.

00:27:28.020 --> 00:27:33.720
He delivereth me from mine enemies, yea, thou liftest me up above those that rise up against

00:27:33.720 --> 00:27:34.160
me.

00:27:34.640 --> 00:27:36.680
Thou hast delivered me from the violent man.

00:27:37.260 --> 00:27:42.720
Therefore will I give thanks unto thee, O Lord, among the heathen, and sing praises unto

00:27:42.720 --> 00:27:43.300
thy name.

00:27:43.900 --> 00:27:50.280
Great deliverance giveth he to his king, and sheweth mercy to his anointed, to David, and

00:27:50.280 --> 00:27:51.760
to his seed for evermore.

00:27:53.780 --> 00:27:54.740
Psalm 19.

00:27:55.780 --> 00:28:00.060
The heavens declare the glory of God, and the firmament sheweth his handiwork.

00:28:00.720 --> 00:28:04.760
Day unto day uttereth speech, and night unto night sheweth knowledge.

00:28:05.540 --> 00:28:08.880
There is no speech nor language where their voice is not heard.

00:28:09.880 --> 00:28:13.980
Their line is gone out through all the earth, and their words to the end of the world.

00:28:14.580 --> 00:28:19.620
In them hath he set a tabernacle for the sun, which is as a bridegroom coming out of his

00:28:19.620 --> 00:28:22.740
chamber, and rejoiceth as a strong man to run a race.

00:28:23.820 --> 00:28:29.080
His going forth is from the end of the heaven, and his circuit unto the ends of it, and there

00:28:29.080 --> 00:28:30.820
is nothing hid from the heat thereof.

00:28:31.240 --> 00:28:34.340
The law of the Lord is perfect, converting the soul.

00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:38.500
The testimony of the Lord is sure, making wise the simple.

00:28:39.320 --> 00:28:42.480
The statutes of the Lord are right, rejoicing the heart.

00:28:43.100 --> 00:28:46.420
The commandment of the Lord is pure, enlightening the eyes.

00:28:46.950 --> 00:28:50.020
The fear of the Lord is clean, enduring forever.

00:28:50.880 --> 00:28:53.440
The judgments of the Lord are true and righteous altogether.

00:28:54.640 --> 00:29:00.480
More to be desired are they than gold, yea, than much fine gold, sweeter also than honey

00:29:00.480 --> 00:29:01.360
and the honeycomb.

00:29:02.520 --> 00:29:07.280
Moreover by them is thy servant warned, and in keeping of them there is great reward.

00:29:07.880 --> 00:29:09.360
Who can understand his errors?

00:29:10.020 --> 00:29:11.820
Cleanse thou me from secret faults.

00:29:12.460 --> 00:29:15.160
Keep back thy servant also from presumptuous sins.

00:29:15.160 --> 00:29:17.520
Let them not have dominion over me.

00:29:18.100 --> 00:29:21.940
Then shall I be upright, and I shall be innocent from the great transgression.

00:29:23.220 --> 00:29:28.020
Let the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heart be acceptable in thy sight, O

00:29:28.020 --> 00:29:30.500
Lord, my strength and my redeemer.

00:29:32.080 --> 00:29:32.960
Psalm 20.

00:29:34.180 --> 00:29:36.020
The Lord hear thee in the day of trouble.

00:29:36.540 --> 00:29:38.580
The name of the God of Jacob defend thee.

00:29:39.520 --> 00:29:42.880
Send thee help from the sanctuary, and strengthen thee out of Zion.

00:29:43.960 --> 00:29:49.000
Remember all thy offerings, and accept thy burnt sacrifice, Selah.

00:29:49.180 --> 00:29:52.780
Grant thee according to thine own heart, and fulfil all thy counsel.

00:29:53.880 --> 00:29:57.320
We will rejoice in thy salvation, and in the name of our God.

00:29:57.960 --> 00:29:59.180
We will set up our banners.

00:29:59.720 --> 00:30:01.480
The Lord fulfil all thy petitions.

00:30:02.600 --> 00:30:04.780
Now know I that the Lord saveth his anointed.

00:30:05.340 --> 00:30:09.800
He will hear him from his holy heaven, with the saving strength of his right hand.

00:30:10.680 --> 00:30:15.920
Some trust in chariots, and some in horses, but we will remember the name of the Lord

00:30:15.920 --> 00:30:16.520
our God.

00:30:17.680 --> 00:30:21.000
They are brought down and fallen, but we are risen and stand upright.

00:30:21.820 --> 00:30:24.880
Save Lord, let the King hear us when we call.

00:30:26.640 --> 00:30:27.600
Psalm 21.

00:30:28.780 --> 00:30:33.300
The King shall joy in thy strength, O Lord, and in thy salvation how greatly shall he

00:30:33.300 --> 00:30:33.800
rejoice.

00:30:34.600 --> 00:30:41.000
Thou hast given him his heart's desire, and hast not withholden the request of his lips, Selah.

00:30:41.240 --> 00:30:43.740
For thou preventest him with the blessings of goodness.

00:30:44.440 --> 00:30:46.780
Thou settest a crown of pure gold on his head.

00:30:47.600 --> 00:30:52.740
He asked life of thee, and thou gavest it him, even length of days forever and ever.

00:30:53.280 --> 00:30:55.280
His glory is great in thy salvation.

00:30:55.740 --> 00:30:58.320
Honor and majesty hast thou laid upon him.

00:30:58.700 --> 00:31:00.820
For thou hast made him most blessed forever.

00:31:01.440 --> 00:31:04.200
Thou hast made him exceeding glad with thy countenance.

00:31:04.720 --> 00:31:09.340
For the King trusteth in the Lord, and through the mercy of the Most High he shall not be

00:31:09.340 --> 00:31:09.700
moved.

00:31:10.660 --> 00:31:15.260
Thine hand shall find out all thine enemies, thy right hand shall find out those that hate

00:31:15.260 --> 00:31:15.680
thee.

00:31:16.020 --> 00:31:18.800
Thou shalt make them as a fiery oven in the time of thine anger.

00:31:19.560 --> 00:31:23.660
The Lord shall swallow them up in his wrath, and the fire shall devour them.

00:31:24.400 --> 00:31:28.600
Their fruit shalt thou destroy from the earth, and their seed from among the children of

00:31:28.600 --> 00:31:31.220
For they intended evil against thee.

00:31:31.700 --> 00:31:35.520
They imagined a mischievous device, which they are not able to perform.

00:31:36.340 --> 00:31:40.580
Therefore shalt thou make them turn their back, when thou shalt make ready thine arrows

00:31:40.580 --> 00:31:43.180
upon thy strings, against the face of them.

00:31:43.640 --> 00:31:48.900
Be thou exalted, Lord, in thine own strength, so we will sing and praise thy power.

00:31:58.600 --> 00:32:04.080
Thou shalt make them turn thine arrows upon thy strings, against the face of them.

00:32:06.080 --> 00:32:10.880
Psalm 22-31

00:32:28.680 --> 00:32:31.700
The Book of Psalms

00:32:31.700 --> 00:32:35.540
King James Version, Psalm 22

00:32:36.520 --> 00:32:42.300
My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?

00:32:42.780 --> 00:32:49.040
Why art thou so far from helping me, and from the words of my roaring?

00:32:49.520 --> 00:32:54.340
O my God, I cry in the daytime, but thou hearest not,

00:32:54.580 --> 00:32:57.720
and in the night season, and am not silent.

00:32:57.720 --> 00:33:03.880
But thou art holy, O thou that inhabitest the praises of Israel.

00:33:04.660 --> 00:33:10.600
Our fathers trusted in thee, they trusted, and thou didst deliver them.

00:33:11.280 --> 00:33:14.880
They cried unto thee, and were delivered.

00:33:15.220 --> 00:33:18.040
They trusted in thee, and were not confounded.

00:33:18.660 --> 00:33:26.140
But I am a worm, and no man, a reproach of men, and despised of the people.

00:33:26.140 --> 00:33:31.780
All they that see me laugh me to scorn, they shoot out the lip.

00:33:32.240 --> 00:33:37.820
They shake the head, saying, he trusted on the Lord that he would deliver him.

00:33:38.160 --> 00:33:41.920
Let him deliver him, seeing he delighted in him.

00:33:42.740 --> 00:33:47.120
But thou art he that took me out of the womb.

00:33:47.440 --> 00:33:52.960
Thou didst make me hope when I was upon my mother's breast.

00:33:52.960 --> 00:33:59.660
I was cast upon thee from the womb, thou art my God, from my mother's belly.

00:34:00.480 --> 00:34:06.080
Be not far from me, for trouble is near, for there is none to help.

00:34:06.680 --> 00:34:13.580
Many bulls have compassed me, strong bulls of Bashan have beset me round.

00:34:13.580 --> 00:34:22.440
They gaped upon me with their mouths, as a ravening and a roaring lion.

00:34:23.280 --> 00:34:27.840
I am poured out like water, and all my bones are out of joint.

00:34:28.100 --> 00:34:34.060
My heart is like wax, it is melted in the midst of my bowels.

00:34:34.500 --> 00:34:40.820
My strength is dried up like a potsherd, and my tongue cleaveth to my jaws.

00:34:40.820 --> 00:34:45.220
And thou hast brought me into the dust of death.

00:34:45.780 --> 00:34:51.140
For dogs have compassed me, the assembly of the wicked have enclosed me.

00:34:51.160 --> 00:34:53.580
They pierced my hands and my feet.

00:34:54.120 --> 00:34:59.220
I may tell all my bones, they look and stare upon me.

00:34:59.700 --> 00:35:05.220
They part my garments among them, and cast lots upon my vesture.

00:35:05.220 --> 00:35:12.660
But be not thou far from me, O Lord, O my strength haste thee to help me.

00:35:12.920 --> 00:35:18.180
Deliver my soul from the sword, my darling from the power of the dog.

00:35:18.680 --> 00:35:25.220
Save me from the lion's mouth, for thou hast heard me from the horns of the unicorns.

00:35:25.940 --> 00:35:34.000
I will declare thy name unto my brethren, in the midst of the congregation will I praise thee.

00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:37.560
Ye that fear the Lord, praise him.

00:35:37.880 --> 00:35:42.940
All ye the seed of Jacob, glorify him and fear him.

00:35:43.200 --> 00:35:46.680
All ye the seed of Israel.

00:35:48.120 --> 00:35:54.040
For he hath not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted.

00:35:54.160 --> 00:35:56.620
Neither hath he hid his face from him.

00:35:56.620 --> 00:36:04.400
But when he cried unto him, he heard, My praise shall be of thee in the great congregation.

00:36:04.860 --> 00:36:08.240
I will pay my vows before them that fear him.

00:36:08.840 --> 00:36:11.820
The meek shall eat and be satisfied.

00:36:12.160 --> 00:36:16.140
They shall praise the Lord that seek him.

00:36:16.680 --> 00:36:19.120
Your heart shall live forever.

00:36:19.580 --> 00:36:24.960
All the ends of the world shall remember and turn unto the Lord.

00:36:24.960 --> 00:36:30.100
And all the kindreds of the nations shall worship before thee.

00:36:30.640 --> 00:36:37.600
For the kingdom is the Lord's and he is the governor among the nations.

00:36:38.600 --> 00:36:42.900
All they that be fat upon earth shall eat and worship.

00:36:43.300 --> 00:36:47.700
All they that go down to the dust shall bow before him.

00:36:48.120 --> 00:36:50.880
And none can keep alive his own soul.

00:36:51.280 --> 00:36:53.400
A seed shall serve him.

00:36:53.400 --> 00:36:57.060
It shall be accounted to the Lord for a generation.

00:36:57.600 --> 00:37:07.620
They shall come and shall declare his righteousness unto a people that shall be born that he hath done this.

00:37:08.540 --> 00:37:10.220
Psalm 23

00:37:10.220 --> 00:37:13.020
The Lord is my shepherd.

00:37:13.400 --> 00:37:14.600
I shall not want.

00:37:15.200 --> 00:37:18.760
He maketh me to lie down in green pastures.

00:37:19.140 --> 00:37:22.180
He leadeth me beside the still waters.

00:37:22.180 --> 00:37:24.420
He restoreth my soul.

00:37:25.140 --> 00:37:30.420
He leadeth me in the paths of righteousness for his name's sake.

00:37:30.860 --> 00:37:37.500
Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil.

00:37:37.920 --> 00:37:39.160
For thou art with me.

00:37:39.660 --> 00:37:43.280
Thy rod and thy staff, they comfort me.

00:37:43.720 --> 00:37:48.660
Thou preparest a table before me in the presence of mine enemies.

00:37:48.660 --> 00:37:52.100
Thou anointest my head with oil.

00:37:52.480 --> 00:37:54.600
My cup runneth over.

00:37:55.700 --> 00:38:01.360
Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life.

00:38:01.480 --> 00:38:06.820
And I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

00:38:08.320 --> 00:38:09.640
Psalm 24

00:38:09.640 --> 00:38:15.990
The earth is the Lord's and the fullness thereof, the world and they that dwell therein.

00:38:15.990 --> 00:38:20.890
For he hath founded it upon the seas and established it upon the floods.

00:38:21.410 --> 00:38:28.170
Who shall ascend into the hill of the Lord, or who shall stand in his holy place?

00:38:28.690 --> 00:38:37.990
He that hath clean hands and a pure heart, who hath not lifted up his soul unto vanity, nor sworn deceitfully.

00:38:37.990 --> 00:38:46.190
He shall receive the blessing from the Lord, and righteousness from the God of his salvation.

00:38:46.970 --> 00:38:54.990
This is the generation of them that seek him, that seek thy face, O Jacob, Selah.

00:38:55.910 --> 00:39:06.730
Lift up your heads, O ye gates, and be ye lift up, ye everlasting doors, and the King of Glory shall come in.

00:39:06.730 --> 00:39:15.170
Who is this King of Glory, the Lord strong and mighty, the Lord mighty in battle?

00:39:15.630 --> 00:39:25.370
Lift up your heads, O ye gates, even lift them up, ye everlasting doors, and the King of Glory shall come in.

00:39:25.610 --> 00:39:30.110
Who is this King of Glory, the Lord of hosts?

00:39:30.490 --> 00:39:35.030
He is the King of Glory, Selah.

00:39:35.030 --> 00:39:37.890
Psalm 25.

00:39:38.750 --> 00:39:41.970
Unto thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.

00:39:42.910 --> 00:39:52.070
O my God, I trust in thee, let me not be ashamed, let not mine enemies triumph over me.

00:39:52.870 --> 00:40:00.850
Yea, let none that wait on thee be ashamed, let them be ashamed which transgress without cause.

00:40:00.850 --> 00:40:05.110
Show me thy ways, O Lord, teach me thy paths.

00:40:06.470 --> 00:40:12.350
Lead me in thy truth and teach me, for thou art the God of my salvation.

00:40:12.970 --> 00:40:15.310
On thee do I wait all the day.

00:40:15.950 --> 00:40:23.970
Remember, O Lord, thy tender mercies and thy loving kindnesses, for they have been ever of old.

00:40:23.970 --> 00:40:28.130
Remember not the sins of my youth, nor my transgressions.

00:40:29.130 --> 00:40:35.330
According to thy mercy, remember thou me, for thy goodness' sake, O Lord.

00:40:36.210 --> 00:40:41.650
Good and upright is the Lord, therefore will he teach sinners in the way.

00:40:42.190 --> 00:40:47.590
The meek will he guide in judgment, and the meek will he teach his way.

00:40:47.590 --> 00:40:56.970
All the paths of the Lord are mercy and truth unto such as keep his covenant and his testimonies.

00:40:57.410 --> 00:41:02.450
For thy name's sake, O Lord, pardon my iniquity, for it is great.

00:41:03.030 --> 00:41:05.310
What man is he that feareth the Lord?

00:41:05.770 --> 00:41:09.770
Him shall he teach in the way that he shall choose.

00:41:10.290 --> 00:41:15.930
His soul shall dwell at ease, and his seed shall inherit the earth.

00:41:15.930 --> 00:41:23.790
The secret of the Lord is with them that fear him, and he will show them his covenant.

00:41:24.770 --> 00:41:32.070
Mine eyes are ever toward the Lord, for he shall pluck my feet out of the net.

00:41:32.750 --> 00:41:40.370
Turn thee unto me and have mercy upon me, for I am desolate and afflicted.

00:41:40.370 --> 00:41:47.590
The troubles of my heart are enlarged. O, bring thou me out of my distresses.

00:41:47.770 --> 00:41:53.650
Look upon mine affliction and my pain, and forgive all my sins.

00:41:53.970 --> 00:42:00.350
Consider mine enemies, for they are many, and they hate me with cruel hatred.

00:42:01.270 --> 00:42:08.190
O, keep my soul and deliver me. Let me not be ashamed, for I put my trust in thee.

00:42:08.190 --> 00:42:14.130
Let integrity and uprightness preserve me, for I wait on thee.

00:42:14.770 --> 00:42:19.610
Redeem Israel, O God, out of all his troubles.

00:42:21.330 --> 00:42:22.930
Psalm 26

00:42:22.930 --> 00:42:27.390
Judge me, O Lord, for I have walked in mine integrity.

00:42:27.950 --> 00:42:32.610
I have trusted also in the Lord, therefore I shall not slide.

00:42:32.610 --> 00:42:39.030
Examine me, O Lord, and prove me. Try my reins and my heart,

00:42:39.590 --> 00:42:45.010
for thy loving kindness is before mine eyes, and I have walked in thy truth.

00:42:45.550 --> 00:42:51.530
I have not sat with vain persons, neither will I go in with dissemblers.

00:42:52.230 --> 00:42:57.710
I have hated the congregation of evildoers, and will not sit with the wicked.

00:42:57.710 --> 00:43:02.030
I will wash mine hands in innocency.

00:43:03.010 --> 00:43:09.970
So will I compass thine altar, O Lord, that I may publish with the voice of thanksgiving

00:43:10.290 --> 00:43:13.310
and tell of all thy wondrous works.

00:43:14.050 --> 00:43:21.170
Lord, I have loved the habitation of thy house, the place where thine honor dwelleth.

00:43:21.170 --> 00:43:27.850
Gather not my soul with sinners, nor my life with bloody men,

00:43:28.430 --> 00:43:33.310
in whose hands is mischief, and their right hand is full of bribes.

00:43:33.630 --> 00:43:37.010
But as for me, I will walk in mine integrity.

00:43:37.530 --> 00:43:41.090
Redeem me and be merciful unto me.

00:43:41.270 --> 00:43:44.710
My foot standeth in an even place.

00:43:45.250 --> 00:43:49.470
In the congregations will I bless the Lord.

00:43:51.110 --> 00:43:52.550
Psalm 27

00:43:52.550 --> 00:43:59.170
The Lord is my light and my salvation, whom shall I fear?

00:44:00.050 --> 00:44:04.850
The Lord is the strength of my life, of whom shall I be afraid?

00:44:05.790 --> 00:44:12.590
When the wicked, even my enemies and my foes, came upon me to eat up my flesh,

00:44:12.830 --> 00:44:14.370
they stumbled and fell.

00:44:14.370 --> 00:44:20.150
Though in hosts should encamp against me, my heart shall not fear.

00:44:20.630 --> 00:44:25.370
Though war should rise against me, in this will I be confident.

00:44:25.810 --> 00:44:30.790
One thing have I desired of the Lord that will I seek after,

00:44:31.410 --> 00:44:37.050
that I may dwell in the house of the Lord all the days of my life,

00:44:37.090 --> 00:44:42.790
to behold the beauty of the Lord and to inquire in his temple.

00:44:42.790 --> 00:44:48.150
For in the time of trouble he shall hide me in his pavilion.

00:44:48.850 --> 00:44:51.990
In the secret of his tabernacle shall he hide me.

00:44:52.190 --> 00:44:55.490
He shall set me up upon a rock.

00:44:56.290 --> 00:45:02.110
And now shall mine head be lifted up above mine enemies round about me.

00:45:02.370 --> 00:45:07.090
Therefore will I offer in his tabernacle sacrifices of joy.

00:45:07.090 --> 00:45:12.570
I will sing, yea, I will sing praises unto the Lord.

00:45:13.370 --> 00:45:20.650
Hear, O Lord, when I cry with my voice, have mercy also upon me and answer me.

00:45:21.030 --> 00:45:28.610
When thou saidest, Seek ye my face, my heart said, unto thee thy face, Lord, will I seek.

00:45:29.290 --> 00:45:34.730
Hide not thy face far from me, put not thy servant away in anger.

00:45:35.690 --> 00:45:43.590
Thou hast been my help, leave me not, neither forsake me, O God of my salvation.

00:45:44.330 --> 00:45:49.930
When my father and my mother forsake me, then the Lord will take me up.

00:45:50.650 --> 00:45:56.750
Teach me thy way, O Lord, and lead me in a plain path because of mine enemies.

00:45:56.750 --> 00:46:07.410
Deliver me not over unto the will of mine enemies, for false witnesses have risen up against me and such as breathe out cruelty.

00:46:08.190 --> 00:46:16.790
I had fainted unless I had believed to see the goodness of the Lord in the land of the living.

00:46:17.510 --> 00:46:23.630
Wait on the Lord, be of good courage, and he shall strengthen thine heart.

00:46:23.630 --> 00:46:27.550
Wait, I say, on the Lord.

00:46:29.330 --> 00:46:30.530
Psalm 28.

00:46:31.410 --> 00:46:42.630
Unto thee will I cry, O Lord, my rock, be not silent to me, lest, if thou be silent to me, I become like them that go down into the pit.

00:46:43.290 --> 00:46:51.010
Hear the voice of my supplications when I cry unto thee, when I lift up my hands toward thy holy oracle.

00:46:51.010 --> 00:47:02.970
Draw me not away with the wicked and with the workers of iniquity, which speak peace to their neighbors, but mischief is in their hearts.

00:47:03.470 --> 00:47:14.090
Give them according to their deeds, and according to the wickedness of their endeavors, give them, after the work of their hands, render to them their desert.

00:47:14.090 --> 00:47:24.490
Because they regard not the works of the Lord nor the operation of his hands, he shall destroy them and not build them up.

00:47:24.810 --> 00:47:30.210
Blessed be the Lord, because he hath heard the voice of my supplications.

00:47:30.630 --> 00:47:36.810
The Lord is my strength and my shield, my heart trusted in him, and I am helped.

00:47:36.810 --> 00:47:43.290
Therefore my heart greatly rejoiceth, and with my song will I praise him.

00:47:43.430 --> 00:47:50.210
The Lord is their strength, and he is the saving strength of his anointed.

00:47:51.110 --> 00:47:59.470
Save thy people and bless thine inheritance, feed them also, and lift them up forever.

00:48:01.250 --> 00:48:02.850
Psalm 29.

00:48:02.850 --> 00:48:10.690
Give unto the Lord, O ye mighty, give unto the Lord glory and strength.

00:48:11.530 --> 00:48:16.630
Give unto the Lord the glory due unto his name.

00:48:16.950 --> 00:48:20.510
Worship the Lord in the beauty of holiness.

00:48:21.210 --> 00:48:26.230
The voice of the Lord is upon the waters, the God of glory thundereth.

00:48:26.670 --> 00:48:28.910
The Lord is upon many waters.

00:48:28.910 --> 00:48:35.730
The voice of the Lord is powerful, the voice of the Lord is full of majesty.

00:48:36.490 --> 00:48:43.410
The voice of the Lord breaketh the cedars, yea, the Lord breaketh the cedars of Lebanon.

00:48:44.210 --> 00:48:51.710
He maketh them also to skip like a calf, Lebanon and Sirion like a young unicorn.

00:48:52.790 --> 00:48:55.970
The voice of the Lord divideth the flames of fire.

00:48:55.970 --> 00:49:03.450
The voice of the Lord shaketh the wilderness, the Lord shaketh the wilderness of Kaddish.

00:49:03.770 --> 00:49:09.930
The voice of the Lord maketh the hinds to calve and discovereth the forest.

00:49:10.310 --> 00:49:15.510
And in his temple doth everyone speak of his glory.

00:49:15.950 --> 00:49:21.830
The Lord sitteth upon the fly, yea, the Lord sitteth king forever.

00:49:21.830 --> 00:49:30.220
The Lord will give strength unto his people, the Lord will bless his people with peace.

00:49:31.730 --> 00:49:33.250
Psalm 30.

00:49:34.070 --> 00:49:46.010
I will extol thee, O Lord, for thou hast lifted me up and hast not made my foes to rejoice over me.

00:49:46.010 --> 00:49:52.290
O Lord, my God, I cried unto thee, and thou hast healed me.

00:49:52.590 --> 00:49:58.010
O Lord, thou hast brought up my soul from the grave.

00:49:58.410 --> 00:50:03.750
Thou hast kept me alive, that I should not go down to the pit.

00:50:04.490 --> 00:50:11.970
Sing unto the Lord, O ye saints of his, and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness,

00:50:11.970 --> 00:50:17.930
For his anger endureth but a moment, and his favor is life.

00:50:18.570 --> 00:50:23.370
Weeping may endure for a night, but joy cometh in the morning.

00:50:23.590 --> 00:50:28.670
And in my prosperity, I said, I shall never be moved.

00:50:29.350 --> 00:50:35.710
Lord, by thy favor, thou hast made my mountain to stand strong.

00:50:36.390 --> 00:50:39.810
Thou didst hide thy face, and I was troubled.

00:50:39.810 --> 00:50:45.850
I cried to thee, O Lord, and unto the Lord I made supplication.

00:50:46.210 --> 00:50:50.830
What profit is there in my blood when I go down to the pit?

00:50:51.270 --> 00:50:55.770
Shall the dust praise thee? Shall it declare thy truth?

00:50:56.450 --> 00:50:59.670
Hear, O Lord, and have mercy upon me.

00:51:00.010 --> 00:51:06.710
Lord, be thou my helper. Thou hast turned for me my mourning into dancing.

00:51:06.710 --> 00:51:12.550
Thou hast put off my sackcloth and girded me with gladness to the end,

00:51:12.970 --> 00:51:17.350
That my glory may sing praise to thee and not be silent.

00:51:17.850 --> 00:51:22.670
O Lord, my God, I will give thanks unto thee forever.

00:51:24.950 --> 00:51:26.230
Psalm 31.

00:51:27.730 --> 00:51:32.690
In thee, O Lord, do I put my trust. Let me never be ashamed.

00:51:32.690 --> 00:51:35.910
Deliver me in thy righteousness.

00:51:36.590 --> 00:51:41.170
Bow down thine ear to me. Deliver me speedily.

00:51:41.430 --> 00:51:46.970
Be thou my strong rock, for in house of defense to save me.

00:51:47.770 --> 00:51:50.590
For thou art my rock and my fortress.

00:51:51.070 --> 00:51:56.190
Therefore, for thy name's sake, lead me and guide me.

00:51:56.410 --> 00:52:02.030
Pull me out of the net that they have laid privily for me.

00:52:02.030 --> 00:52:07.490
For thou art my strength. Into thine hand I commit my spirit.

00:52:07.530 --> 00:52:12.950
Thou hast redeemed me, O Lord God of truth.

00:52:13.070 --> 00:52:19.910
I have hated them that regard lying vanities, but I trust in the Lord.

00:52:20.170 --> 00:52:26.390
I will be glad and rejoice in thy mercy, for thou hast considered my trouble.

00:52:26.390 --> 00:52:35.410
Thou hast known my soul in adversities and hast not shut me up into the hand of the enemy.

00:52:35.670 --> 00:52:38.710
Thou hast set my feet in a large room.

00:52:39.110 --> 00:52:43.890
Have mercy upon me, O Lord, for I am in trouble.

00:52:44.170 --> 00:52:49.290
Mine eye is consumed with grief, yea, my soul and my belly.

00:52:49.630 --> 00:52:54.310
For my life is spent with grief and my years with sighing.

00:52:54.310 --> 00:53:00.750
My strength faileth because of mine iniquity and my bones are consumed.

00:53:01.530 --> 00:53:07.810
I was of reproach among all mine enemies, but especially among my neighbors.

00:53:08.510 --> 00:53:15.430
And a fear to mine acquaintance, they that did see me without, fled from me.

00:53:15.650 --> 00:53:19.830
I am forgotten as a dead man, out of mine.

00:53:19.830 --> 00:53:26.470
I am like a broken vessel, for I have heard the slander of many.

00:53:26.810 --> 00:53:32.570
Fear was on every side while they took counsel together against me.

00:53:32.970 --> 00:53:39.330
They devised to take away my life, but I trusted in thee, O Lord.

00:53:39.630 --> 00:53:42.250
I said, Thou art my God.

00:53:43.090 --> 00:53:45.570
My times are in thy hand.

00:53:45.570 --> 00:53:51.930
Deliver me from the hand of mine enemies and from them that persecute me.

00:53:52.510 --> 00:53:55.470
Make thy face to shine upon thy servant.

00:53:55.990 --> 00:53:58.310
Save me for thy mercy's sake.

00:53:59.290 --> 00:54:03.870
Let me not be ashamed, O Lord, for I have called upon thee.

00:54:04.570 --> 00:54:08.630
Let the wicked be ashamed and let them be silent in the grave.

00:54:08.630 --> 00:54:17.470
Let the lying lips be put to silence, which speak grievous things proudly and contemptuously against the righteous.

00:54:18.310 --> 00:54:23.390
O how great is thy goodness, which thou hast laid up for them that fear thee,

00:54:23.990 --> 00:54:30.130
which thou hast wrought for them that trust in thee before the sons of men.

00:54:30.950 --> 00:54:36.870
Thou shalt hide them in the secret of thy presence from the pride of man.

00:54:36.870 --> 00:54:43.110
Thou shalt keep them secretly in a pavilion from the strife of tongues.

00:54:43.870 --> 00:54:51.470
Blessed be the Lord, for he hath showed me his marvelous kindness in a strong city.

00:54:52.130 --> 00:54:57.570
For I said in my haste, I am cut off from before thine eyes.

00:54:57.890 --> 00:55:04.310
Nevertheless, thou heardest the voice of my supplications when I cried unto thee,

00:55:04.310 --> 00:55:14.450
O love the Lord, all ye his saints, for the Lord preserveth the faithful and plentifully rewardeth the proud doer.

00:55:14.910 --> 00:55:22.890
Be of good courage, and he shall strengthen your heart, all ye that hope in the Lord.

00:55:35.370 --> 00:55:36.770
Amen.

00:55:53.810 --> 00:55:58.930
The Book of Psalms. King James Version. Psalm 32

00:56:00.290 --> 00:56:13.250
Blessed is he whose transgression is forgiven, whose sin is covered. Blessed is the man unto whom the Lord imputeth not iniquity, and in whose spirit there is no guile.

00:56:13.810 --> 00:56:27.710
When I kept silence, my bones waxed old through my roaring all the day long. For day and night thy hand was heavy upon me. My moisture is turned into the drought of summer.

00:56:29.730 --> 00:56:44.690
Selah. I acknowledge my sin unto thee, and mine iniquity have I not hid. I said, I will confess my transgressions unto the Lord. And thou forgavest the iniquity of my sin.

00:56:45.770 --> 00:56:53.790
Selah. For this shall every one that is godly pray unto thee, in a time when thou mayest be found.

00:56:54.550 --> 00:57:10.110
Surely in the floods of great waters they shall not come nigh unto him. Thou art my hiding place. Thou shalt preserve me from trouble. Thou shalt compass me about with songs of deliverance.

00:57:11.310 --> 00:57:12.070
Selah.

00:57:12.690 --> 00:57:20.250
I will instruct thee and teach thee in the way which thou shalt go. I will guide thee with mine eye.

00:57:21.790 --> 00:57:32.450
Be ye not as the horse or as the mule, which have no understanding, whose mouth must be held in with bit and bridle, lest they come near unto thee.

00:57:33.790 --> 00:57:51.350
Many sorrows shall be to the wicked. But he that trusteth in the Lord, mercy shall compass him about. Be glad in the Lord, and rejoice ye righteous, and shout for joy, all ye that are upright in heart.

00:57:51.350 --> 00:57:53.290
Psalm 33.

00:57:53.870 --> 00:58:07.610
Rejoice in the Lord, O ye righteous, for praise is comely for the upright. Praise the Lord with harp. Sing unto him with the psaltery and an instrument of ten strings.

00:58:08.370 --> 00:58:27.430
Sing unto him a new song. Play skillfully with a loud noise. For the word of the Lord is right. And all his works are done in truth. He loveth righteousness and judgment. The earth is full of the goodness of the Lord.

00:58:27.430 --> 00:58:53.310
By the word of the Lord were the heavens made, and all the host of them by the breath of his mouth. He gathereth the waters of the sea together as an heap. He layeth up the depth in storehouses. Let all the earth fear the Lord. Let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him.

00:58:53.310 --> 00:59:18.010
For he spake, and it was done. He commanded, and it stood fast. The Lord bringeth the counsel of the heathen to naught. He maketh the devices of the people of none effect. The counsel of the Lord standeth for ever, the thoughts of his heart to all generations.

00:59:19.610 --> 00:59:33.510
Blessed is the nation whose God is the Lord, and the people whom he hath chosen for his own inheritance. The Lord looketh from heaven. He beholdeth all the sons of men.

00:59:34.430 --> 00:59:55.770
From the place of his habitation he looketh upon all the inhabitants of the earth. He fashioneth their hearts alike. He considereth all their works. There is no king saved by the multitude of and host. A mighty man is not delivered by much strength.

00:59:55.770 --> 01:00:16.730
And horse is a vain thing for safety. Neither shall he deliver any by his great strength. Behold, the eye of the Lord is upon them that fear him, upon them that hope in his mercy, to deliver their soul from death, and to keep them alive in famine.

01:00:16.730 --> 01:00:28.910
Our soul waiteth for the Lord. He is our help and our shield, for our hearts shall rejoice in him, because we have trusted in his holy name.

01:00:30.330 --> 01:00:35.610
Let thy mercy, O Lord, be upon us, according as we hope in thee.

01:00:36.610 --> 01:00:38.110
Psalm 34

01:00:38.890 --> 01:01:06.530
I will bless the Lord at all times. His praise shall continually be in my mouth. My soul shall make her boast in the Lord. The humble shall hear thereof and be glad. O magnify the Lord with me, and let us exalt his name together. I sought the Lord, and he heard me, and delivered me from all my fears.

01:01:07.690 --> 01:01:26.890
They looked unto him and were lightened, and their faces were not ashamed. This poor man cried, and the Lord heard him and saved him out of all his troubles. The angel of the Lord encampeth round about them that fear him, and delivereth them.

01:01:26.890 --> 01:01:50.250
O taste and see that the Lord is good. Blessed is the man that trusteth in him. O fear the Lord, ye his saints, for there is no want to them that fear him. The young lions do lack and suffer hunger, but they that seek the Lord shall not want any good thing.

01:01:50.910 --> 01:01:56.690
Come, ye children, hearken unto me. I will teach you the fear of the Lord.

01:01:58.270 --> 01:02:13.750
What man is he that desireth life, and loveth many days, that he may see good? Keep thy tongue from evil, and thy lips from speaking guile. Depart from evil and do good, seek peace, and pursue it.

01:02:14.770 --> 01:02:30.130
The eyes of the Lord are upon the righteous, and his ears are open unto their cry. The face of the Lord is against them that do evil, to cut off the remembrance of them from the earth.

01:02:31.290 --> 01:02:47.290
The righteous cry, and the Lord heareth and delivereth them out of all their troubles. The Lord is nigh unto them that are of a broken heart, and saveth such as be of a contrite spirit.

01:02:48.990 --> 01:03:07.230
Many are the afflictions of the righteous, but the Lord delivereth him out of them all. He keepeth all his bones. Not one of them is broken. Evil shall slay the wicked, and they that hate the righteous shall be desolate.

01:03:08.470 --> 01:03:16.230
The Lord redeemeth the soul of his servants, and none of them that trust in him shall be desolate.

01:03:26.290 --> 01:03:29.090
Psalm 35

01:03:50.370 --> 01:04:08.870
Let them be as chaff before the wind, and let the angel of the Lord chase them. Let their way be dark and slippery, and let the angel of the Lord persecute them.

01:04:08.870 --> 01:04:25.170
For without cause have they hid for me their net in a pit, which without cause they have digged for my soul. Let destruction come upon him at unawares, and let his net that he hath hid catch himself.

01:04:25.170 --> 01:04:49.630
Into that very destruction let him fall, and my soul shall be joyful in the Lord. It shall rejoice in his salvation. All my bones shall say, Lord, who is like unto thee, which deliverest the poor from him that is too strong for him, yea, the poor and the needy from him that spoileth him?

01:04:51.350 --> 01:05:14.970
False witnesses did rise up. They laid to my charge things that I knew not. They rewarded me evil for good to the spoiling of my soul. But as for me, when they were sick, my clothing was sackcloth. I humbled my soul with fasting, and my prayer returned into mine own bosom.

01:05:14.970 --> 01:05:37.670
I behaved myself as though he had been my friend or brother. I bowed down heavily as one that mourneth for his mother. But in mine adversity they rejoiced and gathered themselves together, yea, the abjects gathered themselves together against me, and I knew it not.

01:05:37.670 --> 01:05:58.130
They did terror me and ceased not. With hypocritical mockers and feasts they gnashed upon me with their teeth. Lord, how long wilt thou look on? Rescue my soul from their destructions, my darling from the lions.

01:05:58.130 --> 01:06:24.370
I will give thee thanks in the great congregation. I will praise thee among much people. Let not them that are mine enemies wrongfully rejoice over me, neither let them wink with the eye that hate me without a cause. For they speak not peace, but they devise deceitful matters against them that are quiet in the land.

01:06:25.410 --> 01:06:53.830
Yea, they opened their mouth wide against me, and said, Aha, aha, our eye hath seen it. This thou hast seen, O Lord. Keep not silence, O Lord, be not far from me. Stir up thyself and awake to my judgment, even unto my cause my God and my Lord. Judge me, O Lord, my God, according to thy righteousness.

01:06:53.830 --> 01:07:19.310
And let them not rejoice over me. Let them not say in their hearts, Ah, so would we have it. Let them not say, We have swallowed him up. Let them be ashamed and brought to confusion together that rejoice at mine hurt. Let them be clothed with shame and dishonor that magnify themselves against me.

01:07:19.310 --> 01:07:36.230
Let them shout for joy and be glad that favor my righteous cause. Yea, let them say continually, Let the Lord be magnified, which hath pleasure in the prosperity of his servant.

01:07:37.250 --> 01:07:45.030
And my tongue shall speak of thy righteousness and of thy praise all the day long.

01:07:45.990 --> 01:07:47.050
Psalm 36

01:07:47.050 --> 01:08:02.190
The transgression of the wicked saith within my heart that there is no fear of God before his eyes, for he flattereth himself in his own eyes, until his iniquity be found to be hateful.

01:08:02.970 --> 01:08:21.030
The words of his mouth are iniquity and deceit. He hath left off to be wise and to do good. He deviseth mischief upon his bed. He setteth himself in a way that is not good. He abhorreth not evil.

01:08:22.370 --> 01:08:40.850
Thy mercy, O Lord, is in the heavens, and thy faithfulness reacheth unto the clouds. Thy righteousness is like the great mountains. Thy judgments are a great deep, O Lord. Thou preservest man and beast.

01:08:41.670 --> 01:08:51.350
How excellent is thy loving kindness, O God! Therefore the children of men put their trust under the shadow of thy wings.

01:08:52.970 --> 01:09:09.710
They shall be abundantly satisfied with the fatness of thy house, and thou shalt make them drink of the river of thy pleasures. For with thee is the fountain of life, and in thy light shall we see light.

01:09:10.930 --> 01:09:26.290
O continue thy loving kindness unto them that know thee, and thy righteousness to the upright and hard. Let not the foot of pride come against me, and let not the hand of the wicked remove me.

01:09:27.070 --> 01:09:33.970
There are the workers of iniquity fallen. They are cast down, and shall not be able to rise.

01:10:01.150 --> 01:10:03.950
Psalm 37

01:10:03.950 --> 01:10:23.290
And he shall give thee the desires of thine heart. Commit thy way unto the Lord. Trust also in him, and he shall bring it to pass. And he shall bring forth thy righteousness as the light, and thy judgment as the noon day.

01:10:23.290 --> 01:10:35.710
Rest in the Lord, and wait patiently for him. Fret not thyself because of him who prospereth in his way, because of the man who bringeth wicked devices to pass.

01:10:35.710 --> 01:10:54.130
Cease from anger, and forsake wrath. Fret not thyself in any wise to do evil. For evildoers shall be cut off, but those that wait upon the Lord, they shall inherit the earth.

01:10:54.130 --> 01:11:13.830
For yet a little while, and the wicked shall not be. Yea, thou shalt diligently consider his place, and it shall not be. But the meek shall inherit the earth, and shall delight themselves in the abundance of peace.

01:11:15.190 --> 01:11:27.670
The wicked plotteth against the just, and gnasheth upon him with his teeth. The Lord shall laugh at him, for he seeth that his day is coming.

01:11:27.670 --> 01:11:45.490
The wicked have drawn out the sword, and have bent their bow, to cast down the poor and needy, and to slay such as be of upright conversation. Their sword shall enter into their own heart, and their bows shall be broken.

01:11:45.490 --> 01:11:58.110
A little that a righteous man hath is better than the riches of many wicked. For the arms of the wicked shall be broken, but the Lord upholdeth the righteous.

01:11:59.050 --> 01:12:13.410
The Lord knoweth the days of the upright, and their inheritance shall be for ever. They shall not be ashamed in the evil time. And in the days of famine they shall be satisfied.

01:12:14.430 --> 01:12:28.250
But the wicked shall perish, and the enemies of the Lord shall be as the fat of lambs. They shall consume. Into smoke shall they consume away.

01:12:28.250 --> 01:12:44.970
The wicked borroweth, and payeth not again. But the righteous showeth mercy, and giveth. For such as be blessed of him shall inherit the earth, and they that be cursed of him shall be cut off.

01:12:44.970 --> 01:12:59.970
The steps of a good man are ordered by the Lord, and he delighteth in his way. Though he fall, he shall not be utterly cast down. For the Lord upholdeth him with his hand.

01:13:00.870 --> 01:13:17.250
I have been young, and now am old. Yet have I not seen the righteous forsaken, nor his seed begging bread. He is ever merciful, and lendeth, and his seed is blessed.

01:13:17.250 --> 01:13:34.650
Depart from evil, and do good, and dwell for evermore. For the Lord loveth judgment, and forsaketh not his saints. They are preserved for ever. But the seed of the wicked shall be cut off.

01:13:35.990 --> 01:13:59.890
The righteous shall inherit the land, and dwell therein for ever. The mouth of the righteous speaketh wisdom, and his tongue talketh of judgment. The law of his God is in his heart. None of his steps shall slide. The wicked watcheth the righteous, and seeketh to slay him.

01:14:01.130 --> 01:14:18.870
The Lord will not leave him in his hand, nor condemn him when he is judged. Wait on the Lord, and keep his way, and he shall exalt thee to inherit the land. When the wicked are cut off, thou shalt see it.

01:14:18.870 --> 01:14:34.210
I have seen the wicked in great power, and spreading himself like a green bay tree. Yet he passed away, and lo, he was not, yea, I sought him. But he could not be found.

01:14:35.710 --> 01:14:57.470
Mark the perfect man, and behold the upright, for the end of that man is peace. But the transgressors shall be destroyed together. The end of the wicked shall be cut off. But the salvation of the righteous is of the Lord. He is their strength in the time of trouble.

01:14:58.330 --> 01:15:09.370
And the Lord shall help them, and deliver them. He shall deliver them from the wicked, and save them, because they trust in him.

01:15:12.590 --> 01:15:15.130
Psalm 38-45

01:15:28.170 --> 01:15:33.270
O Lord, rebuke me not in thy wrath, Neither chasten me in thy hot displeasure.

01:15:33.750 --> 01:15:37.270
For thine arrow-stick fasted me, And thy hand presseth me sore.

01:15:37.810 --> 01:15:41.210
There is no soundness in my flesh Because of thine anger,

01:15:41.870 --> 01:15:45.310
Neither is there any rest In my bones because of my sin.

01:15:46.370 --> 01:15:52.150
For my iniquities are gone over my head As in heavy burden, they are too heavy for me.

01:15:53.010 --> 01:15:56.490
My wounds stink and are corrupt Because of my foolishness.

01:15:57.250 --> 01:16:02.370
I am troubled, I am bowed down greatly, I go mourning all the day long.

01:16:02.370 --> 01:16:08.110
For my loins are filled with a lonesome disease, And there is no soundness in my flesh.

01:16:09.090 --> 01:16:14.690
I am feeble and sore broken, I have roared By reason of the disquietness of my heart.

01:16:15.590 --> 01:16:20.850
Lord, all my desire is before thee, And my groaning is not hid from thee.

01:16:21.810 --> 01:16:28.250
My heart panteth, my strength faileth me, As for the light of mine eyes it also is gone from me.

01:16:29.310 --> 01:16:35.450
My lovers and my friends stand aloof from my sore, And my kinsmen stand afar off.

01:16:36.350 --> 01:16:42.450
They also that seek after my life lay snares for me, And they that seek my hurt speak mischievous

01:16:42.450 --> 01:16:45.870
things, And imagine deceits all the day long.

01:16:47.030 --> 01:16:53.130
But I as a deaf man heard not, And I was as a dumb man that opened not his mouth.

01:16:53.950 --> 01:16:59.450
Thus I was as a man that heareth not, And whose mouth are no reproofs.

01:17:00.230 --> 01:17:04.610
For in thee, O Lord, do I hope thou wilt hear, O Lord my God.

01:17:05.190 --> 01:17:09.630
For I said, Hear me, lest otherwise they should rejoice over me.

01:17:09.950 --> 01:17:13.250
When my foot slipeth, they magnify themselves against me.

01:17:13.830 --> 01:17:17.590
For I am ready to halt, and my sorrow is continually before me.

01:17:18.170 --> 01:17:21.250
For I will declare mine iniquity, I will be sorry for my sin.

01:17:22.330 --> 01:17:28.390
But mine enemies are lively, and they are strong, And they that hate me wrongfully are

01:17:28.390 --> 01:17:28.990
multiplied.

01:17:30.310 --> 01:17:35.670
They also that render evil for good are mine adversaries, Because I follow the thing that

01:17:35.670 --> 01:17:36.510
good is.

01:17:37.250 --> 01:17:42.290
Forsake me not, O Lord, O my God, be not far from me.

01:17:42.830 --> 01:17:46.450
Make haste to help me, O Lord, my salvation.

01:17:48.210 --> 01:17:49.250
Psalm 39

01:17:49.830 --> 01:17:53.970
I said I will take heed to my ways, That I sin not with my tongue.

01:17:54.590 --> 01:17:57.990
I will keep my mouth with a bridle While the wicked is before me.

01:17:58.490 --> 01:18:04.630
I was dumb with silence, I held my peace, Even from good, and my sorrow was stirred.

01:18:05.590 --> 01:18:09.550
My heart was hot within me, While I was musing the fire burned,

01:18:09.730 --> 01:18:11.430
Then spake I with my tongue.

01:18:12.330 --> 01:18:15.870
Lord, make me to know mine end, And the measure of my days,

01:18:16.470 --> 01:18:19.310
What it is that I may know how frail I am.

01:18:20.190 --> 01:18:25.810
Behold, thou hast made my days as in hand-breadth, And mine age is as nothing before thee.

01:18:26.350 --> 01:18:29.510
Verily, every man and his best date Is altogether vanity.

01:18:30.870 --> 01:18:31.430
Selah!

01:18:31.710 --> 01:18:36.790
Surely every man walketh in a vain shoe, Surely they are disquieted in vain.

01:18:36.790 --> 01:18:40.790
He heapeth up riches, and knoweth not Who shall gather them.

01:18:41.570 --> 01:18:43.470
And now, Lord, what wait I for?

01:18:43.870 --> 01:18:45.110
My hope is in thee.

01:18:45.550 --> 01:18:47.730
Deliver me from all my transgressions.

01:18:48.270 --> 01:18:49.930
Make me not the reproach of the foolish.

01:18:50.890 --> 01:18:54.210
I was dumb, I opened not my mouth, Because thou didst it.

01:18:54.770 --> 01:18:58.650
Remove thy stroke away from me, I am consumed By the blow of thine hand.

01:18:59.430 --> 01:19:02.270
When thou with rebukes dost correct man for iniquity,

01:19:02.590 --> 01:19:05.270
Thou makest his beauty to consume away like a moth.

01:19:05.990 --> 01:19:08.050
Surely every man is vanity.

01:19:08.830 --> 01:19:09.390
Selah!

01:19:09.910 --> 01:19:12.870
Hear my prayer, O Lord, and give ear unto my cry.

01:19:13.530 --> 01:19:17.610
Hold not thy peace at my tears, For I am a stranger with thee,

01:19:17.650 --> 01:19:19.950
And a sojourner, as all my fathers were.

01:19:20.870 --> 01:19:25.870
O spare me that I may recover strength Before I go hence, and be no more.

01:19:27.470 --> 01:19:28.590
Psalm 40

01:19:29.190 --> 01:19:33.910
I waited patiently for the Lord, And he inclined unto me and heard my cry.

01:19:34.620 --> 01:19:39.270
He brought me up also out of an horrible pit, Out of the miry clay,

01:19:39.630 --> 01:19:42.730
And set my feet upon a rock, And established my goings.

01:19:43.270 --> 01:19:47.690
And he hath put a new song in my mouth, Even praise unto our God.

01:19:48.070 --> 01:19:51.910
Many shall see it and fear, And shall trust in the Lord.

01:19:53.290 --> 01:19:56.030
Blessed is that man that maketh the Lord his trust,

01:19:56.770 --> 01:20:00.030
And respecteth not the proud, Nor such as turn aside to lies.

01:20:01.150 --> 01:20:05.010
Many, O Lord my God, are thy wonderful works, What thou hast done,

01:20:05.490 --> 01:20:09.790
And thy thoughts, which are to usward, They cannot be reckoned up in order unto thee.

01:20:10.330 --> 01:20:13.430
If I would declare and speak of them, They are more than can be numbered.

01:20:14.890 --> 01:20:17.170
Sacrifice and offering thou didst not desire.

01:20:18.230 --> 01:20:23.150
Mine ears hast thou opened, burnt offering And sin offering hast thou not required.

01:20:23.990 --> 01:20:28.590
Then said I, Lo, I come. In the volume of the book it is written of me.

01:20:28.590 --> 01:20:33.870
I delight to do thy will, O my God. Yea, thy law is within my heart.

01:20:34.630 --> 01:20:39.570
I have preached righteousness in the great congregation. Lo, I have not refrained my lips,

01:20:39.830 --> 01:20:43.750
O Lord thou knowest. I have not hid thy righteousness within my heart.

01:20:44.450 --> 01:20:47.090
I have declared thy faithfulness and thy salvation.

01:20:47.950 --> 01:20:51.710
I have not concealed thy loving kindnesses And thy truth from the great congregation.

01:20:52.710 --> 01:20:55.570
Withhold not thou thy tender mercies from me, O Lord.

01:20:55.570 --> 01:20:59.290
Let thy loving kindnesses and thy truth continually preserve me.

01:21:00.050 --> 01:21:02.230
For innumerable evils have compassed me about.

01:21:02.630 --> 01:21:06.410
Mine iniquities have taken hold upon me, So that I am not able to look up.

01:21:06.690 --> 01:21:10.570
They are more than the hairs of mine head. Therefore my heart faileth me.

01:21:11.370 --> 01:21:15.690
Be pleased, O Lord, to deliver me. O Lord, make haste to help me.

01:21:16.350 --> 01:21:20.510
Let them be ashamed and confounded together That seek after my soul to destroy it.

01:21:20.870 --> 01:21:23.810
Let them be driven backward, Put to shame, that wish me evil.

01:21:24.470 --> 01:21:29.530
Let them be desolate for a reward of their shame That say unto me, Ha ha, ha ha.

01:21:30.050 --> 01:21:33.350
Let all those that seek thee Rejoice and be glad in thee.

01:21:33.590 --> 01:21:37.890
Let such as love thy salvation Say continually the Lord be magnified.

01:21:38.630 --> 01:21:41.910
But I am poor and needy, Yet the Lord thinketh upon me.

01:21:42.150 --> 01:21:45.910
Thou art my help and my deliverer. Make no tarrying, O my God.

01:21:47.190 --> 01:21:48.150
Psalm 41

01:21:48.810 --> 01:21:53.290
Blessed is he that considereth the poor. The Lord will deliver him in time of trouble.

01:21:53.810 --> 01:21:58.290
The Lord will preserve him and keep him alive, And he shall be blessed upon the earth,

01:21:58.890 --> 01:22:01.630
And thou wilt deliver him unto the will of his enemies.

01:22:02.710 --> 01:22:05.310
The Lord will strengthen him upon the bed of languishing.

01:22:05.850 --> 01:22:07.690
Thou wilt make all his bed in his sickness.

01:22:09.070 --> 01:22:14.330
I said, Lord, be merciful unto me. Heal my soul, for I have sinned against thee.

01:22:15.110 --> 01:22:18.950
Mine enemies speak evil of me. When shall he die and his name perish?

01:22:19.830 --> 01:22:25.170
And if he come to see me, he speaketh vanity. His heart gathereth iniquity to itself.

01:22:25.190 --> 01:22:30.490
When he goeth abroad, he telleth it. All that hate me whisper together against me.

01:22:30.970 --> 01:22:37.130
Against me do they devise my hurt. An evil disease, say they, cleaveth fast unto him.

01:22:37.630 --> 01:22:40.130
And now that he lieth, he shall rise up no more.

01:22:40.990 --> 01:22:43.670
Yea, mine own familiar friend, in whom I trusted,

01:22:44.390 --> 01:22:47.430
Which did eat of my bread, hath lifted up his heel against me.

01:22:47.430 --> 01:22:52.290
But thou, O Lord, be merciful unto me, And raise me up, that I may requite them.

01:22:52.750 --> 01:22:57.370
By this I know that thou favorest me, Because mine enemy doth not triumph over me.

01:22:57.790 --> 01:23:00.370
And as for me, thou upholdest me in mine integrity,

01:23:00.930 --> 01:23:05.430
And settest me before thy face for ever. Blessed be the Lord God of Israel,

01:23:05.610 --> 01:23:09.370
From everlasting and to everlasting. Amen and amen.

01:23:10.270 --> 01:23:11.210
Psalm 42

01:23:11.730 --> 01:23:16.490
As the heart panteth after the water brooks, So panteth my soul after thee, O God.

01:23:16.970 --> 01:23:21.390
My soul thirsteth for God, for the living God, When shall I come and appear before God?

01:23:22.110 --> 01:23:26.150
My tears have been my meat day and night, While they continually say unto me,

01:23:26.610 --> 01:23:29.950
Where is thy God? When I remember these things,

01:23:30.030 --> 01:23:33.310
I pour out my soul in me. For I had gone with the multitude,

01:23:33.790 --> 01:23:37.470
I went with them to the house of God, With the voice of joy and praise,

01:23:37.990 --> 01:23:43.170
With the multitude that kept holy day. Why art thou cast down, O my soul,

01:23:43.170 --> 01:23:47.930
And why art thou disquieted in me? Hope thou in God, for I shall yet praise him

01:23:47.930 --> 01:23:52.470
For the help of his countenance. O my God, my soul is cast down within me,

01:23:52.690 --> 01:23:56.410
Therefore will I remember thee from the land of Jordan, and of the Hermonites,

01:23:56.810 --> 01:24:01.450
And from the hill Mizar. Deep calleth unto deep at the noise of thy waterspouts,

01:24:01.990 --> 01:24:04.350
All thy waves and thy billows are gone over me.

01:24:05.010 --> 01:24:07.890
Yet the Lord will command his loving-kindness in the daytime,

01:24:08.570 --> 01:24:12.490
And in the night his song shall be with me, And my prayer unto the God of my life.

01:24:13.190 --> 01:24:16.430
I will say unto God my rock, Why hast thou forgotten me?

01:24:16.770 --> 01:24:19.230
Why go I mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?

01:24:20.250 --> 01:24:23.330
As with a sword in my bones mine enemies reproach me,

01:24:23.550 --> 01:24:25.950
While they say daily unto me, Where is thy God?

01:24:27.150 --> 01:24:30.990
Why art thou cast down, O my soul, And why art thou disquieted within me?

01:24:31.070 --> 01:24:36.250
Hope thou in God, for I shall yet praise him, Who is the help of my countenance and my God.

01:24:37.770 --> 01:24:40.350
Psalm 43 Judge me, O God,

01:24:40.350 --> 01:24:46.510
And plead my cause against an ungodly nation. O deliver me from the deceitful and unjust man,

01:24:47.010 --> 01:24:50.830
For thou art the God of my strength. Why dost thou cast me off?

01:24:51.030 --> 01:24:53.510
Why go I mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?

01:24:54.710 --> 01:24:58.070
O send out thy light and thy truth, Let them lead me,

01:24:58.090 --> 01:25:00.930
Let them bring me unto thy holy hill, Into thy tabernacles.

01:25:01.870 --> 01:25:05.970
Then will I go unto the altar of God, Unto God my exceeding joy,

01:25:06.510 --> 01:25:09.470
Yea, upon the harp will I praise thee, O God, my God.

01:25:10.570 --> 01:25:14.730
Why art thou cast down, O my soul, And why art thou disquieted within me?

01:25:15.090 --> 01:25:20.670
Hope in God, for I shall yet praise him, Who is the help of my countenance and my God.

01:25:21.890 --> 01:25:25.490
Psalm 44 We have heard with our ears, O God,

01:25:25.870 --> 01:25:30.710
Our fathers have told us what work thou didst in their days, In the times of old,

01:25:31.190 --> 01:25:36.330
How thou didst drive out the heathen with thy hand, And plantest them how thou didst afflict

01:25:36.330 --> 01:25:41.670
the people, And cast them out. For they got not the land in possession by their own sword,

01:25:42.350 --> 01:25:46.850
Neither did their own arm save them, But thy right hand, and thine arm,

01:25:46.870 --> 01:25:49.890
In the light of thy countenance, Because thou hadst favor unto them.

01:25:50.730 --> 01:25:54.310
Thou art my king, O God, Command deliverances for Jacob.

01:25:55.190 --> 01:25:59.310
Through thee will we push down our enemies, Through thy name will we tread them under

01:25:59.310 --> 01:26:02.650
That rise up against us. For I will not trust in my bow,

01:26:02.650 --> 01:26:06.910
Neither shall my sword save me. But thou hast saved us from our enemies,

01:26:06.990 --> 01:26:11.710
And hast put them to shame that hated us. In God we boast all the day long,

01:26:11.910 --> 01:26:17.410
And praise thy name forever, saila. But thou hast cast off and put us to shame,

01:26:17.490 --> 01:26:22.750
And goest not forth with our armies. Thou makest us to turn back from the enemy,

01:26:23.290 --> 01:26:28.430
And they which hate us spoil for themselves. Thou hast given us like sheep appointed for meat,

01:26:28.430 --> 01:26:33.250
And hast scattered us among the heathen. Thou sellest thy people for naught,

01:26:33.490 --> 01:26:38.550
And dost not increase thy wealth by their price. Thou makest us to reproach to our neighbors,

01:26:38.890 --> 01:26:41.690
A scorn and a derision to them that are round about us.

01:26:42.450 --> 01:26:46.370
Thou makest us to byword among the heathen, A shaking of the head among the people.

01:26:47.270 --> 01:26:52.570
My confusion is continually before me, And the shame of my face has covered me.

01:26:53.250 --> 01:26:56.490
For the voice of him that reproacheth and blasphemeth

01:26:56.490 --> 01:27:02.770
By reason of the enemy and avenger. All this has come upon us, yet have we not forgotten thee,

01:27:03.010 --> 01:27:07.570
Neither have we dealt falsely in thy covenant. Our heart is not turned back,

01:27:07.970 --> 01:27:13.230
Neither have our steps declined from thy way. Though thou hast sore broken us in the place

01:27:13.230 --> 01:27:17.710
Of dragons and covered us with the shadow of death, If we have forgotten the name of our God

01:27:17.710 --> 01:27:22.790
Or stretched out our hands to a strange God, Shall not God search this out, for he knoweth

01:27:22.790 --> 01:27:27.690
secrets of the heart. Yea, for thy sake are we killed all the day long,

01:27:28.070 --> 01:27:33.470
We are counted as sheep for the slaughter. Awake, why sleepest thou, O Lord?

01:27:34.310 --> 01:27:40.210
Arise, cast us not off for ever. Wherefore hidest thou thy face and forgetest our affliction

01:27:40.210 --> 01:27:45.830
And our oppression? For our soul is bowed down to the dust, Our belly cleaveth unto the earth,

01:27:46.330 --> 01:27:50.010
Arise for our help, and redeem us for thy mercy's sake.

01:27:51.490 --> 01:27:52.530
Psalm 45.

01:27:53.430 --> 01:27:56.170
My heart is indicting a good matter, I speak of the things,

01:27:56.570 --> 01:28:00.750
Which I have made touching the King. My tongue is the pen of a ready writer.

01:28:01.590 --> 01:28:05.450
Thou art fairer than the children of men, Grace is poured into thy lips,

01:28:05.850 --> 01:28:09.650
Therefore God has blessed thee for ever, Gird thy sword upon thy thigh,

01:28:10.170 --> 01:28:15.510
O most mighty, with thy glory and thy majesty. And in thy majesty write prosperously because

01:28:15.510 --> 01:28:20.310
of truth and meekness and righteousness, And thy right hand shall teach thee terrible things.

01:28:20.970 --> 01:28:23.490
Thine arrows are sharp in the heart of the King's enemies,

01:28:24.010 --> 01:28:28.690
Whereby the people fall under thee. Thy throne, O God, is for ever and ever,

01:28:29.130 --> 01:28:35.290
The scepter of thy kingdom is a right scepter. Thou lovest righteousness and hastest wickedness,

01:28:35.730 --> 01:28:41.090
Therefore God, thy God, hath anointed thee With the oil of gladness above thy fellows.

01:28:41.650 --> 01:28:47.610
All thy garments smell of myrrh and aloes and cashew, Out of the ivory palaces whereby they

01:28:47.610 --> 01:28:53.650
have made thee glad. King's daughters were among thy honorable women, Upon thy right hand did stand

01:28:53.650 --> 01:28:58.070
The queen in gold of Ophir. Harken, O daughter, and consider,

01:28:58.590 --> 01:29:02.190
And incline thy ear, forget also thine own people In thy father's house.

01:29:02.690 --> 01:29:07.250
So shall the King greatly desire thy beauty, For he is thy Lord, and worship thou him.

01:29:07.810 --> 01:29:12.830
And the daughter of Tyre shall be there with a gift, Even the rich among the people shall

01:29:12.830 --> 01:29:19.010
entreat thy favor. The King's daughter is all glorious within, Her clothing is of wrought gold.

01:29:19.830 --> 01:29:24.410
She shall be brought unto the King in raiment of needlework, The virgins or companions that

01:29:24.410 --> 01:29:29.190
follow her shall be brought unto thee. With gladness and rejoicing shall they be brought,

01:29:29.610 --> 01:29:34.690
They shall enter into the King's palace. Instead of thy fathers shall be thy children,

01:29:34.690 --> 01:29:39.950
Whom thou mayest make princes in all the earth. I will make thy name to be remembered in all

01:29:39.950 --> 01:29:43.770
generations, Therefore shall the people praise thee forever and ever.

01:29:45.770 --> 01:29:49.770
Psalms 46-55

01:30:07.870 --> 01:30:14.250
The Book of Psalms, King James Version, Psalm 46

01:30:15.050 --> 01:30:36.870
God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble. Therefore will not we fear, though the earth be removed, and though the mountains be carried into the midst of the sea, though the waters thereof roar and be troubled, though the mountains shake with the swelling thereof, say la.

01:30:36.870 --> 01:30:55.950
There is a river, the streams whereof shall make glad the city of God, the holy place of the tabernacles of the Most High. God is in the midst of her, she shall not be moved, God shall help her, and that right early.

01:30:55.950 --> 01:31:09.010
The heathen raged, the kingdoms were moved, he uttered his voice, the earth melted. The Lord of Host is with us, the God of Jacob is our refuge, say la.

01:31:09.010 --> 01:31:27.110
Come, behold the works of the Lord, what desolations he hath made in the earth. He maketh wars to cease unto the end of the earth. He breaketh the bow and cutteth the spear in sunder. He burneth the chariot in the fire.

01:31:27.110 --> 01:31:44.010
Be still and know that I am God. I will be exalted among the heathen, I will be exalted in the earth. The Lord of Host is with us, the God of Jacob is our refuge, say la.

01:31:45.330 --> 01:32:05.570
Psalm 47. O clap your hands, all ye people, shout unto God with the voice of triumph, for the Lord Most High is terrible, he is a great king over all the earth. He shall subdue the people under us and the nations under our feet.

01:32:05.570 --> 01:32:13.830
He shall choose our inheritance for us, the excellency of Jacob whom he loved, say la.

01:32:13.830 --> 01:32:30.130
God is gone up with a shout, the Lord with the sound of a trumpet. Sing praises to God, sing praises, sing praises unto our King, sing praises, for God is the King of all the earth.

01:32:30.130 --> 01:32:55.050
Sing ye praises with understanding, God reigneth over the heathen, God sitteth upon the throne of his holiness. The princes of the people are gathered together, even the people of the God of Abraham, for the shields of the earth belong unto God. He is greatly exalted.

01:32:55.050 --> 01:33:13.490
Psalm 48. Great is the Lord and greatly to be praised in the city of our God, in the mountain of his holiness, beautiful for situation. The joy of the whole earth is Mount Zion.

01:33:13.490 --> 01:33:31.270
On the sides of the north, the city of the great king, God is known in her palaces for a refuge. For lo, the kings were assembled, they passed by together, they saw it and so they marveled.

01:33:31.270 --> 01:33:47.770
They were troubled and hasted away. Fear took hold upon them there, and pain, as of a woman in travail, thou breakest the ships of Tarshish with an east wind, as we have heard.

01:33:47.770 --> 01:33:57.970
So have we seen in the city of the Lord of hosts, in the city of our God. God will establish it forever, say la.

01:33:57.970 --> 01:34:10.670
We have thought of thy loving kindness, O God, in the midst of thy temple. According to thy name, O God, so is thy praise unto the ends of the earth.

01:34:10.670 --> 01:34:22.250
Thy right hand is full of righteousness. Let Mount Zion rejoice. Let the daughters of Judah be glad because of thy judgments.

01:34:22.250 --> 01:34:37.350
Walk about Zion and go round about her. Tell the towers thereof. Mark ye well her bulwarks. Consider her palaces, that ye may tell it to the generation following.

01:34:37.350 --> 01:34:48.830
For this God is our God forever and ever. He will be our guide even unto death.

01:34:48.830 --> 01:34:51.670
Psalm 49.

01:35:18.830 --> 01:35:26.530
Or should I fear in the days of evil, when the iniquity of my heels shall compass me about?

01:35:27.470 --> 01:35:41.430
They that trust in their wealth and boast themselves in the multitude of their riches, none of them can by any means redeem his brother, nor give to God a ransom for him.

01:35:41.430 --> 01:35:52.810
For the redemption of their soul is precious, and it ceaseth forever, that he should still live forever and not see corruption.

01:35:52.810 --> 01:36:03.010
For he seeth that wise men die. Likewise the fool and the brutish person perish and leave their wealth to others.

01:36:03.390 --> 01:36:15.030
Their inward thought is that their houses shall continue forever, and their dwelling places to all generations they call their lands after their own names.

01:36:15.030 --> 01:36:30.350
Nevertheless, man, being in honor, abideth not. He is like the beast that perish. This their way is their folly, yet their posterity approve their sayings.

01:36:31.610 --> 01:36:46.810
Like sheep, they are laid in the grave. Death shall feed on them, and the upright shall have dominion over them in the morning, and their beauty shall consume in the grave from their dwelling.

01:36:46.810 --> 01:36:58.290
But God will redeem my soul from the power of the grave, for he shall receive me, Selah.

01:36:58.290 --> 01:37:13.330
Be not thou afraid, when one is made rich, when the glory of his house is increased. For when he dieth, he shall carry nothing away. His glory shall not descend after him.

01:37:13.330 --> 01:37:29.150
Though while he lived, he blessed his soul, and men will praise thee when thou doest well to thyself. He shall go to the generation of his fathers, they shall never see light.

01:37:29.150 --> 01:37:37.190
Man, that is in honor, and understandeth not, is like the beast that perish.

01:37:39.450 --> 01:37:41.050
Psalm 50

01:37:41.050 --> 01:37:56.490
The mighty God, even the Lord hath spoken, and called the earth from the rising of the sun unto the going down thereof. Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God hath shined.

01:37:56.490 --> 01:38:08.730
Our God shall come, and shall not keep silence. A fire shall devour before him, and it shall be very tempestuous round about him.

01:38:08.730 --> 01:38:24.010
He shall call to the heavens from above, and to the earth, that he may judge his people. Gather my saints together unto me, those that have made a covenant with me by sacrifice.

01:38:24.010 --> 01:38:30.530
And the heavens shall declare his righteousness, for God is judge himself. Say la.

01:38:31.310 --> 01:38:50.850
Hear, O my people, and I will speak. O Israel, I will testify against thee. I am God, even thy God. I will not reprove thee for thy sacrifices, or thy burnt offerings, to have been continually before me.

01:38:50.850 --> 01:39:03.850
I will take no bullock out of thy house, nor he goats out of thy folds. For every beast of the forest is mine, and the cattle upon a thousand hills.

01:39:04.390 --> 01:39:17.190
I know all the fowls of the mountains, and the wild beasts of the field are mine. If I were hungry, I would not tell thee, for the world is mine, and the fullness thereof.

01:39:17.190 --> 01:39:35.570
Will I eat the flesh of bulls, or drink the blood of goats? Offer unto God thanksgiving, and pay thy vows unto the Most High, and call upon me in the day of trouble. I will deliver thee, and thou shalt glorify me.

01:39:35.570 --> 01:39:53.330
But unto the wicked God saith, What hast thou to do to declare my statutes? Or that thou shouldest take my covenant in thy mouth? Seeing thou hatest instruction, and castest my words behind thee.

01:39:53.330 --> 01:40:08.530
When thou sawest a thief, then thou consented with him, and hast been partaker with adulterers. Thou givest thy mouth to evil, and thy tongue frameth deceit.

01:40:08.530 --> 01:40:33.090
Thou sittest, and speakest against thy brother. Thou slanderest thine own mother's son. These things hast thou done, and I kept silence. Thou thoughtest that I was altogether such in one as thyself. But I will reprove thee, and set them in order before thine eyes.

01:40:33.090 --> 01:40:53.450
Now consider this. Ye that forget God, lest I tear you in pieces, and there be none to deliver. Whoso offereth praise, glorifyeth me. And to him that ordereth his conversation aright, will I show the salvation of God.

01:40:53.450 --> 01:40:56.150
Psalm 51

01:41:24.870 --> 01:41:41.810
And done this evil in thy sight, that thou mightest be justified when thou speakest, and be clear when thou judgest. Behold, I was shapen in iniquity, and in sin did my mother conceive me.

01:41:41.810 --> 01:41:59.830
Behold, thou desirest truth in the inward parts, and in the hidden part thou shalt make me to know wisdom. Purge me with hisop, and I shall be clean. Wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow.

01:41:59.830 --> 01:42:19.930
Make me to hear joy and gladness, that the bones which thou hast broken may rejoice. High thy face from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities. Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me.

01:42:19.930 --> 01:42:41.850
Cast me not away from thy presence, and take not thy holy spirit from me. Restore unto me the joy of thy salvation, and uphold me with thy free spirit. Then will I teach transgressors thy ways, and sinners shall be converted unto thee.

01:42:41.850 --> 01:43:07.370
Deliver me from blood-guiltiness, O God, thou God of my salvation, and my tongue shall sing aloud of thy righteousness. O Lord, open thou my lips, and my mouth shall show forth thy praise. For thou desirest not sacrifice, else would I give it. Thou delightest not in burnt offering.

01:43:07.370 --> 01:43:22.610
The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit, a broken and a contrite heart. O God, thou wilt not despise. Do good in thy good pleasure unto Zion.

01:43:22.610 --> 01:43:38.990
Build thou the walls of Jerusalem, then shalt thou be pleased with the sacrifices of righteousness, with burnt offering and whole burnt offering. Then shall they offer bullocks upon thine altar.

01:43:38.990 --> 01:43:41.710
Psalm 52

01:44:09.110 --> 01:44:25.810
O thou deceitful tongue, God shall likewise destroy thee forever. He shall take thee away, and pluck thee out of thy dwelling place, and root thee out of the land of the living.

01:44:26.910 --> 01:44:44.690
Selah, the righteous also shall see, and fear, and shall laugh at him. Lo, this is the man that made not God his strength, but trusted in the abundance of his riches, and strengthened himself in his wickedness.

01:44:44.690 --> 01:45:05.690
But I am like a green olive tree in the house of God, I trust in the mercy of God forever and ever. I will praise thee forever, because thou hast done it, and I will wait on thy name, for it is good before thy saints.

01:45:05.690 --> 01:45:08.710
Psalm 53

01:45:08.710 --> 01:45:32.770
The fool hath said in his heart, There is no God. Corrupt are they, and have done abominable iniquity. There is none that doeth good. God looked down from heaven upon the children of men to see if there were any that did understand, that did seek God.

01:45:32.770 --> 01:45:51.650
Every one of them is gone back. They are all together become filthy. There is none that doeth good. No, not one. Have the workers of iniquity no knowledge, who eat up my people as they eat bread?

01:45:51.650 --> 01:46:12.450
They have not called upon God. There were they in great fear, where no fear was. For God hath scattered the bones of him that encampeth against thee. Thou hast put them to shame, because God hath despised them.

01:46:12.450 --> 01:46:26.410
Oh, that the salvation of Israel were come out of Zion. When God bringeth back the captivity of his people, Jacob shall rejoice, and Israel shall be glad.

01:46:26.410 --> 01:46:29.790
Psalm 54

01:46:56.410 --> 01:47:20.070
He shall reward evil unto mine enemies, cut them off in thy truth. I will freely sacrifice unto thee. I will praise thy name, O Lord, for it is good. For he hath delivered me out of all trouble, and mine eye hath seen his desire upon mine enemies.

01:47:22.210 --> 01:47:23.770
Psalm 55

01:47:23.770 --> 01:47:47.650
Give ear to my prayer, O God, and hide not thyself from my supplication. Attend unto me and hear me. I mourn in my complaint and make a noise. Because of the voice of the enemy, because of the oppression of the wicked, for they cast iniquity upon me, and in wrath they hate me.

01:47:47.650 --> 01:48:01.770
My heart is sore pained within me, and the terrors of death are falling upon me. Fearfulness and trembling are come upon me, and horror hath overwhelmed me.

01:48:01.770 --> 01:48:16.830
And I said, O, that I had wings like a dove, for then would I fly away and be at rest. Lo, then would I wander far off and remain in the wilderness.

01:48:16.830 --> 01:48:35.990
I would hasten my escape from the windy storm and tempest. Destroy, O Lord, and divide their tongues, for I have seen violence and strife in the city. Day and night they go about it upon the walls thereof.

01:48:35.990 --> 01:48:52.530
Mischief also and sorrow are in the midst of it. Wickedness is in the midst thereof. Deceit and guile. Depart not from her streets, for it was not an enemy that reproached me.

01:48:52.530 --> 01:49:05.350
Then I could have borne it. Neither was it he that hated me that did magnify himself against me. Then I would have hid myself from him.

01:49:05.350 --> 01:49:19.950
But it was thou, a man, mine equal, my guide, and mine acquaintance. We took sweet counsel together and walked unto the house of God in company.

01:49:19.950 --> 01:49:31.430
Let death seize upon them, and let them go down quick into hell, for wickedness is in their dwellings and among them.

01:49:31.430 --> 01:49:46.010
As for me, I will call upon God, and the Lord shall save me. Evening and morning and at noon will I pray and cry aloud, and he shall hear my voice.

01:49:46.010 --> 01:50:02.770
He hath delivered my soul in peace from the battle that was against me, for there were many with me. God shall hear and afflict them, even he that abideth of old, saila.

01:50:02.770 --> 01:50:17.010
Because they have no changes, therefore they fear not God. He hath put forth his hands against such as be at peace with him. He hath broken his covenant.

01:50:17.950 --> 01:50:29.550
The words of his mouth were smoother than butter, but war was in his heart. His words were softer than oil, yet were they drawn swords.

01:50:30.530 --> 01:50:44.570
Cast thy burden upon the Lord, and he shall sustain thee. He shall never suffer the righteous to be moved, but thou, O God, shall bring them down into the pit of destruction.

01:50:44.570 --> 01:50:54.430
Bloody and deceitful men shall not live out half their days, but I will trust in thee.

01:50:56.430 --> 01:51:24.010
Psalm 56 Be merciful unto me, O God, for man would swallow

01:51:24.010 --> 01:51:32.950
me up. He fighting daily oppresseth me. Mine enemies would daily swallow me up, for they

01:51:32.950 --> 01:51:41.230
be many that fight against me, O thou most high. What time I am afraid I will trust in thee.

01:51:41.830 --> 01:51:50.730
In God I will praise his word. In God I have put my trust. I will not fear what flesh can do unto me.

01:51:51.610 --> 01:51:57.910
Every day they rest my words. All their thoughts are against me for evil.

01:51:59.050 --> 01:52:05.510
They gather themselves together. They hide themselves. They mark my steps when they wait

01:52:05.510 --> 01:52:14.030
for my soul. Shall they escape by iniquity? In thine anger cast down the people, O God.

01:52:14.870 --> 01:52:21.490
Thou tellest my wanderings. Put thou my tears into thy bottle. Are they not in thy book?

01:52:22.350 --> 01:52:29.110
When I cry unto thee, then shall mine enemies turn back. This I know, for God is with me.

01:52:30.130 --> 01:52:36.490
In God will I praise his word. In the Lord will I praise his word.

01:52:37.450 --> 01:52:42.550
In God have I put my trust. I will not be afraid what man can do unto me.

01:52:44.030 --> 01:52:51.230
Thy vows are upon me, O God. I will render praises unto thee. For thou hast delivered

01:52:51.230 --> 01:52:57.990
my soul from death. Wilt not thou deliver my feet from falling, that I may walk before God

01:52:57.990 --> 01:53:01.570
in the light of the living? Psalm 57

01:53:02.470 --> 01:53:10.470
Be merciful unto me, O God. Be merciful unto me. For my soul trusteth in thee.

01:53:10.470 --> 01:53:18.290
Yea, in the shadow of thy wings will I make my refuge, until these calamities be overpassed.

01:53:18.390 --> 01:53:25.130
I will cry unto God most high, unto God that performeth all things for me.

01:53:25.770 --> 01:53:32.250
He shall send from heaven, and save me from the reproach of him that would swallow me up.

01:53:32.250 --> 01:53:42.470
Selah God shall send forth his mercy and his truth. My soul is among lions, and I lie even

01:53:42.470 --> 01:53:49.390
among them that are set on fire, even the sons of men, whose teeth are spears and arrows,

01:53:49.770 --> 01:53:58.950
and their tongue a sharp sword. Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens. Let thy glory be above

01:53:58.950 --> 01:54:06.850
all the earth. They have prepared a net for my steps. My soul is bowed down. They have

01:54:06.850 --> 01:54:13.170
digged a pit before me, into the midst whereof they are fallen themselves. Selah

01:54:13.810 --> 01:54:22.890
My heart is fixed. O God, my heart is fixed. I will sing and give praise. Awake up my glory,

01:54:23.530 --> 01:54:31.430
psaltery and harp. I myself will awake early. I will praise thee, O Lord, among the people.

01:54:32.090 --> 01:54:39.010
I will sing unto thee among the nations. For thy mercy is great unto the heavens,

01:54:39.370 --> 01:54:46.690
and thy truth unto the clouds. Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens.

01:54:47.210 --> 01:54:52.150
Let thy glory be above all the earth. Psalm 58

01:54:52.710 --> 01:54:58.410
Do ye indeed speak righteousness, O congregation? Do ye judge uprightly,

01:54:58.530 --> 01:55:05.830
O ye sons of men? Yea, in heart ye work wickedness. Ye weigh the violence of your

01:55:05.830 --> 01:55:13.790
hands in the earth. The wicked are estranged from the womb. They go astray as soon as they are born,

01:55:13.790 --> 01:55:21.770
speaking lies. Their poison is like the poison of a serpent. They are like the deaf adder that

01:55:21.770 --> 01:55:27.910
stopeth her ear, which will not hearken to the voice of charmers, charming never so wisely.

01:55:28.350 --> 01:55:34.950
Break their teeth, O God, in their mouth. Break out the great teeth of the young lions, O Lord.

01:55:35.590 --> 01:55:41.930
Let them melt away as waters which run continually. When he bendeth his bow to shoot his arrows,

01:55:41.930 --> 01:55:50.370
let them be as cut in pieces, as a snail which melteth. Let every one of them pass away,

01:55:50.790 --> 01:55:58.350
like the untimely birth of a woman, that they may not see the sun. Before your pots can feel the

01:55:58.350 --> 01:56:04.910
thorns, he shall take them away, as with a whirlwind both living and in his wrath.

01:56:05.690 --> 01:56:12.330
The righteous shall rejoice when he seeth the vengeance. He shall wash his feet in the blood

01:56:12.330 --> 01:56:20.070
of the wicked, so that a man shall say, Verily, there is a reward for the righteous. Verily,

01:56:20.230 --> 01:56:24.770
he is a God that judgeth in the earth. Psalm 59

01:56:24.770 --> 01:56:31.970
Deliver me from mine enemies, O my God. Defend me from them that rise up against me.

01:56:31.970 --> 01:56:38.690
Deliver me from the workers of iniquity, and save me from bloody men. For lo,

01:56:38.690 --> 01:56:44.950
they lie in wait for my soul. The mighty are gathered against me, not for my transgression,

01:56:45.050 --> 01:56:52.730
nor for my sin, O Lord. They run and prepare themselves without my fault. Awake to help me,

01:56:52.790 --> 01:57:01.710
and behold, thou therefore, O Lord, God of hosts, the God of Israel, awake to visit all the heathen.

01:57:02.550 --> 01:57:07.690
Be not merciful to any wicked transgressors. Selah

01:57:07.690 --> 01:57:15.450
They return at evening. They make a noise like a dog, and go round about the city. Behold,

01:57:15.570 --> 01:57:22.370
they belt out with their mouth. Swords are in their lips. For who, say they, doth hear?

01:57:22.930 --> 01:57:29.510
But thou, O Lord, shalt laugh at them. Thou shalt have all the heathen in derision.

01:57:30.150 --> 01:57:38.970
Because of his strength will I wait upon thee. For God is my defense. The God of my mercy shall

01:57:38.970 --> 01:57:46.750
prevent me. God shall let me see my desire upon mine enemies. Slay them not lest my people forget.

01:57:47.270 --> 01:57:54.770
Scatter them by thy power, and bring them down, O Lord, our shield. For the sin of their mouth,

01:57:54.770 --> 01:58:01.470
and the words of their lips, let them even be taken in their pride, and for cursing and lying

01:58:01.470 --> 01:58:11.850
which they speak. Consume them in wrath. Consume them that they may not be, and let them know that

01:58:11.850 --> 01:58:18.030
God ruleth in Jacob unto the ends of the earth. Selah

01:58:18.030 --> 01:58:27.070
And at evening let them return, and let them make a noise like a dog, and go round about the city.

01:58:27.370 --> 01:58:34.630
Let them wander up and down for meat, and grudge if they be not satisfied. But I will sing of thy

01:58:34.630 --> 01:58:44.290
power, yea, I will sing aloud of thy mercy in the morning. For thou hast been my defense and refuge

01:58:44.290 --> 01:58:53.210
in the day of my trouble. Unto thee, O my strength, will I sing. For God is my defense,

01:58:53.750 --> 01:58:57.290
and the God of my mercy. Psalm 60

01:58:57.290 --> 01:59:05.330
O God, thou hast cast us off, thou hast scattered us, thou hast been displeased,

01:59:06.150 --> 01:59:12.670
O turn thyself to us again, thou hast made the earth to tremble, thou hast broken it,

01:59:12.670 --> 01:59:19.730
heal the breaches thereof, for it shaketh. Thou hast showed thy people hard things,

01:59:20.350 --> 01:59:26.650
thou hast made us to drink the wine of astonishment, thou hast given a banner to

01:59:26.650 --> 01:59:33.930
them that fear thee, that it may be displayed because of the truth. Selah

01:59:33.930 --> 01:59:40.970
That thy beloved may be delivered, save with thy right hand, and hear me. God hath spoken

01:59:40.970 --> 01:59:49.010
in his holiness. I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem, and meet out the valley of Sukkoth.

01:59:49.710 --> 01:59:56.590
Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine. Ephraim also is the strength of mine head.

01:59:57.130 --> 02:00:05.570
Judah is my law-giver. Moab is my wash-pot. Over Edom will I cast out my shoe.

02:00:06.370 --> 02:00:12.190
Philistia triumph thou because of me. Who will bring me into the strong city?

02:00:12.570 --> 02:00:18.910
Who will lead me into Edom? Wilt not thou, O God, which hast cast us off,

02:00:19.250 --> 02:00:22.250
and thou, O God, which didst not go out with our armies?

02:00:23.790 --> 02:00:27.430
Give us help from trouble, for vain is the help of man.

02:00:28.330 --> 02:00:35.030
Through God we shall do valiantly, for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.

02:00:37.030 --> 02:00:38.230
Psalm 61

02:00:38.770 --> 02:00:45.910
Hear my cry, O God. Attend unto my prayer. From the end of the earth will I cry unto thee.

02:00:46.290 --> 02:00:51.150
When my heart is overwhelmed, lead me to the rock that is higher than I.

02:00:52.730 --> 02:00:57.950
For thou hast been a shelter for me, and a strong tower from the enemy.

02:00:58.530 --> 02:01:04.510
I will abide in thy tabernacle for ever. I will trust in the covered of thy wings.

02:01:04.510 --> 02:01:14.150
Selah. For thou, O God, hast heard my vows. Thou hast given me the heritage of those that fear thy

02:01:14.150 --> 02:01:23.470
name. Thou wilt prolong the king's life, and his years as many generations. He shall abide before

02:01:23.470 --> 02:01:32.990
God for ever. O prepare mercy and truth which may preserve him. So will I sing praise unto thy name

02:01:32.990 --> 02:01:39.070
for ever, that I may daily perform my vows. Psalm 62

02:01:39.630 --> 02:01:48.490
Truly my soul waiteth upon God. From him cometh my salvation. He only is my rock and my salvation.

02:01:48.770 --> 02:01:57.310
He is my defense. I shall not be greatly moved. How long will ye imagine mischief against a man?

02:01:57.310 --> 02:02:05.650
Ye shall be slain, all of you, as a bowing wall shall ye be, and as a tottering fence.

02:02:06.310 --> 02:02:13.110
They only consult to cast him down from his excellency. They delight in lies. They bless

02:02:13.110 --> 02:02:23.230
with their mouths, but they curse inwardly. Selah. My soul wait thou only upon God. For my

02:02:23.230 --> 02:02:32.910
expectation is from him. He only is my rock and my salvation. He is my defense. I shall not be

02:02:32.910 --> 02:02:42.810
moved. In God is my salvation and my glory. The rock of my strength and my refuge is in God.

02:02:43.850 --> 02:02:52.090
Trust in him at all times ye people. Pour out your heart before him. God is a refuge for us.

02:02:52.090 --> 02:03:01.470
Selah. Surely men of low degree are vanity and men of high degree are a lie. To be laid in the

02:03:01.470 --> 02:03:09.350
balance they are altogether lighter than vanity. Trust not in oppression and become not vain in

02:03:09.350 --> 02:03:18.710
robbery. If riches increase set not your heart upon them. God hath spoken once, twice have I

02:03:18.710 --> 02:03:26.830
heard this, that power belongeth unto God. Also unto thee, O Lord, belongeth mercy.

02:03:27.610 --> 02:03:37.870
For thou renderest to every man according to his work. Psalm 63. O God, thou art my God. Early will

02:03:37.870 --> 02:03:46.650
I seek thee. My soul thirsteth for thee. My flesh longeth for thee in a dry and thirsty land where

02:03:46.650 --> 02:03:54.930
water is. To see thy power and thy glory so as I have seen thee in the sanctuary.

02:03:55.950 --> 02:04:00.710
Because thy loving kindness is better than life, my lips shall praise thee.

02:04:01.610 --> 02:04:10.650
Thus will I bless thee while I live. I will lift up my hands in thy name. My soul shall be satisfied

02:04:10.650 --> 02:04:18.070
as with marrow and fatness and my mouth shall praise thee with joyful lips when I remember

02:04:18.070 --> 02:04:25.390
thee upon my bed and meditate on thee in the night watches. Because thou hast been my help.

02:04:26.310 --> 02:04:33.250
Therefore in the shadow of thy wings will I rejoice. My soul followeth hard after thee.

02:04:33.250 --> 02:04:40.170
Thy right hand upholdeth me. But those that seek my soul to destroy it

02:04:40.590 --> 02:04:46.970
shall go into the lower parts of the earth. They shall fall by the sword. They shall be a portion

02:04:46.970 --> 02:04:56.530
for foxes. But the king shall rejoice in God. Everyone that sweareth by him shall glory.

02:04:56.530 --> 02:05:04.050
But the mouth of them that speak lies shall be stopped. Psalm 64

02:05:04.850 --> 02:05:10.810
Hear my voice, O God, in my prayer. Preserve my life from fear of the enemy.

02:05:11.370 --> 02:05:18.090
Hide me from the secret counsel of the wicked, from the insurrection of the workers of iniquity,

02:05:18.430 --> 02:05:25.530
who wet their tongue like a sword, and bend their bows to shoot their arrows, even bitter words,

02:05:25.530 --> 02:05:32.190
that they may shoot in secret at the perfect. Suddenly do they shoot at him and fear not.

02:05:32.690 --> 02:05:39.010
They encourage themselves in an evil manner. They commune of laying snares privily.

02:05:39.570 --> 02:05:47.470
They say, Who shall see them? They search out iniquities. They accomplish a diligent search.

02:05:47.970 --> 02:05:52.730
Both the inward thought of every one of them and the heart is deep.

02:05:53.490 --> 02:06:00.670
But God shall shoot at them with an arrow. Suddenly shall they be wounded. So they shall

02:06:00.670 --> 02:06:09.970
make their own tongue to fall upon themselves. All that see them shall flee away. And all men

02:06:09.970 --> 02:06:17.070
shall fear and shall declare the work of God, for they shall wisely consider of his doing.

02:06:18.170 --> 02:06:27.030
The righteous shall be glad in the Lord and shall trust in him, and all the upright in heart shall

02:06:27.030 --> 02:06:29.730
glory. Psalm 65

02:06:29.730 --> 02:06:37.930
Praise waiteth for thee, O God, in Sion, and unto thee shall the vow be performed. O thou that

02:06:37.930 --> 02:06:46.550
hearest prayer, unto thee shall all flesh come. Iniquities prevail against me, as for our

02:06:46.550 --> 02:06:53.810
aggressions thou shalt purge them away. Blessed is the man whom thou choosest, and causes to

02:06:53.810 --> 02:07:00.430
approach unto thee, that he may dwell in thy courts. We shall be satisfied with the goodness

02:07:00.430 --> 02:07:08.290
of thy house, even of thy holy temple. By terrible things and righteousness wilt thou answer us,

02:07:08.470 --> 02:07:15.530
O God of our salvation, who art the confidence of all the ends of the earth, and of them that

02:07:15.530 --> 02:07:23.550
are afar off upon the sea, which by his strength setteth fast the mountains, being girded with

02:07:23.550 --> 02:07:31.390
power, which stilleth the noise of the seas, the noise of their waves, and the tumult of the people.

02:07:31.970 --> 02:07:38.710
They also that dwell in the uttermost parts are afraid at thy tokens. Thou makest the outgoings

02:07:38.710 --> 02:07:46.430
of the morning and evening to rejoice. Thou visitest the earth, and waterest it. Thou greatly

02:07:46.430 --> 02:07:54.030
enrichest it with the river of God, which is full of water. Thou preparest them corn, when thou hast

02:07:54.030 --> 02:08:02.010
so provided for it. Thou waterest the ridges thereof abundantly. Thou settlest the furrows thereof.

02:08:02.010 --> 02:08:09.690
Thou makest it soft with showers. Thou blessest the springing thereof. Thou crownest the year

02:08:09.690 --> 02:08:16.570
with thy goodness, and thy paths drop fatness. They drop upon the pastures of the wilderness,

02:08:17.030 --> 02:08:24.510
and the little hills rejoice on every side. The pastures are clothed with flocks. The valleys

02:08:24.510 --> 02:08:33.630
also are covered over with corn. They shout for joy. They also sing. Psalm 66.

02:08:34.310 --> 02:08:42.790
Make a joyful noise unto God all ye lands. Sing forth the honor of his name. Make his praise

02:08:42.790 --> 02:08:51.730
glorious. Say unto God, How terrible art thou in thy works! Through the greatness of thy power

02:08:51.730 --> 02:08:58.050
shall thine enemies submit themselves unto thee. All the earth shall worship thee,

02:08:58.790 --> 02:09:04.790
and shall sing unto thee. They shall sing to thy name. Say la.

02:09:06.190 --> 02:09:12.230
Come and see the works of God. He is terrible in his doing toward the children of men.

02:09:12.790 --> 02:09:21.250
He turned the sea into dry land. They went through the flood on foot. There did we rejoice in him.

02:09:21.730 --> 02:09:29.690
He ruleth by his power forever. His eyes behold the nations. Let not the rebellious

02:09:29.690 --> 02:09:40.130
exalt themselves. Say la. O bless our God, ye people, and make the voice of his praise to be

02:09:40.130 --> 02:09:48.510
heard, which holdeth our soul in life, and suffereth not our feet to be moved. For thou, O God, hast

02:09:48.510 --> 02:09:56.850
proved us. Thou hast tried us, as silver is tried. Thou broadest us into the net. Thou

02:09:56.850 --> 02:10:03.750
laitst affliction upon our loins. Thou hast caused men to ride over our heads.

02:10:04.930 --> 02:10:12.190
We went through fire and through water, but thou broadest us out into a wealthy place.

02:10:12.190 --> 02:10:20.750
I will go into thy house with burnt offerings. I will pay thee my vows, which my lips have uttered,

02:10:20.750 --> 02:10:28.290
and my mouth hath spoken when I was in trouble. I will offer unto thee burnt sacrifices of

02:10:28.290 --> 02:10:35.710
fatlings. With the incense of rams I will offer bullocks with goats. Say la.

02:10:36.670 --> 02:10:43.690
Come and hear all ye that fear God, and I will declare what he hath done for my soul.

02:10:44.410 --> 02:10:50.930
I cried unto him with my mouth, and he was extolled with my tongue. If I regard iniquity

02:10:50.930 --> 02:10:59.110
in my heart, the Lord will not hear me. But verily God hath heard me. He hath attended to the voice

02:10:59.110 --> 02:11:08.320
of my prayer. Blessed be God, which hath not turned away my prayer, nor his mercy from me.

02:11:10.320 --> 02:11:15.220
Psalms 67-72

02:11:15.220 --> 02:11:29.620
This is a LibriVax recording. All LibriVax recordings are in the public domain. For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibriVax.org.

02:11:33.600 --> 02:11:41.360
The Book of Psalms, King James Version, Psalm 67

02:11:41.360 --> 02:11:51.360
God, be merciful unto us and bless us, and cause his face to shine upon us, Selah.

02:11:52.560 --> 02:11:59.100
That thy way may be known upon earth, thy saving health among all nations.

02:11:59.100 --> 02:12:04.820
Let the people praise thee, O God, let all the people praise thee.

02:12:05.220 --> 02:12:17.460
O, let the nations be glad and sing for joy, for thou shalt judge the people righteously, and govern the nations upon earth, Selah.

02:12:17.760 --> 02:12:22.860
Let the people praise thee, O God, let all the people praise thee.

02:12:22.860 --> 02:12:31.300
Then shall the earth yield her increase, and God, even our own God, shall bless us.

02:12:31.480 --> 02:12:36.500
God shall bless us, and all the ends of the earth shall fear him.

02:12:37.960 --> 02:12:39.480
Psalm 68

02:12:39.480 --> 02:12:48.820
Let God arise, let his enemies be scattered, let them also that hate him flee before him.

02:12:48.820 --> 02:12:58.900
As smoke is driven away, so drive them away, as wax melteth before the fire, so let the wicked perish at the presence of God.

02:12:59.560 --> 02:13:07.040
But let the righteous be glad, let them rejoice before God, yea, let them exceedingly rejoice.

02:13:07.800 --> 02:13:13.980
Sing unto God, sing praises to his name, extol him.

02:13:13.980 --> 02:13:22.280
That writeth upon the heavens by his name, Jah, and rejoice before him.

02:13:22.800 --> 02:13:29.940
A father of the fatherless, and a judge of the widows, is God in his holy habitation.

02:13:30.920 --> 02:13:34.300
God setteth the solitary in families.

02:13:34.800 --> 02:13:39.060
He bringeth out those which are bound with chains.

02:13:39.060 --> 02:13:43.700
But the rebellious dwell in a dry land.

02:13:44.440 --> 02:13:52.360
O God, when thou wentest forth before thy people, when thou didst march through the wilderness, say la.

02:13:53.560 --> 02:13:58.580
The earth shook, the heavens also dropped at the presence of God.

02:13:59.080 --> 02:14:07.660
Even Sinai itself was moved at the presence of God, the God of Israel.

02:14:07.660 --> 02:14:15.360
Thou, O God, didst send a plentiful rain, whereby thou didst confirm thine inheritance.

02:14:15.980 --> 02:14:20.940
When it was weary, thy congregation hath dwelt therein.

02:14:21.140 --> 02:14:25.740
Thou, O God, hast prepared of thy goodness for the poor.

02:14:26.300 --> 02:14:32.260
The Lord gave the word, great was the company of those that published it.

02:14:32.260 --> 02:14:39.200
Kings of armies did flee apace, and she that tarried at home divided the spoil.

02:14:39.980 --> 02:14:47.740
Though ye have leaned among the pots, yet shall ye be as the wings of a dove,

02:14:48.180 --> 02:14:52.100
covered with silver, and her feathers with yellow gold.

02:14:52.780 --> 02:15:00.540
When the Almighty scattered kings in it, it was white as snow in salmon.

02:15:00.540 --> 02:15:09.500
The hill of God is as the hill of Bashan, and high hill as the hill of Bashan.

02:15:09.900 --> 02:15:17.280
Why leap ye, ye high hills? This is the hill which God desireth to dwell in.

02:15:17.520 --> 02:15:20.540
Yea, the Lord will dwell in it forever.

02:15:21.620 --> 02:15:26.440
The chariots of God are twenty thousand, even thousands of angels.

02:15:26.440 --> 02:15:32.260
The Lord is among them, as in Sinai, in the holy place.

02:15:32.600 --> 02:15:38.760
Thou hast ascended on high. Thou hast led captivity captive.

02:15:39.120 --> 02:15:42.740
Thou hast received gifts for men.

02:15:43.240 --> 02:15:49.440
Yea, for the rebellious also, that the Lord God might dwell among them.

02:15:49.440 --> 02:15:59.660
Blessed be the Lord, who daily loadeth us with benefits, even the God of our salvation, Selah.

02:16:00.540 --> 02:16:09.880
He that is our God is the God of salvation, and unto God the Lord belong the issues from death.

02:16:09.880 --> 02:16:20.960
But God shall wound the head of his enemies, and the hairy scalp of such in one as goeth on still in his trespasses.

02:16:21.020 --> 02:16:28.080
The Lord said, I will bring again from Bashan, I will bring my people again,

02:16:28.520 --> 02:16:36.220
from the depths of the sea, that thy foot may be dipped in the blood of thine enemies,

02:16:36.220 --> 02:16:40.740
and the tongue of thy dogs in the same.

02:16:41.320 --> 02:16:48.380
They have seen thy goings, O God, even the goings of my God, my King, in the sanctuary.

02:16:48.840 --> 02:16:53.220
The singers went before, the players on instruments followed after.

02:16:53.720 --> 02:16:58.240
Among them were the damsels playing with timbrels.

02:16:58.620 --> 02:17:04.540
Bless ye God in the congregations, even the Lord from the fountain of Israel.

02:17:04.540 --> 02:17:11.340
There is little Benjamin with their ruler, the princes of Judah and their council,

02:17:11.740 --> 02:17:16.220
the princes of Zebulon, and the princes of Nepheli.

02:17:17.140 --> 02:17:19.780
Thy God hath commanded thy strength.

02:17:20.400 --> 02:17:25.260
Strengthen, O God, that which thou hast wrought for us.

02:17:25.820 --> 02:17:32.860
Because of thy temple at Jerusalem shall kings bring presents unto thee.

02:17:33.840 --> 02:17:40.900
Rebuke the company of spearmen, the multitude of the bulls, with the calves of the people,

02:17:41.420 --> 02:17:45.460
till every one submit himself with pieces of silver.

02:17:45.780 --> 02:17:49.180
Scatter thou the people that delight in war.

02:17:49.620 --> 02:17:51.820
Princes shall come out of Egypt.

02:17:52.240 --> 02:17:57.020
Ethiopia shall soon stretch out her hands unto God.

02:17:57.700 --> 02:18:00.420
Sing unto God, ye kingdoms of the earth.

02:18:00.420 --> 02:18:05.220
O sing praises unto the Lord, Selah.

02:18:05.740 --> 02:18:11.660
To him that writeth upon the heavens of heavens, which were of old,

02:18:11.960 --> 02:18:17.240
lo, he doth send out his voice, and that a mighty voice.

02:18:17.700 --> 02:18:20.240
Ascribe ye strength unto God.

02:18:20.500 --> 02:18:26.360
His excellency is over Israel, and his strength is in the clouds.

02:18:26.360 --> 02:18:31.600
O God, thou art terrible out of thy holy places.

02:18:31.980 --> 02:18:37.560
The God of Israel is he that giveth strength and power unto his people.

02:18:37.940 --> 02:18:40.240
Blessed be God.

02:18:42.320 --> 02:18:43.490
Psalm 69.

02:18:44.460 --> 02:18:49.000
Save me, O God, for the waters are come in unto my soul.

02:18:49.440 --> 02:18:53.600
I sink in deep mire where there is no standing.

02:18:53.600 --> 02:19:00.820
I am come into deep waters where the floods overflow me.

02:19:01.100 --> 02:19:02.920
I am weary of my crying.

02:19:03.140 --> 02:19:04.980
My throat is dried.

02:19:05.580 --> 02:19:10.060
Mine eyes fail while I wait for my God.

02:19:10.900 --> 02:19:16.040
They that hate me without a cause are more than the hairs of mine head.

02:19:16.400 --> 02:19:21.580
They that would destroy me, being mine enemies wrongfully, are mighty.

02:19:21.580 --> 02:19:25.900
Then I restore that which I took not away.

02:19:26.600 --> 02:19:32.040
O God, thou knowest my foolishness, and my sins are not hid from thee.

02:19:32.760 --> 02:19:38.360
Let not them that wait on thee, O Lord God of hosts, be ashamed.

02:19:38.960 --> 02:19:47.000
For my sake, let not those that seek thee be confounded for my sake, O God of Israel.

02:19:47.000 --> 02:19:53.420
Because for thy sake I have borne reproach, shame hath covered my face.

02:19:53.880 --> 02:19:59.900
I am become a stranger unto my brethren, and an alien unto my mother's children.

02:20:00.560 --> 02:20:09.640
For the zeal of thine house hath eaten me up, and the reproaches of them that reproached thee are fallen upon me.

02:20:10.000 --> 02:20:16.220
When I wept and chastened my soul with fasting, that was to my reproach.

02:20:16.220 --> 02:20:21.680
I made sackcloth also my garment, and I became a proverb to them.

02:20:22.720 --> 02:20:28.820
They that sit in the gates speak against me, and I was the song of the drunkards.

02:20:29.240 --> 02:20:35.940
But as for me, my prayer is unto thee, O Lord, in an acceptable time, O God.

02:20:36.380 --> 02:20:41.800
In the multitude of thy mercy hear me in the truth of thy salvation.

02:20:41.800 --> 02:20:46.560
Deliver me out of the mire, and let me not sink.

02:20:47.080 --> 02:20:52.820
Let me be delivered from them that hate me, and out of the deep waters.

02:20:53.320 --> 02:20:58.420
Let not the water-flood overflow me, neither let the deep swallow me up.

02:20:58.660 --> 02:21:02.220
And let not the pit shut her mouth upon me.

02:21:02.640 --> 02:21:06.340
Hear me, O Lord, for thy loving-kindness is good.

02:21:06.340 --> 02:21:15.180
Turn unto me according to the multitude of thy tender mercies, and hide not thy face from thy servant.

02:21:15.620 --> 02:21:18.580
For I am in trouble. Hear me speedily.

02:21:18.900 --> 02:21:21.840
Draw nigh unto my soul, and redeem it.

02:21:22.020 --> 02:21:24.660
Deliver me because of mine enemies.

02:21:25.120 --> 02:21:29.640
Thou hast known my reproach, and my shame, and my dishonor.

02:21:30.300 --> 02:21:33.120
Mine adversaries are all before thee.

02:21:33.120 --> 02:21:37.820
My reproach hath broken my heart, and I am full of heaviness.

02:21:38.120 --> 02:21:41.840
And I looked for some to take pity, but there was none.

02:21:42.160 --> 02:21:44.980
And for comforters, but I found none.

02:21:45.720 --> 02:21:52.100
They gave me also gall for my meat, and in my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.

02:21:52.860 --> 02:22:00.940
Let their table become a snare before them, and that which should have been for their welfare, let it become a trap.

02:22:00.940 --> 02:22:08.600
Let their eyes be darkened that they see not, and make their loins continually to shake.

02:22:09.380 --> 02:22:15.480
Pour out thine indignation upon them, and let thy wrathful anger take hold of them.

02:22:15.880 --> 02:22:21.040
Let their habitation be desolate, and let none dwell in their tents.

02:22:21.500 --> 02:22:28.920
For they persecute him whom thou hast smitten, and they talk to the grief of those whom thou hast wounded.

02:22:28.920 --> 02:22:35.180
Add iniquity unto their iniquity, and let them not come into thy righteousness.

02:22:36.060 --> 02:22:42.480
Let them be blotted out of the book of the living, and not be written with the righteous.

02:22:43.100 --> 02:22:50.160
But I am poor and sorrowful. Let thy salvation, O God, set me up on high.

02:22:50.660 --> 02:22:56.120
I will praise the name of God with a song, and will magnify him with thanksgiving.

02:22:56.120 --> 02:23:04.920
This also shall please the Lord better than an ox or bullock that hath horns and hoofs.

02:23:04.980 --> 02:23:11.540
The humble shall see this and be glad, and your heart shall live that seek God.

02:23:11.860 --> 02:23:15.960
For the Lord heareth the poor and despiseth not his prisoners.

02:23:16.520 --> 02:23:22.340
Let the heaven and earth praise him, the seas and everything that moveth therein.

02:23:22.340 --> 02:23:30.980
For God will save Zion, and will build the cities of Judah, that they may dwell there and have it in possession.

02:23:31.700 --> 02:23:40.300
The seed also of his servants shall inherit it, and they that love his name shall dwell therein.

02:23:43.120 --> 02:23:49.680
Make haste, O God, to deliver me. Make haste to help me, O Lord.

02:23:49.680 --> 02:23:55.240
Let them be ashamed and confounded that seek after my soul.

02:23:55.460 --> 02:24:00.760
Let them be turned backward and put to confusion that desire my hurt.

02:24:01.140 --> 02:24:07.960
Let them be turned back for a reward of their shame that say, Aha! Aha!

02:24:08.520 --> 02:24:13.240
Let all those that seek thee rejoice and be glad in thee.

02:24:13.240 --> 02:24:20.840
And let such as love thy salvation say continually, Let God be magnified.

02:24:21.340 --> 02:24:26.980
But I am poor and needy. Make haste unto me, O God.

02:24:27.360 --> 02:24:32.780
Thou art my help and my deliverer, O Lord. Make no tarrying.

02:24:34.720 --> 02:24:39.920
Psalm 71. In thee, O Lord, do I put my trust.

02:24:39.920 --> 02:24:47.560
Let me never be put to confusion. Deliver me in thy righteousness and cause me to escape.

02:24:48.100 --> 02:24:50.940
Incline thine ear unto me and save me.

02:24:51.900 --> 02:24:56.720
Be thou my strong habitation, whereunto I may continually resort.

02:24:57.140 --> 02:25:03.080
Thou hast given commandment to save me, for thou art my rock and my fortress.

02:25:03.080 --> 02:25:12.160
Deliver me, O my God, out of the hand of the wicked, out of the hand of the unrighteous and cruel man.

02:25:12.820 --> 02:25:18.840
For thou art my hope, O Lord God. Thou art my trust from my youth.

02:25:19.640 --> 02:25:27.940
By thee have I been holding up from the womb. Thou art he that took me out of my mother's bowels.

02:25:27.940 --> 02:25:34.640
My praise shall be continually of thee. I am as a wonder unto many.

02:25:34.960 --> 02:25:43.620
But thou art my strong refuge. Let my mouth be filled with thy praise and with thy honor all the day.

02:25:44.200 --> 02:25:50.720
Cast me not off in the time of old age. Forsake me not when my strength faileth.

02:25:50.720 --> 02:25:59.220
For mine enemies speak against me, and they that lay wait for my soul take counsel together, saying,

02:25:59.580 --> 02:26:06.040
God hath forsaken him. Persecute and take him, for there is none to deliver him.

02:26:06.680 --> 02:26:12.120
O God, be not far from me. O my God, make haste for my help.

02:26:12.620 --> 02:26:17.880
Let them be confounded and consumed that are adversaries to my soul.

02:26:17.880 --> 02:26:22.820
Let them be covered with reproach and dishonor that seek my hurt.

02:26:23.380 --> 02:26:28.440
But I will hope continually and will yet praise thee more and more.

02:26:28.860 --> 02:26:34.240
My mouth shall show forth thy righteousness and thy salvation all the day.

02:26:34.780 --> 02:26:40.940
For I know not the numbers thereof. I will go in the strength of the Lord God.

02:26:40.940 --> 02:26:46.880
I will make mention of thy righteousness, even of thine only.

02:26:47.080 --> 02:26:53.880
O God, thou hast taught me from my youth, and hitherto have I declared thy wondrous works.

02:26:54.220 --> 02:27:04.620
Now also, when I am old and gray-headed, O God, forsake me not until I have showed thy strength unto this generation

02:27:04.620 --> 02:27:08.940
and thy power to everyone that is to come.

02:27:08.940 --> 02:27:18.680
Thy righteousness also, O God, is very high. Who has done great things, O God, who is like unto thee?

02:27:19.240 --> 02:27:24.340
Thou, which has showed me great and sore troubles, shalt quicken me again,

02:27:24.720 --> 02:27:29.100
and shalt bring me up again from the depths of the earth.

02:27:29.840 --> 02:27:34.860
Thou shalt increase my greatness and comfort me on every side.

02:27:34.860 --> 02:27:41.120
I will also praise thee with the salt tree, even thy truth, O my God.

02:27:41.340 --> 02:27:47.760
Unto thee will I sing with the heart, O thou holy one of Israel.

02:27:48.800 --> 02:27:55.180
My lips shall greatly rejoice when I sing unto thee, and my soul which thou hast redeemed.

02:27:55.740 --> 02:28:01.280
My tongue also shall talk of thy righteousness all the day long.

02:28:01.280 --> 02:28:08.920
For they are confounded, for they are brought unto shame that seek my hurt.

02:28:10.340 --> 02:28:12.180
Psalm 72.

02:28:13.300 --> 02:28:20.760
Give the king thy judgments, O God, and thy righteousness unto the king's son.

02:28:21.300 --> 02:28:26.560
He shall judge thy people with righteousness, and thy poor with judgment.

02:28:26.560 --> 02:28:32.660
The mountains shall bring peace to the people, and the little hills by righteousness.

02:28:33.500 --> 02:28:36.040
He shall judge the poor of the people.

02:28:36.400 --> 02:28:42.560
He shall save the children of the needy, and shall break in pieces the oppressor.

02:28:43.520 --> 02:28:48.180
They shall fear thee as long as the sun and moon endure.

02:28:48.180 --> 02:28:58.700
For throughout all generations he shall come down like rain upon the mown grass as showers that water the earth.

02:28:59.460 --> 02:29:07.060
In his days shall the righteous flourish, an abundance of peace so long as the moon endureth.

02:29:07.240 --> 02:29:15.920
He shall have dominion also from sea to sea, and from the river unto the ends of the earth.

02:29:15.920 --> 02:29:25.080
They that dwell in the wilderness shall bow before him, and his enemies shall lick the dust.

02:29:25.840 --> 02:29:30.320
The kings of Tarshish and of the Isles shall bring presents.

02:29:31.020 --> 02:29:34.880
The kings of Sheba and Seba shall offer gifts.

02:29:35.220 --> 02:29:39.360
Yea, all kings shall fall down before him.

02:29:39.700 --> 02:29:42.040
All nations shall serve him.

02:29:42.040 --> 02:29:49.040
For he shall deliver the needy when he crieth, the poor also, and him who hath no helper.

02:29:49.700 --> 02:29:55.460
He shall spare the poor and needy, and shall save the souls of the needy.

02:29:55.480 --> 02:30:04.340
He shall redeem their soul from deceit and violence, and precious shall their blood be in his sight.

02:30:04.340 --> 02:30:10.480
And he shall live, and to him shall be given of the gold of Sheba.

02:30:10.660 --> 02:30:17.620
Prayer also shall be made for him, continually and daily shall he be praised.

02:30:18.340 --> 02:30:24.300
There shall be a handful of corn in the earth, upon the top of the mountains.

02:30:24.720 --> 02:30:33.380
The fruit thereof shall shake like Lebanon, and they of the city shall flourish like grass of the earth.

02:30:33.380 --> 02:30:37.240
His name shall endure forever.

02:30:37.880 --> 02:30:46.600
His name shall be continued as long as the sun and men shall be blessed in him.

02:30:46.940 --> 02:30:50.460
All nations shall call him blessed.

02:30:50.980 --> 02:30:58.060
Blessed be the Lord God, the God of Israel, who only doeth wondrous things.

02:30:58.500 --> 02:31:02.320
And blessed be his glorious name forever.

02:31:02.320 --> 02:31:06.500
And let the whole earth be filled with his glory.

02:31:07.260 --> 02:31:09.660
Amen, and amen.

02:31:10.540 --> 02:31:16.300
The prayers of David, the son of Jesse, are ended.

02:31:17.280 --> 02:31:21.860
End of Psalms 67-72.

02:31:24.780 --> 02:31:27.660
Psalm 73-78

02:31:42.960 --> 02:31:47.540
Truly God is good to Israel, even to such as are of a clean heart.

02:31:48.120 --> 02:31:52.640
But as for me my feet were almost gone, my steps had well nigh slipped,

02:31:52.640 --> 02:31:57.080
for I was envious at the foolish, when I saw the prosperity of the wicked.

02:31:57.820 --> 02:32:01.480
For there are no bands in their death, but their strength is firm.

02:32:02.240 --> 02:32:06.700
They are not in trouble as other men, neither are they plagued like other men.

02:32:07.280 --> 02:32:13.140
Therefore pride compasseth them about as a chain, violence covereth them as a garment.

02:32:13.920 --> 02:32:17.980
Their eyes stand out with fatness, they have more than heart could wish.

02:32:17.980 --> 02:32:23.060
They are corrupt and speak wickedly concerning oppression, they speak loftily.

02:32:23.720 --> 02:32:27.360
They set their mouth against the heavens, and their tongue walketh through the earth.

02:32:28.220 --> 02:32:32.800
Therefore his people return hither, and waters of a full cup are wrung out to them.

02:32:33.440 --> 02:32:37.520
And they say, How doth God know? and is their knowledge in the most high?

02:32:38.460 --> 02:32:43.220
Behold, these are the ungodly who prosper in the world, they increase in riches.

02:32:44.300 --> 02:32:49.600
Verily, I have cleansed my heart in vain, and washed my hands in innocency.

02:32:50.760 --> 02:32:54.840
For all the day long have I been plagued and chastened every morning.

02:32:55.680 --> 02:33:00.480
If I say, I will speak thus, behold, I should offend against the generation of thy children.

02:33:01.200 --> 02:33:04.260
When I thought to know this, it was too painful for me.

02:33:04.820 --> 02:33:09.080
Until I went into the sanctuary of God, then understood I their end.

02:33:09.460 --> 02:33:14.480
Surely thou didst set them as slippery places, thou castedst them down into destruction.

02:33:15.300 --> 02:33:17.980
How they are brought into desolation, as in a moment.

02:33:18.320 --> 02:33:20.360
They are utterly consumed with terrors.

02:33:20.580 --> 02:33:26.120
As a dream, when one awaketh, so, O Lord, when thou awakest, thou shalt despise their

02:33:26.120 --> 02:33:26.460
image.

02:33:27.340 --> 02:33:30.000
Thus my heart was grieved, and I was pricked in my reins.

02:33:30.720 --> 02:33:34.140
So foolish was I, and ignorant, I was as a beast before thee.

02:33:34.920 --> 02:33:39.360
Nevertheless, I am continually with thee, thou hast holden me by my right hand.

02:33:40.040 --> 02:33:43.880
Thou shalt guide me with thy counsel, and afterward receive me to glory.

02:33:44.740 --> 02:33:49.400
Whom have I in heaven but thee, and there is none upon earth that I desire beside thee.

02:33:50.340 --> 02:33:56.440
My flesh and my heart faileth, but God is the strength of my heart, and my portion forever.

02:33:56.960 --> 02:34:01.600
For lo, they that are far from thee shall perish, thou hast destroyed all them that

02:34:01.600 --> 02:34:03.080
go a-whoring from thee.

02:34:03.760 --> 02:34:06.500
But it is good for me to draw near to God.

02:34:07.100 --> 02:34:11.320
I have put my trust in the Lord God, that I may declare all thy works.

02:34:12.740 --> 02:34:16.840
Psalm 74 O God, why hast thou cast us off forever?

02:34:17.420 --> 02:34:20.700
Why dost thine anger smoke against the sheep of thy pasture?

02:34:21.580 --> 02:34:27.100
Remember thy congregation, which thou hast purchased of old, the rod of thine inheritance,

02:34:27.100 --> 02:34:31.700
which thou hast redeemed, this Mount Zion wherein thou hast dwelt.

02:34:32.620 --> 02:34:37.940
Lift up thy feet unto the perpetual desolations, even all that the enemy hath done wickedly

02:34:37.940 --> 02:34:38.680
in the sanctuary.

02:34:39.580 --> 02:34:44.280
Thine enemies roar in the midst of thy congregations, they set up their ensigns for signs.

02:34:45.220 --> 02:34:49.260
A man was famous according as he had lifted up axes upon the thick trees.

02:34:50.300 --> 02:34:54.720
But now they break down the carved work thereof at once with axes and hammers.

02:34:54.720 --> 02:34:59.340
They have cast fire into thy sanctuary, they have defiled by casting down the dwelling

02:34:59.340 --> 02:35:01.080
place of thy name to the ground.

02:35:01.820 --> 02:35:06.420
They said in their hearts, Let us destroy them together, they have burned up all the

02:35:06.420 --> 02:35:08.120
synagogues of God in the land.

02:35:09.160 --> 02:35:14.740
We see not our signs, there is no more any prophet, neither is there among us any that

02:35:14.740 --> 02:35:15.640
knoweth how long.

02:35:16.500 --> 02:35:19.760
O God, how long shall the adversary reproach?

02:35:20.120 --> 02:35:22.120
Shall the enemy blaspheme thy name forever?

02:35:23.320 --> 02:35:26.320
Why withdrawest thou thy hand, even thy right hand?

02:35:26.640 --> 02:35:27.720
Pluck it out of thy bosom.

02:35:29.260 --> 02:35:32.960
For God is my King of old, working salvation in the midst of the earth.

02:35:33.680 --> 02:35:38.260
Thou didst divide the sea by thy strength, thou breakest the heads of the dragons in

02:35:38.260 --> 02:35:44.080
the waters, thou breakest the heads of leviathan in pieces, and gavest him to be meat to the

02:35:44.080 --> 02:35:45.460
people inhabiting the wilderness.

02:35:46.060 --> 02:35:50.640
Thou didst cleave the fountain and the flood, thou driedst up mighty rivers.

02:35:52.120 --> 02:35:56.460
The day is thine, the night also is thine, thou hast prepared the light and the sun,

02:35:57.060 --> 02:36:00.600
thou hast set all the borders of the earth, thou hast made summer and winter.

02:36:01.480 --> 02:36:06.400
Remember this, that the enemy hath reproached, O Lord, and that the foolish people have blasphemed

02:36:06.400 --> 02:36:07.120
thy name.

02:36:07.960 --> 02:36:12.420
O, deliver not the soul of thy turtle dove unto the multitude of the wicked, forget not

02:36:12.420 --> 02:36:14.340
the congregation of thy poor forever.

02:36:15.120 --> 02:36:20.720
Have respect unto the covenant, for the dark places of the earth are full of the habitations

02:36:20.720 --> 02:36:21.440
of cruelty.

02:36:22.540 --> 02:36:27.200
O, let not the oppressed return ashamed, let the poor and needy praise thy name.

02:36:28.020 --> 02:36:33.140
Arise, O God, clean thine own cause, remember how the foolish man reproacheth thee daily.

02:36:33.960 --> 02:36:38.020
Forget not the voice of thine enemies, the tumult of those that rise up against thee

02:36:38.020 --> 02:36:39.500
increaseth continually.

02:36:41.140 --> 02:36:42.100
Psalm 75

02:36:42.700 --> 02:36:47.900
Unto thee, O God, do we give thanks, unto thee do we give thanks, for that thy name

02:36:47.900 --> 02:36:50.100
is near thy wondrous works declare.

02:36:51.680 --> 02:36:55.500
When I shall receive the congregation, I will judge uprightly.

02:36:56.040 --> 02:37:00.740
The earth and all the inhabitants thereof are dissolved, I bear up the pillars of it,

02:37:00.840 --> 02:37:01.340
salah.

02:37:02.100 --> 02:37:08.120
I said unto the fools, Deal not foolishly, and to the wicked, lift not up the horn, lift

02:37:08.120 --> 02:37:12.860
not up your horn on high, speak not with a stiff neck, for a promotion comes neither

02:37:12.860 --> 02:37:15.560
from the east, nor from the west, nor from the south.

02:37:16.360 --> 02:37:20.140
But God is the judge, he putteth down one, and setteth up another.

02:37:21.140 --> 02:37:26.980
For in the hand of the Lord there is a cup, and the wine is red, it is full of mixture,

02:37:27.360 --> 02:37:32.340
and he poureth out of the same, but the dregs thereof, all the wicked of the earth, shall

02:37:32.340 --> 02:37:33.800
wring them out and drink them.

02:37:34.320 --> 02:37:38.020
But I will declare, for ever, I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.

02:37:38.880 --> 02:37:43.200
All the horns of the wicked also will I cut off, but the horns of the righteous shall

02:37:43.200 --> 02:37:43.960
be exalted.

02:37:45.120 --> 02:37:46.080
Psalm 76

02:37:46.740 --> 02:37:49.900
In Judah is God known, his name is great in Israel.

02:37:50.460 --> 02:37:53.900
In Salem also is his tabernacle, and his dwelling place in Zion.

02:37:54.680 --> 02:37:59.600
There break he the arrows of the bow, the shield, and the sword, and the battle, salah.

02:38:00.240 --> 02:38:03.560
Thou art more glorious and excellent than the mountains of prey.

02:38:04.380 --> 02:38:09.420
The stout-hearted are spoiled, they have slept their sleep, and none of the men of might

02:38:09.420 --> 02:38:10.560
have found their hands.

02:38:12.400 --> 02:38:16.880
At thy rebuke, O God of Jacob, both the chariot and horse are cast into a dead sleep.

02:38:18.320 --> 02:38:23.460
Thou, even thou, art to be feared, and who may stand in thy sight when once thou art

02:38:23.460 --> 02:38:23.860
angry?

02:38:24.780 --> 02:38:27.140
Thou didst cause judgments to be heard from heaven.

02:38:27.140 --> 02:38:29.300
The earth feared and was still.

02:38:30.240 --> 02:38:36.160
When God arose to judgment to save all the meek of the earth, salah, surely the wrath

02:38:36.160 --> 02:38:40.700
of man shall praise thee, the remainder of wrath shalt thou restrain.

02:38:41.080 --> 02:38:45.900
Vow and pay unto the Lord your God, let all that be round about him bring presents unto

02:38:45.900 --> 02:38:47.080
him that ought to be feared.

02:38:48.760 --> 02:38:52.880
He shall cut off the spirit of princes, he is terrible to the kings of the earth.

02:38:54.160 --> 02:38:55.120
Psalm 77

02:38:55.780 --> 02:39:01.260
I cried unto God with my voice, even unto God with my voice, and he gave ear unto me.

02:39:01.740 --> 02:39:06.840
In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord, my sore ran in the night, and ceased not,

02:39:07.280 --> 02:39:09.180
my soul refused to be comforted.

02:39:09.620 --> 02:39:11.500
I remembered God and was troubled.

02:39:12.380 --> 02:39:15.960
I complained and my spirit was overwhelmed, salah.

02:39:16.780 --> 02:39:20.540
Thou holdest mine eyes waking, I am so troubled that I cannot speak.

02:39:21.140 --> 02:39:24.600
I have considered the days of old, the years of ancient times.

02:39:25.640 --> 02:39:31.020
I called to remembrance my song in the night, I communed with mine own heart, and my spirit

02:39:31.020 --> 02:39:32.200
made diligent search.

02:39:33.160 --> 02:39:37.020
Will the Lord cast off for ever, and will he be favorable no more?

02:39:37.720 --> 02:39:39.920
Is his mercy clean gone for ever?

02:39:40.420 --> 02:39:42.180
Doth his promise fail for ever more?

02:39:43.060 --> 02:39:44.620
Hath God forgotten to be gracious?

02:39:45.420 --> 02:39:47.760
Hath he in anger shut up his tender mercies?

02:39:48.620 --> 02:39:49.180
Salah.

02:39:49.760 --> 02:39:54.080
And I said this is my infirmity, but I will remember the years of the right hand of the

02:39:54.080 --> 02:39:54.820
Most High.

02:39:55.420 --> 02:39:59.620
I will remember the works of the Lord, surely I will remember thy works of old.

02:40:00.400 --> 02:40:05.360
I will meditate also of all thy works, and talk of thy doings.

02:40:05.800 --> 02:40:09.820
Thy way, O God, is in the sanctuary, who is so great a God as our God.

02:40:10.660 --> 02:40:15.200
Thou art the God that doest wonders, thou hast declared thy strength among the people.

02:40:15.800 --> 02:40:20.080
Thou hast with thine arm redeemed thy people, the sons of Jacob and Joseph.

02:40:20.800 --> 02:40:21.400
Salah.

02:40:22.420 --> 02:40:24.020
The waters saw thee, O God.

02:40:24.500 --> 02:40:27.960
The waters saw thee, they were afraid, the depths also were troubled.

02:40:28.660 --> 02:40:30.300
The clouds poured out water.

02:40:30.940 --> 02:40:34.640
The skies sent out a sound, thine arrows also went abroad.

02:40:35.440 --> 02:40:37.560
The voice of thy thunder was in the heaven.

02:40:38.140 --> 02:40:41.280
The lightnings lightened the world, the earth trembled and shook.

02:40:41.940 --> 02:40:47.140
Thy way is in the sea, and thy path in the great waters, and thy footsteps are not known.

02:40:47.760 --> 02:40:51.120
Thou lettest thy people like a flock by the hand of Moses and Aaron.

02:40:52.940 --> 02:40:53.900
Psalm 78.

02:40:54.900 --> 02:40:59.480
Give ear, O my people, to my law, incline your ears to the words of my mouth.

02:41:00.340 --> 02:41:06.020
I will open my mouth in a parable, I will utter dark sayings of old, which we have heard

02:41:06.020 --> 02:41:08.120
and known and our fathers have told us.

02:41:08.120 --> 02:41:13.920
We will not hide them from their children, shewing to the generation to come the praises

02:41:13.920 --> 02:41:18.140
of the Lord, and his strength, and his wonderful works that he hath done.

02:41:18.800 --> 02:41:24.440
For he established a testimony in Jacob, and appointed a law in Israel, which he commanded

02:41:24.440 --> 02:41:27.000
our fathers that they should make them known to their children.

02:41:27.960 --> 02:41:32.980
That the generation to come might know them, even the children which should be born, who

02:41:32.980 --> 02:41:35.060
should arise and declare them to their children.

02:41:35.580 --> 02:41:40.260
That they might set their hope in God, and not forget the works of God, but keep his

02:41:40.260 --> 02:41:46.420
commandments, and might not be as their fathers a stubborn and rebellious generation, a generation

02:41:46.420 --> 02:41:50.880
that set not their heart aright, and whose spirit was not steadfast with God.

02:41:51.760 --> 02:41:56.980
The children of Ephraim, being armed and carrying bows, turned back in the day of battle.

02:41:57.680 --> 02:42:02.980
They kept not the covenant of God, and refused to walk in his law, and forgot his works,

02:42:02.980 --> 02:42:05.280
and his wonders that he showed them.

02:42:06.320 --> 02:42:10.380
Marvelous things did he in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt in the field

02:42:10.380 --> 02:42:10.980
of Zohan.

02:42:11.700 --> 02:42:16.460
He divided the sea, and caused them to pass through, and he made the waters to stand as

02:42:16.460 --> 02:42:16.820
in heap.

02:42:17.700 --> 02:42:22.000
In the daytime also he led them with a cloud, and all the night with a light of fire.

02:42:22.700 --> 02:42:27.080
He claved the rocks in the wilderness, and gave them drink as out of the great depths.

02:42:27.640 --> 02:42:33.060
He brought streams also out of the rock, and caused waters to run down like rivers.

02:42:33.920 --> 02:42:38.700
And they sinned yet more against him by provoking the Most High in the wilderness, and they

02:42:38.700 --> 02:42:41.800
tempted God in their heart by asking meat for their lust.

02:42:42.640 --> 02:42:47.260
Yea, they spake against God, they said, Can God furnish a table in the wilderness?

02:42:48.160 --> 02:42:52.320
Behold he smote the rock, that the waters gushed out, and the streams overflowed.

02:42:52.340 --> 02:42:53.480
Can he give bread also?

02:42:53.480 --> 02:42:55.860
Can he provide flesh for his people?

02:42:57.180 --> 02:42:59.180
Therefore the Lord heard this, and was wroth.

02:42:59.780 --> 02:43:05.040
So a fire was kindled against Jacob, and anger also came up against Israel, because they

02:43:05.040 --> 02:43:08.540
believed not in God, and trusted not in his salvation.

02:43:09.220 --> 02:43:13.800
Though he had commanded the clouds from above, and opened the doors of heaven, and had rained

02:43:13.800 --> 02:43:18.020
down manna upon them to eat, and had given them of the corn of heaven.

02:43:18.760 --> 02:43:21.520
Man did eat angels' food, he sent them meat to the fold.

02:43:22.160 --> 02:43:27.240
He caused an east wind to blow in the heaven, and by his power he brought in the south wind.

02:43:27.760 --> 02:43:33.120
He rained flesh also upon them as dust, and feathered fowls like as the sand of the sea.

02:43:33.460 --> 02:43:36.780
And he let it fall in the midst of their camp round about their habitations.

02:43:37.360 --> 02:43:41.640
So they did eat, and were well filled, for he gave them their own desire.

02:43:42.180 --> 02:43:43.940
They were not estranged from their lust.

02:43:44.600 --> 02:43:48.820
But while their meat was yet in their mouth, the wrath of God came upon them, and slew

02:43:48.820 --> 02:43:51.520
the fattest of them, and smote down the chosen men of Israel.

02:43:52.600 --> 02:43:57.260
For all this they sinned still, and believed not for his wondrous works.

02:43:58.100 --> 02:44:02.460
Therefore their days did he consume in vanity, and their years in trouble.

02:44:03.280 --> 02:44:08.280
When he slew them, then they sought him, and they returned, and inquired early after God.

02:44:08.980 --> 02:44:13.000
And they remembered that God was their Rock, and the High God their Redeemer.

02:44:13.560 --> 02:44:17.980
Nevertheless they did flatter him with their mouth, and they lied unto him with their tongues.

02:44:18.900 --> 02:44:23.240
For their heart was not right with him, neither were they steadfast in his covenant.

02:44:24.040 --> 02:44:28.600
But he, being full of compassion, forgave their iniquity, and destroyed them not.

02:44:29.140 --> 02:44:33.780
Yea, many a time turned he his anger away, and did not stir up all his wrath.

02:44:34.400 --> 02:44:39.280
For he remembered that they were but flesh, a wind that passeth away, and cometh not again.

02:44:39.280 --> 02:44:43.160
How oft did they provoke him in the wilderness, and grieve him in the desert.

02:44:43.960 --> 02:44:47.480
Yea, they turned back, and tempted God, and limited the Holy One of Israel.

02:44:48.480 --> 02:44:52.240
They remembered not his hand, nor the day when he delivered them from the enemy.

02:44:52.980 --> 02:44:57.360
How he had wrought his signs in Egypt, and his wonders in the field of Zohan,

02:44:57.840 --> 02:45:02.280
and had turned their rivers into blood, and their floods that they could not drink.

02:45:02.800 --> 02:45:08.640
He sent diverse sorts of flies among them, which devoured them, and frogs which destroyed them.

02:45:09.420 --> 02:45:14.060
He gave also their increase unto the caterpillar, and their labor unto the locust.

02:45:14.760 --> 02:45:19.160
He destroyed their vines with hail, and their sycamore trees with frost.

02:45:19.700 --> 02:45:24.060
He gave up their cattle also to the hail, and their flocks to hot thunderbolts.

02:45:24.900 --> 02:45:28.760
He cast upon them the fierceness of his anger, wrath, and indignation,

02:45:29.200 --> 02:45:31.760
and trouble by sending evil angels among them.

02:45:32.320 --> 02:45:35.860
He made a way to his anger, he spared not their soul from death,

02:45:36.300 --> 02:45:38.260
but gave their life over to the pestilence.

02:45:38.840 --> 02:45:43.880
And smote all the first born in Egypt, the chief of their strength in the tabernacles of Ham,

02:45:44.760 --> 02:45:49.420
but made his own people to go forth like sheep, and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.

02:45:50.820 --> 02:45:55.520
And he led them on safely, so that they feared not, but the sea overwhelmed their enemies.

02:45:56.620 --> 02:46:00.100
And he brought them to the border of his sanctuary, even to this mountain,

02:46:00.300 --> 02:46:01.720
which his right hand had purchased.

02:46:02.460 --> 02:46:07.400
He cast out the heathen also before them, and divided them in inheritance by line,

02:46:07.400 --> 02:46:10.140
and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.

02:46:11.280 --> 02:46:15.540
Yet they tempted and provoked the Most High God, and kept not his testimonies.

02:46:16.340 --> 02:46:19.520
But turned back, and dealt unfaithfully like their fathers,

02:46:20.040 --> 02:46:22.180
they were turned aside like a deceitful bow,

02:46:22.620 --> 02:46:24.980
for they provoked him to anger with their high places,

02:46:25.080 --> 02:46:27.240
and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.

02:46:28.220 --> 02:46:31.380
When God heard this, he was wroth, and greatly abhorred Israel,

02:46:31.760 --> 02:46:36.860
so that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent which he placed among men.

02:46:36.860 --> 02:46:41.960
And delivered his strength into captivity, and his glory into the enemy's hand.

02:46:42.680 --> 02:46:47.380
He gave his people over also unto the sword, and was wroth with his inheritance.

02:46:48.520 --> 02:46:52.580
The fire consumed their young men, and their maidens were not given to marriage.

02:46:53.280 --> 02:46:57.380
Their priests fell by the sword, and their widows made no lamentation.

02:46:58.300 --> 02:47:02.940
Then the Lord awaked as one out of sleep, and like a mighty man that shouteth by reason of wine.

02:47:02.940 --> 02:47:07.660
And he smote his enemies in the hindered parts, he put them to a perpetual reproach.

02:47:08.740 --> 02:47:13.700
Moreover he refused the tabernacle of Joseph, and chose not the tribe of Ephraim,

02:47:14.420 --> 02:47:17.960
but chose the tribe of Judah, the mountain Zion which he loved.

02:47:19.900 --> 02:47:25.200
And he built his sanctuary like high palaces, like the earth which he hath established forever.

02:47:25.920 --> 02:47:29.740
He chose David also his servant, and took him from the sheepfolds.

02:47:30.280 --> 02:47:34.820
From following the ooze great with young, he brought him to feed Jacob his people,

02:47:35.100 --> 02:47:36.500
and Israel his inheritance.

02:47:37.400 --> 02:47:39.840
So he fed them according to the integrity of his heart,

02:47:40.400 --> 02:47:42.720
and guided them by the skillfulness of his hands.

02:47:44.720 --> 02:47:47.540
Psalm 79 to 88.

02:48:01.490 --> 02:48:03.300
The Book of Psalms.

02:48:03.540 --> 02:48:05.300
King James Version.

02:48:06.200 --> 02:48:07.140
Psalm 79.

02:48:08.300 --> 02:48:11.880
O God, the heathen are come into thine inheritance.

02:48:12.510 --> 02:48:17.670
Thy holy temple have they defiled, they have laid Jerusalem on heaps.

02:48:19.040 --> 02:48:25.000
The dead bodies of thy servants have they given to be meat unto the fowls of the heaven,

02:48:25.800 --> 02:48:28.720
the flesh of thy saints unto the beasts of the earth.

02:48:29.680 --> 02:48:37.240
Their blood have they shed like water round about Jerusalem, and there was none to bury them.

02:48:37.240 --> 02:48:45.180
We are become a reproach to our neighbors, a scorn and derision to them that are round about us.

02:48:46.380 --> 02:48:53.240
How long, O Lord, wilt thou be angry forever? Shall thy jealousy burn like fire?

02:48:54.520 --> 02:49:01.540
Pour out thy wrath upon the heathen that have not known thee, and upon the kingdoms that have not

02:49:01.540 --> 02:49:10.900
thy name. For they have devoured Jacob, and laid waste his dwelling place. O,

02:49:11.240 --> 02:49:17.800
remember not against us former iniquities, let thy tender mercy speedily prevent us,

02:49:18.120 --> 02:49:26.920
for we are brought very low. Help us, O God of our salvation, for the glory of thy name,

02:49:26.920 --> 02:49:31.800
and deliver us, and purge away our sins for thy name's sake.

02:49:33.380 --> 02:49:37.140
Wherefore should the heathen say, Where is their God?

02:49:38.060 --> 02:49:44.920
Let him be known among the heathen in our sight, by the revenging of the blood of thy servants

02:49:44.920 --> 02:49:51.630
which is shed. Let the sighing of the prisoner come before thee. According to the greatness of

02:49:51.630 --> 02:49:59.170
thy power, preserve thou those that are appointed to die, and render unto our neighbors sevenfold

02:49:59.170 --> 02:50:07.130
into their bosom their reproach, wherewith they have reproached thee, O Lord. So we thy people

02:50:07.130 --> 02:50:14.330
and sheep of thy pasture will give thee thanks forever. We will show forth thy praise

02:50:14.330 --> 02:50:18.690
to all generations. Psalm 80

02:50:19.870 --> 02:50:28.050
Give ear, O shepherd of Israel, thou that leadest Joseph like a flock, thou that dwellest

02:50:28.050 --> 02:50:36.250
between the cherubims, shine forth, before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh. Stir up thy strength

02:50:36.250 --> 02:50:46.510
and save us. Turn us again, O God, and cause thy face to shine, and we shall be saved. O Lord,

02:50:46.630 --> 02:50:54.270
God of hosts, how long wilt thou be angry against the prayer of thy people? Thou feedest them with

02:50:54.270 --> 02:51:03.790
the bread of tears, and givest them tears to drink in great measure. Thou makest us a strife

02:51:03.790 --> 02:51:12.270
unto our neighbors, and our enemies laugh among themselves. Turn us again, O God of hosts,

02:51:12.930 --> 02:51:20.790
and cause thy face to shine, and we shall be saved. Thou hast brought a vine out of Egypt,

02:51:21.250 --> 02:51:28.530
thou hast cast out the heathen and planted it, thou preparest room before it, and didst

02:51:28.530 --> 02:51:35.670
cause it to take deep root, and it filled the land. The hills were covered with the shadow of it,

02:51:35.970 --> 02:51:42.750
and the boughs thereof were like the goodly cedars. She sent out her boughs unto the sea,

02:51:43.070 --> 02:51:52.650
and her branches unto the river. Why hast thou then broken down her hedges, so that all they

02:51:52.650 --> 02:52:01.390
which pass by the way do pluck her? The boar out of the wood doth waste it, and the wild beast of

02:52:01.390 --> 02:52:09.850
the field doth devour it. Return, we beseech thee, O God of hosts, look down from heaven,

02:52:10.070 --> 02:52:17.010
and behold, and visit this vine, and the vineyard which thy right hand hath planted, and the branch

02:52:17.010 --> 02:52:23.710
that thou made is strong for thyself. It is burned with fire, it is cut down,

02:52:23.950 --> 02:52:31.890
they perish at the rebuke of thy countenance. Let thy hand be upon the man of thy right hand,

02:52:32.290 --> 02:52:39.950
upon the son of man whom thou made is strong for thyself. So will not we go back from thee,

02:52:39.950 --> 02:52:49.610
quicken us, and we will call upon thy name. Turn us again, O Lord, God of hosts, cause thy face

02:52:49.610 --> 02:52:58.950
to shine, and we shall be saved. Psalm 81. Sing aloud unto God our strength. Make a joyful

02:52:58.950 --> 02:53:05.790
noise unto the God of Jacob. Take a psalm, and bring hither the timbrel, the pleasant harp,

02:53:05.790 --> 02:53:13.570
with the psaltery. Blow up the trumpet in the new moon, in the time appointed on our solemn feast

02:53:13.570 --> 02:53:22.430
day. For this was a statute for Israel, and a law of the God of Jacob. This he ordained in Joseph

02:53:22.430 --> 02:53:29.490
for a testimony, when he went out through the land of Egypt, where I heard a language that I

02:53:29.490 --> 02:53:37.490
understood not. I removed his shoulder from the burden, his hands were delivered from the pots.

02:53:38.630 --> 02:53:45.450
Thou cult'st in trouble, and I delivered thee. I answered thee in the secret place of thunder.

02:53:46.030 --> 02:53:55.830
I proved thee at the waters of Meribah. Selah. Here, O my people, and I will testify unto thee,

02:53:55.830 --> 02:54:03.190
O Israel, if thou wilt hearken unto me, there shall no strange God be in thee,

02:54:03.730 --> 02:54:12.530
neither shalt thou worship any strange God. I am the Lord thy God, which brought thee out of the

02:54:12.530 --> 02:54:19.790
land of Egypt. Open thy mouth wide, and I will fill it. But my people would not hearken to my voice,

02:54:19.790 --> 02:54:25.750
and Israel would none of me. So I gave them up unto their own heart's lust,

02:54:26.450 --> 02:54:32.190
and they walked in their own counsels. O that my people had hearkened unto me,

02:54:32.250 --> 02:54:38.530
and Israel had walked in my ways. I should soon have subdued their enemies,

02:54:39.290 --> 02:54:45.530
and turned my hand against their adversaries. The haters of the Lord should have submitted

02:54:45.530 --> 02:54:51.930
themselves unto him, but their time should have endured for ever. He should have fed them also

02:54:51.930 --> 02:54:58.870
with the finest of the wheat, and with honey out of the rock should I have satisfied thee.

02:55:00.090 --> 02:55:07.990
Psalm 82 God standeth in the congregation of the mighty, he judgeth among the gods.

02:55:08.890 --> 02:55:17.250
How long will ye judge unjustly, and accept the persons of the wicked? Say la! Defend the

02:55:17.250 --> 02:55:24.970
poor and fatherless, do justice to the afflicted and needy, deliver the poor and needy, rid them

02:55:24.970 --> 02:55:32.690
out of the hand of the wicked. They know not, neither will they understand, they walk on in

02:55:32.690 --> 02:55:40.510
darkness. All the foundations of the earth are out of course. I have said ye are gods,

02:55:41.250 --> 02:55:49.170
and all of you are children of the Most High, but ye shall die like men, and fall like one of the

02:55:49.170 --> 02:55:55.970
princes. Arise, O God, judge the earth, for thou shalt inherit all nations.

02:55:57.270 --> 02:56:07.150
Psalm 83 Keep not thou silence, O God, hold not thy peace, and be not still, O God, for lo, thine

02:56:07.150 --> 02:56:14.050
enemies make a tumult, and they that hate thee have lifted up the head. They have taken crafty

02:56:14.050 --> 02:56:21.570
counsel against thy people, and consulted against thy hidden ones. They have said, Come, let us cut

02:56:21.570 --> 02:56:29.830
them off from being a nation, that the name of Israel may be no more in remembrance. For they

02:56:29.830 --> 02:56:37.650
have consulted together with one consent, they are confederate against thee, the tabernacles of Edom,

02:56:38.070 --> 02:56:46.530
and the Ishmaelites of Moab and the Hagarines, Gebel and Ammon and Amalek the Philistines with

02:56:46.530 --> 02:56:55.210
the inhabitants of Tyre. Aesir also is joined with them. They have hopened the children of Lot.

02:56:57.750 --> 02:57:06.010
Do unto them as unto the Midianites, as to Sisera, as to Jabin at the brook of Kaishon,

02:57:06.350 --> 02:57:13.590
which perished at Endor, they became as dung for the earth. Make their nobles like Orib,

02:57:14.090 --> 02:57:22.930
and like Zebe, yea, all their princes as Zeba, and as Zalmunna, who said, Let us take to ourselves

02:57:22.930 --> 02:57:32.230
the houses of God in possession. O my God, make them like a wheel, as the stubble before the wind,

02:57:33.030 --> 02:57:40.670
as the fire burneth a wood, and as the flame setteth the mountains on fire. So persecute them

02:57:40.670 --> 02:57:48.750
with thy tempest, and make them afraid with thy storm. Fill their faces with shame,

02:57:49.070 --> 02:57:55.910
that they may seek thy name, O Lord. Let them be confounded and troubled forever, yea,

02:57:56.350 --> 02:58:05.710
let them be put to shame and perish, that men may know that thou, whose name alone is Jehovah, art

02:58:05.710 --> 02:58:14.570
the most high over all the earth. Psalm 84 How amiable are thy tabernacles, O Lord of hosts!

02:58:15.530 --> 02:58:23.610
My soul longeth, yea, even fainteth for the courts of the Lord. My heart and my flesh cryeth out for

02:58:23.610 --> 02:58:31.430
the living God. Yea, the sparrow hath found a house, and the swallow a nest for herself,

02:58:31.430 --> 02:58:39.470
where she may lay her young even thine altars, O Lord of hosts, my king and my God. Blessed are

02:58:39.470 --> 02:58:47.950
they that dwell in thy house. They will be still praising thee, say la. Blessed is the man whose

02:58:47.950 --> 02:58:55.710
strength is in thee, in whose heart are the ways of them, who passing through the valley of Baca,

02:58:55.710 --> 02:59:02.930
make it a well, the rain also filleth the pools. They go from strength to strength,

02:59:03.330 --> 02:59:11.590
every one of them in Zion appeareth before God. O Lord, God of hosts, hear my prayer,

02:59:11.870 --> 02:59:21.230
give ear, O God of Jacob, say la. Behold, O God, our shield, and look upon the face of thine anointed,

02:59:21.230 --> 02:59:27.770
for a day in thy courts is better than a thousand. I had rather be a doorkeeper

02:59:27.770 --> 02:59:31.950
in the house of my God than to dwell in the tents of wickedness.

02:59:33.730 --> 02:59:40.370
For the Lord God is a sun and shield. The Lord will give grace and glory,

02:59:40.670 --> 02:59:47.210
no good thing will he withhold from them that walk uprightly. O Lord of hosts,

02:59:48.090 --> 02:59:53.430
blessed is the man that trusteth in thee. Psalm 85

02:59:53.430 --> 03:00:01.330
Lord, thou hast been favorable unto thy land, thou hast brought back the captivity of Jacob,

03:00:02.270 --> 03:00:09.130
thou hast forgiven the iniquity of thy people, thou hast covered all their sin, say la.

03:00:09.830 --> 03:00:18.150
Thou hast taken away all thy wrath, thou hast turned thyself from the fierceness of thine anger,

03:00:18.890 --> 03:00:24.230
turn us, O God, of our salvation, and cause thine anger toward us to cease.

03:00:25.330 --> 03:00:30.990
Wilt thou be angry with us forever? Wilt thou draw out thine anger to all generations?

03:00:31.550 --> 03:00:36.750
Wilt thou not revive us again, that thy people may rejoice in thee?

03:00:37.610 --> 03:00:44.170
Show us thy mercy, O Lord, and grant us thy salvation. I will hear what God the Lord will

03:00:44.170 --> 03:00:51.410
speak, for he will speak peace unto his people and to his saints, but let them not turn again

03:00:51.410 --> 03:01:00.070
to folly. Surely his salvation is nigh them that fear him, that glory may dwell in our land.

03:01:00.070 --> 03:01:06.070
Mercy and truth are met together, righteousness and peace have kissed each other.

03:01:06.930 --> 03:01:13.750
Truth shall spring out of the earth, and righteousness shall look down from heaven.

03:01:14.670 --> 03:01:20.910
Yea, the Lord shall give that which is good, and our land shall yield her increase.

03:01:22.150 --> 03:01:27.830
Righteousness shall go before him, and shall set us in the way of his steps.

03:01:27.830 --> 03:01:36.470
Psalm 86 Bow down thine ear, O Lord, hear me, for I am poor and needy. Preserve my soul,

03:01:36.810 --> 03:01:44.790
for I am holy. O thou my God, save thy servant that trusteth in thee. Be merciful unto me,

03:01:44.790 --> 03:01:52.990
O Lord, for I cry unto thee daily. Rejoice the soul of thy servant, for unto thee, O Lord,

03:01:52.990 --> 03:02:01.910
do I lift up my soul. For thou, Lord, art good, and ready to forgive, and plenteous in mercy unto

03:02:01.910 --> 03:02:10.870
all them that call upon thee. Give ear, O Lord, unto my prayer, and attend to the voice of my

03:02:10.870 --> 03:02:19.170
supplications. In the day of my trouble I will call upon thee, for thou wilt answer me. Among

03:02:19.170 --> 03:02:25.990
the gods there is none like unto thee, O Lord. Neither are there any works like unto thy works.

03:02:26.850 --> 03:02:32.550
All nations whom thou hast made shall come and worship before thee, O Lord,

03:02:32.870 --> 03:02:41.310
and shall glorify thy name. For thou art great, and doest wondrous things. Thou art God alone.

03:02:42.410 --> 03:02:50.390
Teach me thy way, O Lord. I will walk in thy truth, unite my heart to fear thy name. I will

03:02:50.390 --> 03:02:59.330
praise thee, O Lord my God, with all my heart, and I will glorify thy name for evermore. For

03:02:59.330 --> 03:03:07.330
great is thy mercy toward me, and thou hast delivered my soul from the lowest hell. O God,

03:03:07.330 --> 03:03:14.870
the proud have risen against me, and the assemblies of violent men have sought after my soul,

03:03:15.770 --> 03:03:23.510
and have not set thee before them. But thou, O Lord, art a God full of compassion, and gracious,

03:03:23.950 --> 03:03:33.850
long-suffering, and plenteous in mercy and truth. O turn unto me, and have mercy upon me. Give thy

03:03:33.850 --> 03:03:40.850
strength unto thy servant, and save the son of thine handmaid. Show me a token for good,

03:03:41.190 --> 03:03:48.010
that they which hate me may see it, and be ashamed, because thou, Lord, hast holpened me,

03:03:48.610 --> 03:03:56.890
and comforted me. Psalm 87. His foundation is in the holy mountains. The Lord loveth the gates of

03:03:56.890 --> 03:04:04.470
Zion more than all the dwellings of Jacob. Glorious things are spoken of thee, O city of God.

03:04:05.750 --> 03:04:14.290
I will make mention of Rahab and Babylon to them that know me. Behold Philistia and Tyre with

03:04:14.290 --> 03:04:23.590
Ethiopia. This man was born there, and of Zion it shall be said, This and that man was born in her,

03:04:23.590 --> 03:04:31.330
and the highest himself shall establish her. The Lord shall count, when he writeth up the people,

03:04:31.490 --> 03:04:38.770
that this man was born there. Selah. As well the singers and the players on instruments shall be

03:04:38.770 --> 03:04:48.810
there. All my springs are in thee. Psalm 88. O Lord God of my salvation, I have cried day and

03:04:48.810 --> 03:04:55.270
night before thee. Let my prayer come before thee. Incline thy near unto my cry,

03:04:56.430 --> 03:05:04.210
for my soul is full of troubles, and my life draweth nigh unto the grave. I am counted with them

03:05:04.210 --> 03:05:13.530
that go down into the pit. I am as a man that hath no strength, free among the dead, like the

03:05:13.530 --> 03:05:21.450
that lie in the grave, whom thou remembertst no more. And they are cut off from thy hand.

03:05:22.490 --> 03:05:29.410
Thou hast laid me in the lowest pit. In darkness, in the deeps, thy wrath lieth

03:05:29.410 --> 03:05:39.430
hard upon me, and thou hast afflicted me with all thy waves. Selah. Thou hast put away mine

03:05:39.430 --> 03:05:46.370
acquaintance far from me. Thou hast made me an abomination unto them. I am shut up,

03:05:46.890 --> 03:05:52.130
and I cannot come forth. Mine eye mourneth by reason of affliction.

03:05:52.770 --> 03:05:59.030
Lord, I have called daily upon thee. I have stretched out my hands unto thee.

03:05:59.570 --> 03:06:07.310
Wilt thou show wonders to the dead? Shall the dead arise and praise thee? Selah.

03:06:07.310 --> 03:06:14.350
Shall thy loving kindness be declared in the grave, or thy faithfulness in destruction?

03:06:15.810 --> 03:06:21.970
Shall thy wonders be known in the dark, and thy righteousness in the land of forgetfulness?

03:06:23.050 --> 03:06:30.190
But unto thee have I cried, O Lord, and in the morning shall my prayer prevent thee.

03:06:30.190 --> 03:06:37.630
Lord, why castest thou off my soul? Why hidest thou thy face from me?

03:06:38.130 --> 03:06:45.830
I am afflicted and ready to die from my youth up. While I suffer thy terrors, I am distracted.

03:06:46.230 --> 03:06:51.490
Thy feareth wrath, goeth over me. Thy terrors have cut me off.

03:06:52.870 --> 03:06:57.570
They came round about me daily like water they compassed me about together.

03:06:57.570 --> 03:07:04.410
Lover and friend, hast thou put far from me and mine acquaintance into darkness?

03:07:06.410 --> 03:07:28.170
Psalm 89 I will sing of the mercies of the Lord forever.

03:07:28.470 --> 03:07:32.850
With my mouth will I make known thy faithfulness to all generations.

03:07:32.850 --> 03:07:40.270
For I have said, Mercy shall be built up forever, thy faithfulness shalt thou establish in the very

03:07:40.270 --> 03:07:47.650
heavens. I have made a covenant with my Chosen, I have sworn unto David my servant, thy seed will

03:07:47.650 --> 03:07:54.970
I establish forever, and build up thy throne to all generations, Sila. And the heavens shall praise

03:07:54.970 --> 03:08:01.890
thy wonders, O Lord, thy faithfulness also in the congregation of the saints. For who in the heaven

03:08:01.890 --> 03:08:09.410
can be compared unto the Lord? Who among the sons of the mighty can be likened unto the Lord? God is

03:08:09.410 --> 03:08:15.070
greatly to be feared in the assembly of the saints, and to be had in reverence of all them

03:08:15.070 --> 03:08:23.010
that are about him. O Lord God of hosts, who is a strong Lord like unto thee, or to thy faithfulness

03:08:23.010 --> 03:08:29.730
round about thee? Thou rulest the raging of the sea, when the waves thereof arise thou stillest

03:08:29.730 --> 03:08:37.110
them. Thou hast broken Rahab in pieces, as one that is slain. Thou hast scattered thine enemies

03:08:37.110 --> 03:08:43.850
with thy strong arm. The heavens are thine, the earth also is thine. As for the world and the

03:08:43.850 --> 03:08:49.970
fullness thereof, thou hast founded them. The north and the south thou hast created them,

03:08:50.430 --> 03:08:57.390
Tabor and Hermon shall rejoice in thy name. Thou hast a mighty arm, strong is thy hand,

03:08:57.390 --> 03:09:03.370
and high is thy right hand. Justice and judgment are the habitation of thy throne,

03:09:03.830 --> 03:09:10.110
mercy and truth shall go before thy face. Blessed is the people that know the joyful sound,

03:09:10.550 --> 03:09:16.450
they shall walk, O Lord, in the light of thy countenance. In thy name shall they rejoice all

03:09:16.450 --> 03:09:22.990
the day, and in thy righteousness shall they be exalted. For thou art the glory of their strength,

03:09:22.990 --> 03:09:29.510
and in thy favor our horn shall be exalted. For the Lord is our defense, and the Holy One of

03:09:29.510 --> 03:09:36.870
Israel is our King. Then thou spakest in vision to thy Holy One, and saidst, I have laid help upon

03:09:36.870 --> 03:09:43.550
one that is mighty, I have exalted one chosen out of the people. I have found David my servant,

03:09:43.910 --> 03:09:51.310
with my holy oil have I anointed him, with whom my hand shall be established, mine arm also shall

03:09:51.310 --> 03:09:57.770
strengthen him. The enemy shall not exact upon him, nor the son of wickedness afflict him,

03:09:58.070 --> 03:10:04.770
and I will beat down his foes before his face, and plague them that hate him. But my faithfulness

03:10:04.770 --> 03:10:11.790
and my mercy shall be with him, and in my name shall his horn be exalted. I will set his hand

03:10:11.790 --> 03:10:19.370
also in the sea, and his right hand in the rivers. He shall cry unto me, Thou art my Father, my God,

03:10:19.370 --> 03:10:26.030
and the Rock of my salvation. Also I will make him my firstborn, higher than the kings of the

03:10:26.030 --> 03:10:33.710
earth. My mercy will I keep for him for evermore, and my covenant shall stand fast with him. His

03:10:33.710 --> 03:10:40.270
seed also will I make to endure for ever, and his throne as the days of heaven. If his children

03:10:40.270 --> 03:10:46.910
forsake my law, and walk not in my judgments, if they break my statutes and keep not my commandments,

03:10:46.910 --> 03:10:53.430
then will I visit their transgression with the rod, and their iniquity with stripes. Nevertheless,

03:10:53.690 --> 03:10:59.730
my loving-kindness will I not utterly take from him, nor suffer my faithfulness to fail.

03:11:00.230 --> 03:11:07.010
My covenant will I not break, nor alter the thing that has gone out of my lips. Once have I sworn

03:11:07.010 --> 03:11:14.230
by my holiness that I will not lie unto David. His seed shall endure for ever, and his throne

03:11:14.230 --> 03:11:20.410
as the sun before me. It shall be established for ever as the moon, and as a faithful witness

03:11:20.410 --> 03:11:28.250
in heaven, Sila. But thou hast cast off and abhorred, thou hast been wroth with thine anointed,

03:11:28.850 --> 03:11:35.350
thou hast made void the covenant of thy servant, thou hast profaned his crown by casting it to the

03:11:35.350 --> 03:11:41.930
ground, thou hast broken down all his hedges, thou hast brought his strongholds to ruin,

03:11:41.930 --> 03:11:49.110
all that pass by the way spoil him, he is a reproach to his neighbors, thou hast set up the

03:11:49.110 --> 03:11:55.970
right hand of his adversaries, thou hast made all his enemies to rejoice, thou hast also turned the

03:11:55.970 --> 03:12:02.790
edge of his sword, and hast not made him to stand in the battle, thou hast made his glory to cease,

03:12:03.190 --> 03:12:08.910
and cast his throne down to the ground, the days of his youth hast thou shortened,

03:12:08.910 --> 03:12:16.130
thou hast covered him with shame, Sila. How long, Lord, wilt thou hide thyself for ever?

03:12:16.590 --> 03:12:23.550
Shall thy wrath burn like fire? Remember how short my time is, wherefore hast thou made all men in

03:12:23.550 --> 03:12:30.230
vain? What man is he that liveth, and shall not see death? Shall he deliver his soul from the hand

03:12:30.230 --> 03:12:37.350
of the grave, Sila? Lord, where are thy former loving-kindnesses, which thou swearest unto David

03:12:37.350 --> 03:12:44.510
in thy truth? Remember, Lord, the reproach of thy servants, how I do bear in my bosom the reproach

03:12:44.510 --> 03:12:50.350
of all the mighty people, wherewith thine enemies have reproached, O Lord, wherewith they have

03:12:50.350 --> 03:12:57.570
reproached the footsteps of thine anointed. Blessed be the Lord for evermore. Amen and Amen.

03:12:59.310 --> 03:13:00.210
Psalm 90

03:13:00.730 --> 03:13:06.110
Lord, thou hast been our dwelling-place in all generations, before the mountains were

03:13:06.110 --> 03:13:11.390
brought forth, or ever thou hadst formed the earth and the world, even from everlasting to

03:13:11.390 --> 03:13:19.110
everlasting, thou art God. Thou turnest man to destruction, and sayest, Return ye children of

03:13:19.110 --> 03:13:25.930
men. For a thousand years in thy sight are but as yesterday, when it is past, and as a watch in the

03:13:25.930 --> 03:13:32.820
night. Thou cariest them away as with a flood, they are as asleep, in the morning they are like

03:13:32.820 --> 03:13:39.580
grass which groweth up. In the morning it flourisheth and groweth up, in the evening it is cut down and

03:13:39.580 --> 03:13:47.660
withereth. For we are consumed by thine anger, and by thy wrath are we troubled. Thou hast set our

03:13:47.660 --> 03:13:53.520
iniquities before thee, our secret sins, in the light of thy countenance. For all our days are

03:13:53.520 --> 03:14:00.700
passed away in thy wrath, we spend our years as a tale that is told. The days of our years are three

03:14:00.700 --> 03:14:06.560
score years and ten, and if by reason of strength they be four score years, yet is their strength

03:14:06.560 --> 03:14:13.820
labor and sorrow, for it is soon cut off and we fly away. Who knoweth the power of thine anger?

03:14:14.200 --> 03:14:20.620
Even according to thy fear so is thy wrath. So teach us to number our days, that we may apply

03:14:20.620 --> 03:14:28.020
our hearts unto wisdom. Return, O Lord, how long, and let it repent thee concerning thy servants.

03:14:28.740 --> 03:14:34.960
O satisfy us early with thy mercy, that we may rejoice and be glad all our days.

03:14:35.600 --> 03:14:41.080
Make us glad according to the days wherein thou hast afflicted us, and the years wherein we have

03:14:41.080 --> 03:14:48.360
seen evil. Let thy work appear unto thy servants, and thy glory unto their children. And let the

03:14:48.360 --> 03:14:54.140
beauty of the Lord our God be upon us, and establish thou the work of our hands upon us,

03:14:54.140 --> 03:14:57.580
yea, the work of our hands, establish thou it.

03:14:59.060 --> 03:15:05.620
Psalm 91 He that dwelleth in the secret place of the Most High shall abide under the shadow of

03:15:05.620 --> 03:15:12.860
the Almighty. I will say of the Lord, He is my refuge and my fortress, my God, in Him will I

03:15:12.860 --> 03:15:19.680
trust. Surely He shall deliver thee from the snare of the fowler and from the noisome pestilence.

03:15:19.680 --> 03:15:26.020
He shall cover thee with His feathers, and under His wings shalt thou trust. His truth

03:15:26.020 --> 03:15:31.460
shall be thy shield and buckler. Thou shalt not be afraid for the terror by night,

03:15:31.840 --> 03:15:37.240
nor for the arrow that flyeth by day, nor for the pestilence that walketh in darkness,

03:15:37.640 --> 03:15:43.080
nor for the destruction that wasteth at noonday. A thousand shall fall at thy side,

03:15:43.080 --> 03:15:49.700
and ten thousand at thy right hand, but it shall not come nigh thee. Only with thine eyes

03:15:49.700 --> 03:15:54.840
shalt thou behold and see the reward of the wicked. Because thou hast made the Lord,

03:15:54.940 --> 03:16:01.180
which is thy refuge, even the Most High, thy habitation, there shall no evil befall thee,

03:16:01.420 --> 03:16:07.580
neither shall any plague come nigh thy dwelling. For He shall give His angels charge over thee,

03:16:07.580 --> 03:16:14.020
to keep thee in all thy ways. They shall bear thee up in their hands, lest thou dash thy foot

03:16:14.020 --> 03:16:20.540
against a stone. Thou shalt tread upon the lion and adder, the young lion and the dragon shalt

03:16:20.540 --> 03:16:26.860
thou trample under feet. Because He hath set His love upon me, therefore will I deliver Him,

03:16:27.060 --> 03:16:33.420
I will set Him on high, because He hath known my name. He shall call upon me, and I will answer

03:16:33.420 --> 03:16:39.880
Him, I will be with Him in trouble, I will deliver Him and honor Him. With long life will

03:16:39.880 --> 03:16:45.620
I satisfy Him and show Him my salvation. Psalm 92

03:16:46.240 --> 03:16:52.480
It is a good thing to give thanks unto the Lord and to sing praises unto thy name, O Most High,

03:16:52.840 --> 03:16:57.580
to show forth thy loving-kindness in the morning and thy faithfulness every night,

03:16:57.580 --> 03:17:03.880
upon an instrument of ten strings and upon the psaltery, upon the harp with a solemn sound.

03:17:04.500 --> 03:17:10.420
For thou, Lord, hast made me glad through thy work, I will triumph in the works of thy hands.

03:17:11.020 --> 03:17:17.740
O Lord, how great are thy works, and thy thoughts are very deep. A brutish man knoweth not,

03:17:18.040 --> 03:17:27.440
neither doth a fool understand this. When the wicked spring is the grass, and when all the

03:17:27.440 --> 03:17:34.220
works are destroyed, for ever. But thou, Lord, art Most High for ever more. For lo thine enemies,

03:17:34.340 --> 03:17:40.720
O Lord, for lo thine enemies shall perish, all the workers of iniquity shall be scattered.

03:17:41.300 --> 03:17:47.780
But my horn shalt thou exalt like the horn of an unicorn, I shall be anointed with fresh oil.

03:17:48.560 --> 03:17:55.320
Mine eye also shall see my desire on mine enemies, and mine ears shall hear my desire of the wicked

03:17:55.320 --> 03:18:02.020
that rise up against me. The righteous shall flourish like the palm tree, he shall grow like

03:18:02.020 --> 03:18:08.000
a cedar in Lebanon. Those that be planted in the house of the Lord shall flourish in the courts of

03:18:08.000 --> 03:18:13.980
our God. They shall still bring forth fruit in old age, they shall be fat and flourishing.

03:18:14.480 --> 03:18:20.100
To show that the Lord is upright, he is my rock and there is no unrighteousness in him.

03:18:21.460 --> 03:18:22.700
Psalm 93

03:18:23.540 --> 03:18:29.080
The Lord reigneth, he is clothed with majesty, the Lord is clothed with strength,

03:18:29.440 --> 03:18:35.420
wherewith he hath girded himself. The world also is established, that it cannot be moved.

03:18:36.140 --> 03:18:42.460
Thy throne is established of old, thou art from everlasting. The floods have lifted up, O Lord,

03:18:42.700 --> 03:18:49.620
the floods have lifted up their voice, the floods lift up their waves. The Lord on high is mightier

03:18:49.620 --> 03:18:55.600
than the noise of many waters, yea, than the mighty waves of the sea. Thy testimonies are

03:18:55.600 --> 03:19:00.140
very sure, holiness becomeeth thine house, O Lord, for ever.

03:19:01.720 --> 03:19:02.920
Psalm 94

03:19:03.520 --> 03:19:10.480
O Lord God, to whom vengeance belongeth, O God, to whom vengeance belongeth, show thyself.

03:19:10.980 --> 03:19:15.700
Lift up thyself, thou judge of the earth, render a reward to the proud.

03:19:16.260 --> 03:19:20.420
Lord, how long shall the wicked, how long shall the wicked triumph,

03:19:20.880 --> 03:19:26.800
how long shall they utter and speak hard things, and all the workers of iniquity boast themselves?

03:19:27.480 --> 03:19:33.640
They break in pieces thy people, O Lord, and afflict thine heritage. They slay the

03:19:33.640 --> 03:19:38.020
widow and the stranger, and murder the fatherless, yet they say,

03:19:38.320 --> 03:19:41.980
The Lord shall not see, neither shall the God of Jacob regard it.

03:19:41.980 --> 03:19:47.560
Understand ye, brutish among the people, and ye fools, when will ye be wise?

03:19:48.120 --> 03:19:54.380
He that planted the ear, shall he not hear? He that formed the eye, shall he not see?

03:19:54.880 --> 03:19:58.480
He that chastiseth the he, then, shall not he correct?

03:19:59.000 --> 03:20:02.480
He that teacheth man knowledge, shall not he know?

03:20:03.040 --> 03:20:06.480
The Lord knoweth the thoughts of man, that they are vanity.

03:20:07.040 --> 03:20:12.340
Blessed is the man whom thou chastenest, O Lord, and teachest him out of thy law,

03:20:12.720 --> 03:20:18.520
that thou mayest give him rest from the days of adversity, until the pit be digged for the wicked.

03:20:19.000 --> 03:20:23.960
For the Lord will not cast off his people, neither will he forsake his inheritance.

03:20:24.480 --> 03:20:30.440
But judgment shall return unto righteousness, and all the upright in heart shall follow it.

03:20:30.740 --> 03:20:36.360
Who will rise up for me against the evildoers, or who will stand up for me against the workers

03:20:36.360 --> 03:20:42.560
of iniquity? Unless the Lord had been my help, my soul had almost dwelt in silence.

03:20:43.040 --> 03:20:49.540
When I said, My foot slippeth, thy mercy, O Lord, held me up. In the multitude of my

03:20:49.540 --> 03:20:55.540
thoughts within me, thy comforts delight my soul. Shall the throne of iniquity have fellowship

03:20:55.540 --> 03:21:01.680
with thee, which frameth mischief by a law? They gather themselves together against the soul of the

03:21:01.680 --> 03:21:08.860
righteous, and condemn the innocent blood. But the Lord is my defense, and my God is the rock of my

03:21:08.860 --> 03:21:14.920
refuge. And he shall bring upon them their own iniquity, and shall cut them off in their own

03:21:14.920 --> 03:21:24.400
wickedness. Yea, the Lord our God shall cut them off. Psalm 95. O come, let us sing unto the Lord,

03:21:24.760 --> 03:21:30.640
let us make a joyful noise to the rock of our salvation. Let us come before his presence with

03:21:30.640 --> 03:21:36.600
thanksgiving, and make a joyful noise unto him with psalms. For the Lord is a great God,

03:21:36.700 --> 03:21:43.380
and a great King above all gods. In his hand are the deep places of the earth, the strength of the

03:21:43.380 --> 03:21:51.640
hills is his also. The sea is his, and he made it, and his hands formed the dry land. O come,

03:21:51.720 --> 03:21:58.720
let us worship and bow down, let us kneel before the Lord our Maker. For he is our God, and we are

03:21:58.720 --> 03:22:05.820
people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand. Today, if ye will hear his voice, harden not your

03:22:05.820 --> 03:22:11.800
heart, as in the provocation, and as in the day of temptation in the wilderness, when your fathers

03:22:11.800 --> 03:22:18.640
tempted me, proved me, and saw my work. Forty years long was I grieved with this generation,

03:22:18.900 --> 03:22:24.540
and said, It is a people that do err in their heart, and they have not known my ways,

03:22:24.540 --> 03:22:29.400
unto whom I swear in my wrath that they should not enter into my rest.

03:22:31.300 --> 03:22:35.480
Psalm 96 O sing unto the Lord a new song,

03:22:35.760 --> 03:22:40.560
Sing unto the Lord all the earth, Sing unto the Lord bless his name,

03:22:40.920 --> 03:22:46.400
Show forth his salvation from day to day. Declare his glory among the heathen,

03:22:46.560 --> 03:22:51.960
His wonders among all people. For the Lord is great and greatly to be praised,

03:22:51.960 --> 03:22:57.580
He is to be feared above all gods. For all the gods of the nations are idols,

03:22:57.860 --> 03:23:02.560
But the Lord made the heavens. Honor and majesty are before him,

03:23:02.920 --> 03:23:08.740
Strength and beauty are in his sanctuary. Give unto the Lord, O ye kindreds of the people,

03:23:09.120 --> 03:23:15.160
Give unto the Lord glory and strength. Give unto the Lord the glory due unto his name,

03:23:15.600 --> 03:23:21.780
Bring an offering and come into his courts. O worship the Lord in the beauty of holiness,

03:23:21.960 --> 03:23:27.600
Fear before him all the earth. Say among the heathen that the Lord reigneth,

03:23:27.920 --> 03:23:31.740
The world also shall be established that it shall not be moved,

03:23:32.000 --> 03:23:38.400
He shall judge the people righteously. Let the heavens rejoice and let the earth be glad,

03:23:38.840 --> 03:23:44.960
Let the sea roar in the fullness thereof, Let the field be joyful and all that is therein,

03:23:45.360 --> 03:23:49.060
Then shall all the trees of the wood rejoice before the Lord,

03:23:49.060 --> 03:23:52.660
For he cometh, for he cometh to judge the earth,

03:23:52.960 --> 03:23:57.720
He shall judge the world with righteousness and the people with his truth.

03:24:01.700 --> 03:24:06.160
Psalms 97-105

03:24:22.940 --> 03:24:30.340
The Book of Psalms, King James Version, Psalm 97

03:24:30.700 --> 03:24:34.560
The Lord reigneth, let the earth rejoice.

03:24:35.000 --> 03:24:38.440
Let the multitude of the Isles be glad thereof.

03:24:38.840 --> 03:24:42.840
Clouds and darkness are round about him.

03:24:44.000 --> 03:24:48.060
Righteousness and judgment are the habitation of his throne.

03:24:48.060 --> 03:24:54.180
A fire goeth before him, and burneth up his enemies round about.

03:24:54.800 --> 03:24:57.920
His lightnings enlightened the world.

03:24:58.360 --> 03:25:00.420
The earth saw and trembled.

03:25:00.800 --> 03:25:04.240
The hills melted like wax at the presence of the Lord,

03:25:04.600 --> 03:25:08.300
at the presence of the Lord of the whole earth.

03:25:08.920 --> 03:25:11.100
The heavens declare his righteousness,

03:25:11.580 --> 03:25:14.780
and all the people see his glory.

03:25:14.780 --> 03:25:19.380
Confounded be all they that serve, graven images,

03:25:19.920 --> 03:25:22.300
that boast themselves of idols,

03:25:22.820 --> 03:25:25.180
worship him, all ye gods.

03:25:25.920 --> 03:25:27.800
Zion heard and was glad,

03:25:28.140 --> 03:25:33.600
and the daughters of Judah rejoiced because of thy judgments, O Lord.

03:25:34.160 --> 03:25:37.300
For thou, Lord, art high above all the earth.

03:25:37.780 --> 03:25:41.440
Thou art exalted far above all gods.

03:25:41.440 --> 03:25:45.200
Ye that love the Lord, hate evil,

03:25:45.900 --> 03:25:48.480
he preserveth the souls of his saints.

03:25:48.860 --> 03:25:52.680
He delivereth them out of the hand of the wicked.

03:25:53.420 --> 03:25:55.920
Light is sown for the righteous,

03:25:56.440 --> 03:25:58.960
and gladness for the upright in heart.

03:25:59.700 --> 03:26:02.440
Rejoice in the Lord, ye righteous,

03:26:02.760 --> 03:26:07.020
and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness.

03:26:08.340 --> 03:26:09.940
Psalm 98

03:26:09.940 --> 03:26:13.600
O sing unto the Lord a new song,

03:26:13.900 --> 03:26:16.260
for he hath done marvelous things.

03:26:16.880 --> 03:26:19.600
His right hand and his holy arm

03:26:19.600 --> 03:26:21.920
hath gotten him the victory.

03:26:22.380 --> 03:26:24.800
The Lord hath made known his salvation.

03:26:25.200 --> 03:26:27.720
His righteousness hath he openly showed

03:26:27.720 --> 03:26:29.920
in the sight of the heathen.

03:26:30.120 --> 03:26:32.280
He hath remembered his mercy

03:26:32.280 --> 03:26:35.340
and his truth toward the house of Israel.

03:26:35.900 --> 03:26:38.380
All the ends of the earth have seen

03:26:38.380 --> 03:26:40.600
the salvation of our God.

03:26:40.660 --> 03:26:43.560
Make a joyful noise unto the Lord.

03:26:43.960 --> 03:26:46.260
All the earth make a loud noise,

03:26:46.520 --> 03:26:49.120
and rejoice and sing praise.

03:26:49.840 --> 03:26:51.980
Sing unto the Lord with the harp,

03:26:52.020 --> 03:26:55.560
with the harp and the voice of a psalm,

03:26:56.080 --> 03:26:59.280
with trumpets and sound of cornet.

03:26:59.620 --> 03:27:02.840
Make a joyful noise before the Lord, the King.

03:27:03.300 --> 03:27:06.580
Let the sea roar in the fullness thereof,

03:27:06.580 --> 03:27:10.140
and the world and they that dwell therein.

03:27:10.420 --> 03:27:12.600
Let the floods clap their hands.

03:27:12.720 --> 03:27:16.320
Let the hills be joyful together before the Lord,

03:27:16.460 --> 03:27:20.240
for he cometh to judge the earth with righteousness

03:27:20.240 --> 03:27:25.380
shall he judge the world and the people with equity.

03:27:27.260 --> 03:27:28.700
Psalm 99

03:27:28.700 --> 03:27:32.520
The Lord reigneth, let the people tremble.

03:27:32.740 --> 03:27:34.700
He sitteth between the sherabims.

03:27:34.700 --> 03:27:37.300
Let the earth be moved.

03:27:37.880 --> 03:27:40.080
The Lord is great in Zion,

03:27:40.420 --> 03:27:43.140
and he is high above all the people.

03:27:43.860 --> 03:27:47.460
Let them praise thy great and terrible name,

03:27:47.820 --> 03:27:49.600
for it is holy.

03:27:50.180 --> 03:27:52.920
The King's strength also loveth judgment.

03:27:53.500 --> 03:27:56.400
Thou dost establish equity.

03:27:56.820 --> 03:28:00.920
Thou executest judgment and righteousness in Jacob.

03:28:01.660 --> 03:28:04.200
Exult ye the Lord our God,

03:28:04.200 --> 03:28:09.280
and worship at his footstool, for he is holy.

03:28:09.820 --> 03:28:12.740
Moses and Aaron among his priests,

03:28:13.220 --> 03:28:17.180
and Samuel among them that called upon his name.

03:28:17.560 --> 03:28:20.580
They called upon the Lord, and he answered them.

03:28:21.040 --> 03:28:24.300
He spake unto them in the cloudy pillar.

03:28:24.660 --> 03:28:29.120
They kept his testimonies and the ordinance that he gave them.

03:28:29.560 --> 03:28:32.640
Thou answerest them, O Lord our God.

03:28:32.640 --> 03:28:36.100
Thou wast a God that forgavest them,

03:28:36.540 --> 03:28:40.840
though thou tookest vengeance of their inventions.

03:28:41.380 --> 03:28:45.560
Exult the Lord our God, and worship at his holy hill,

03:28:45.780 --> 03:28:48.960
for the Lord our God is holy.

03:28:49.920 --> 03:28:51.440
Psalm 100

03:28:51.440 --> 03:28:56.200
Make a joyful noise unto the Lord all ye lands.

03:28:56.700 --> 03:28:58.420
Serve the Lord with gladness.

03:28:58.420 --> 03:29:02.200
Come before his presence with singing.

03:29:02.820 --> 03:29:06.020
Know ye that the Lord, he is God.

03:29:06.320 --> 03:29:11.060
It is he that hath made us, and not we ourselves.

03:29:11.520 --> 03:29:15.820
We are his people, and the sheep of his pasture.

03:29:16.700 --> 03:29:19.800
Enter into his gates with thanksgiving,

03:29:20.240 --> 03:29:23.060
and into his courts with praise.

03:29:23.440 --> 03:29:27.120
Be thankful unto him, and bless his name,

03:29:27.120 --> 03:29:29.020
for the Lord is good.

03:29:29.240 --> 03:29:33.080
His mercy is everlasting, and his truth

03:29:33.080 --> 03:29:36.560
endureth to all generations.

03:29:37.480 --> 03:29:39.100
Psalm 101

03:29:40.100 --> 03:29:43.760
I will sing of mercy and judgment unto thee, O Lord.

03:29:44.100 --> 03:29:45.380
Will I sing?

03:29:45.820 --> 03:29:50.120
I will behave myself wisely in a perfect way.

03:29:50.520 --> 03:29:53.900
O, when wilt thou come unto me?

03:29:53.900 --> 03:29:58.380
I will walk within my house with a perfect heart.

03:29:58.960 --> 03:30:01.980
I will set no wicked thing before mine eyes.

03:30:02.380 --> 03:30:04.840
I hate the work of them that turn aside.

03:30:05.280 --> 03:30:07.480
It shall not cleave to me.

03:30:08.420 --> 03:30:10.820
A foward heart shall depart from me.

03:30:10.940 --> 03:30:13.740
I will not know a wicked person.

03:30:14.300 --> 03:30:17.260
Who so privily slandereth his neighbor?

03:30:17.740 --> 03:30:18.980
Him will I cut off.

03:30:19.280 --> 03:30:23.180
Him that hath an high look and a proud heart will not.

03:30:23.180 --> 03:30:24.360
I suffer.

03:30:24.960 --> 03:30:28.740
Mine eyes shall be upon the faithful of the land,

03:30:29.120 --> 03:30:31.140
that they may dwell with me.

03:30:31.380 --> 03:30:34.240
He that walketh in a perfect way,

03:30:34.540 --> 03:30:36.260
he shall serve me.

03:30:36.680 --> 03:30:40.720
He that worketh deceit shall not dwell within my house.

03:30:41.140 --> 03:30:45.060
He that telleth lies shall not tarry in my sight.

03:30:45.720 --> 03:30:50.300
I will early destroy all the wicked of the land,

03:30:50.300 --> 03:30:56.000
that I may cut off all wicked doers from the city of the Lord.

03:30:57.100 --> 03:30:58.460
Psalm 102.

03:31:00.160 --> 03:31:04.240
Hear my prayer, O Lord, and let my cry come unto thee.

03:31:04.600 --> 03:31:09.060
Hide not thy face from me in the day when I am in trouble.

03:31:09.520 --> 03:31:13.280
Incline thine ear unto me in the day when I call.

03:31:13.480 --> 03:31:18.500
Answer me speedily, for my days are consumed like smoke.

03:31:18.500 --> 03:31:22.040
My bones are burned as in hearth.

03:31:22.260 --> 03:31:25.720
My heart is smitten and withered like grass,

03:31:25.940 --> 03:31:29.340
so that I forget to eat my bread.

03:31:29.940 --> 03:31:34.960
By reason of the voice of my groaning, my bones cleave to my skin.

03:31:35.400 --> 03:31:38.680
I am like a pelican of the wilderness.

03:31:38.920 --> 03:31:41.780
I am like an owl of the desert.

03:31:42.140 --> 03:31:46.780
I watch and am as a sparrow alone upon the housetop.

03:31:46.780 --> 03:31:50.380
Mine enemies reproach me all the day,

03:31:50.760 --> 03:31:55.840
and they that are mad against me are sworn against me.

03:31:56.180 --> 03:32:01.600
For I have eaten ashes like bread and mingled my drink with weeping,

03:32:01.980 --> 03:32:05.000
because of thine indignation and thy wrath.

03:32:05.280 --> 03:32:09.880
For thou hast lifted me up and cast me down.

03:32:10.440 --> 03:32:13.460
My days are like a shadow that declineeth,

03:32:13.460 --> 03:32:16.440
and I am withered like grass.

03:32:16.760 --> 03:32:19.820
But thou, O Lord, shall endure forever,

03:32:20.180 --> 03:32:23.360
and thy remembrance unto all generations.

03:32:24.420 --> 03:32:28.440
Thou shalt arise and have mercy upon Zion,

03:32:28.920 --> 03:32:33.920
for the time to favor her, yea, the set time is come.

03:32:34.580 --> 03:32:37.600
For thy servants take pleasure in her stones,

03:32:38.000 --> 03:32:40.720
and favor the dust thereof.

03:32:40.720 --> 03:32:44.900
So the heathen shall fear the name of the Lord,

03:32:45.080 --> 03:32:48.560
and all the kings of the earth thy glory.

03:32:49.180 --> 03:32:53.740
When the Lord shall build up Zion, he shall appear in his glory.

03:32:54.040 --> 03:32:59.360
He will regard the prayer of the destitute, and not despise their prayer.

03:33:00.080 --> 03:33:03.720
This shall be written for the generation to come,

03:33:04.080 --> 03:33:08.560
and the people which shall be created shall praise the Lord.

03:33:08.560 --> 03:33:12.880
For he hath looked down from the height of his sanctuary,

03:33:13.420 --> 03:33:16.880
from heaven did the Lord behold the earth.

03:33:17.360 --> 03:33:19.280
To hear the groaning of the prisoner,

03:33:19.600 --> 03:33:22.360
to loose those that are appointed to death,

03:33:22.520 --> 03:33:26.080
to declare the name of the Lord in Zion,

03:33:26.340 --> 03:33:28.740
and his praise in Jerusalem.

03:33:29.540 --> 03:33:32.340
When the people are gathered together,

03:33:32.540 --> 03:33:35.840
and the kingdoms to serve the Lord.

03:33:35.840 --> 03:33:39.280
He weakened my strength in the way.

03:33:39.580 --> 03:33:41.960
He shortened my days.

03:33:42.320 --> 03:33:48.280
I said, O my God, take me not away in the midst of my days.

03:33:48.760 --> 03:33:52.020
Thy years are throughout all generations.

03:33:52.660 --> 03:33:56.880
Of old hast thou laid the foundation of the earth,

03:33:57.160 --> 03:33:59.960
and the heavens are the work of thy hands.

03:34:00.420 --> 03:34:04.100
They shall perish, but thou shalt endure.

03:34:04.100 --> 03:34:10.240
Yea, all of them shall wax old like a garment as a vesture,

03:34:10.460 --> 03:34:14.460
shalt thou change them, and they shall be changed.

03:34:15.120 --> 03:34:19.740
But thou art the same, and thy years shall have no end.

03:34:20.440 --> 03:34:23.520
The children of thy servants shall continue,

03:34:23.600 --> 03:34:27.840
and their seed shall be established before thee.

03:34:28.780 --> 03:34:30.440
Psalm 103.

03:34:31.440 --> 03:34:38.380
Bless the Lord, O my soul, and all that is within me.

03:34:38.780 --> 03:34:41.160
Bless his holy name.

03:34:41.720 --> 03:34:47.020
Bless the Lord, O my soul, and forget not all his benefits.

03:34:47.860 --> 03:34:50.780
Who forgiveth all thine iniquities?

03:34:51.100 --> 03:34:53.040
Who healeth all thy diseases?

03:34:53.780 --> 03:34:56.780
Who redeemeth thy life from destruction?

03:34:56.780 --> 03:35:03.680
Who crowneth thee with loving kindness and tender mercies?

03:35:03.940 --> 03:35:07.340
Who satisfieth thy mouth with good things,

03:35:07.840 --> 03:35:12.780
so that thy youth is renewed like the eagles?

03:35:12.920 --> 03:35:17.300
In the heavens and his kingdom ruleth over all.

03:35:17.920 --> 03:35:22.580
Bless the Lord, ye his angels, that excel in strength.

03:35:22.580 --> 03:35:27.780
That do, the Lord executeth righteousness and judgment

03:35:27.780 --> 03:35:30.240
for all that are oppressed.

03:35:30.840 --> 03:35:33.540
He made known his ways unto Moses,

03:35:33.840 --> 03:35:36.740
his acts unto the children of Israel.

03:35:37.320 --> 03:35:39.960
The Lord is merciful and gracious,

03:35:40.560 --> 03:35:43.240
slow to anger and plenteous in mercy.

03:35:43.740 --> 03:35:49.320
He will not always chide, neither will he keep his anger forever.

03:35:49.320 --> 03:35:53.280
He hath not dealt with us after our sins,

03:35:53.680 --> 03:35:56.400
nor rewarded us according to our iniquities.

03:35:57.460 --> 03:36:00.780
For as the heaven is high above the earth,

03:36:00.980 --> 03:36:05.820
so great is his mercy toward them that fear him.

03:36:06.780 --> 03:36:09.940
As far as the east is from the west,

03:36:10.300 --> 03:36:15.300
so far hath he removed our transgressions from us.

03:36:15.300 --> 03:36:19.320
Like as a father pityeth his children,

03:36:19.640 --> 03:36:22.760
so the Lord pityeth them that fear him.

03:36:23.260 --> 03:36:28.760
For he knoweth our frame, he remembereth that we are dust.

03:36:29.500 --> 03:36:32.620
As for man, his days are as grass,

03:36:32.740 --> 03:36:36.140
as a flower of the field, so he flourisheth.

03:36:36.460 --> 03:36:40.400
For the wind passeth over it, and it is gone,

03:36:40.780 --> 03:36:43.940
and the place thereof shall know it no more.

03:36:43.940 --> 03:36:49.320
But the mercy of the Lord is from everlasting to everlasting

03:36:49.580 --> 03:36:52.300
upon them that fear him,

03:36:52.600 --> 03:36:56.060
and his righteousness unto children's children.

03:36:56.600 --> 03:36:59.080
To such as keep his covenant,

03:36:59.500 --> 03:37:02.880
and to those that remember his commandments to do them,

03:37:03.280 --> 03:37:07.020
the Lord hath prepared his throne in the heavens,

03:37:07.360 --> 03:37:10.360
and his kingdom ruleth over all.

03:37:10.360 --> 03:37:13.540
Bless the Lord, ye his angels,

03:37:13.900 --> 03:37:15.620
that excel in strength,

03:37:16.160 --> 03:37:17.940
that do his commandments,

03:37:18.340 --> 03:37:21.100
hearkening unto the voice of his word.

03:37:21.600 --> 03:37:25.180
Bless ye the Lord, all ye his hosts,

03:37:25.520 --> 03:37:28.720
ye ministers of his, that do his pleasure.

03:37:29.140 --> 03:37:32.080
Bless the Lord, all his works,

03:37:32.180 --> 03:37:35.020
in all places of his dominion.

03:37:35.180 --> 03:37:39.760
Bless the Lord, O my soul.

03:37:39.760 --> 03:37:42.560
Psalm 104.

03:37:43.700 --> 03:37:46.200
Bless the Lord, O my soul.

03:37:47.000 --> 03:37:50.200
O Lord my God, thou art very great,

03:37:50.680 --> 03:37:54.400
thou art clothed with honor and majesty,

03:37:55.000 --> 03:37:57.380
who coverest thyself with light,

03:37:57.840 --> 03:37:59.300
as with a garment.

03:38:00.120 --> 03:38:03.280
Who stretcheth out the heavens like a curtain,

03:38:03.760 --> 03:38:07.740
who layeth the beams of his chambers in the waters,

03:38:07.740 --> 03:38:11.460
who maketh the clouds his chariot,

03:38:11.840 --> 03:38:14.620
who walketh upon the wings of the wind,

03:38:15.040 --> 03:38:17.980
who maketh his angels' spirits,

03:38:18.160 --> 03:38:21.380
his ministers, a flaming fire,

03:38:22.380 --> 03:38:25.180
who laid the foundations of the earth,

03:38:25.420 --> 03:38:28.460
that it should not be removed forever.

03:38:28.980 --> 03:38:31.920
Thou coverest it with the deep,

03:38:32.500 --> 03:38:33.820
as with a garment.

03:38:34.040 --> 03:38:36.960
The waters stood above the mountains,

03:38:36.960 --> 03:38:39.280
at thy rebuke they fled,

03:38:39.320 --> 03:38:43.240
at the voice of thy thunder they hasted away.

03:38:43.740 --> 03:38:46.200
They go up by the mountains,

03:38:46.320 --> 03:38:48.560
they go down by the valleys,

03:38:49.400 --> 03:38:52.180
unto the place which thou hast founded for them.

03:38:52.760 --> 03:38:56.240
Thou hast set abound that they may not pass over,

03:38:56.920 --> 03:39:00.160
that they turn not again to cover the earth.

03:39:01.120 --> 03:39:04.180
He sendeth the springs into the valleys,

03:39:04.180 --> 03:39:06.580
which run among the hills.

03:39:06.860 --> 03:39:10.260
They give drink to every beast of the field,

03:39:10.580 --> 03:39:12.920
the wild asses quench their thirst.

03:39:13.620 --> 03:39:17.420
By them shall the fowls of the heaven have their habitation,

03:39:17.580 --> 03:39:19.760
which sing among the branches.

03:39:20.320 --> 03:39:22.600
He watereth the hills from his chambers.

03:39:22.940 --> 03:39:27.860
The earth is satisfied with the fruit of thy works.

03:39:28.220 --> 03:39:30.980
He causeth the grass to grow for the cattle,

03:39:30.980 --> 03:39:33.860
and herb for the service of man,

03:39:33.960 --> 03:39:37.840
that he may bring forth food out of the earth,

03:39:38.280 --> 03:39:41.420
and wine that maketh glad the heart of man,

03:39:42.180 --> 03:39:45.760
and oil to make his face to shine,

03:39:46.280 --> 03:39:49.020
and bread which strengtheneth man's heart.

03:39:49.540 --> 03:39:52.340
The trees of the Lord are full of sap,

03:39:52.720 --> 03:39:56.240
the cedars of Lebanon, which he hath planted,

03:39:56.620 --> 03:39:58.540
where the birds make their nest,

03:39:58.540 --> 03:40:03.960
as for the stork the fir trees are her house.

03:40:04.560 --> 03:40:07.940
The high hills are a refuge for the wild goats,

03:40:08.360 --> 03:40:10.700
and the rocks for the conies.

03:40:11.400 --> 03:40:13.820
He appointed the moon for seasons,

03:40:14.080 --> 03:40:16.740
the sun knoweth his going down.

03:40:17.020 --> 03:40:20.580
Thou makest darkness, and it is night.

03:40:21.200 --> 03:40:25.700
Wherein all the beasts of the forest do creep forth,

03:40:25.700 --> 03:40:29.100
the young lions roar after their prey,

03:40:29.760 --> 03:40:31.740
and seek their meat from God.

03:40:32.180 --> 03:40:35.440
The sun ariseth, they gather themselves together,

03:40:35.960 --> 03:40:38.560
and lay them down in their dens.

03:40:39.160 --> 03:40:41.740
Man goeth forth unto his work,

03:40:42.140 --> 03:40:45.500
and to his labor until the evening.

03:40:45.840 --> 03:40:49.180
O Lord, how manifold are thy works!

03:40:49.840 --> 03:40:53.140
In wisdom hast thou made them all.

03:40:53.140 --> 03:40:56.480
The earth is full of thy riches,

03:40:57.120 --> 03:41:00.620
so is this great and wide sea,

03:41:01.100 --> 03:41:04.140
wherein are things creeping innumerable,

03:41:04.820 --> 03:41:07.060
both small and great beasts.

03:41:07.460 --> 03:41:11.140
There go the ships, there is that Leviathan,

03:41:12.080 --> 03:41:14.960
whom thou hast made to play therein.

03:41:15.440 --> 03:41:17.460
These wait all upon thee,

03:41:17.800 --> 03:41:21.480
that thou mayest give them their meat in due season,

03:41:21.480 --> 03:41:24.620
that thou givest them, they gather.

03:41:25.080 --> 03:41:28.820
Thou openest thy hand, they are filled with good.

03:41:29.640 --> 03:41:31.880
Thou hidest thy face, they are troubled.

03:41:32.240 --> 03:41:34.780
Thou takest away their breath, they die,

03:41:35.380 --> 03:41:37.600
and return to their dust.

03:41:38.440 --> 03:41:42.460
Thou sendest forth thy spirit, they are created,

03:41:42.980 --> 03:41:46.340
and thou renewest the face of the earth.

03:41:47.020 --> 03:41:50.600
The glory of the Lord shall endure forever.

03:41:50.600 --> 03:41:54.140
The Lord shall rejoice in his works.

03:41:54.740 --> 03:41:56.780
He looketh on the earth, and it trembleth.

03:41:57.500 --> 03:42:00.440
He toucheth the hills, and they smoke.

03:42:01.040 --> 03:42:04.940
I will sing unto the Lord as long as I live.

03:42:05.240 --> 03:42:09.300
I will sing praise to my God while I have my being.

03:42:09.720 --> 03:42:12.720
My meditation of him shall be sweet.

03:42:13.160 --> 03:42:15.600
I will be glad in the Lord.

03:42:16.180 --> 03:42:19.640
Let the sinners be consumed out of the earth,

03:42:19.640 --> 03:42:22.740
and let the wicked be no more.

03:42:22.900 --> 03:42:26.600
Bless thou the Lord, O my soul.

03:42:26.820 --> 03:42:29.560
Praise ye the Lord.

03:42:30.920 --> 03:42:32.440
Psalm 105.

03:42:33.240 --> 03:42:36.020
O give thanks unto the Lord.

03:42:36.540 --> 03:42:38.120
Call upon his name.

03:42:38.480 --> 03:42:41.480
Make known his deeds among the people.

03:42:42.100 --> 03:42:45.220
Sing unto him, sing psalms unto him.

03:42:45.520 --> 03:42:48.780
Talk ye of all his wondrous works.

03:42:48.780 --> 03:42:52.140
Glory ye in his holy name.

03:42:52.720 --> 03:42:56.780
Let the heart of them rejoice that seek the Lord.

03:42:57.360 --> 03:42:59.060
Seek the Lord and his strength.

03:42:59.380 --> 03:43:01.520
Seek his face evermore.

03:43:01.920 --> 03:43:05.300
Remember his marvelous works that he hath done,

03:43:05.580 --> 03:43:09.200
his wonders, and the judgments of his mouth.

03:43:10.000 --> 03:43:13.260
O ye seed of Abraham, his servant,

03:43:13.720 --> 03:43:15.660
ye children of Jacob his chosen.

03:43:15.660 --> 03:43:18.660
He is the Lord, our God.

03:43:19.080 --> 03:43:21.660
His judgments are in all the earth.

03:43:22.140 --> 03:43:24.660
He hath remembered his covenant forever,

03:43:25.280 --> 03:43:29.400
the word which he commanded to a thousand generations,

03:43:29.820 --> 03:43:32.820
which covenant he made with Abraham,

03:43:33.060 --> 03:43:35.300
and his oath unto Isaac,

03:43:36.100 --> 03:43:39.720
and confirmed the same unto Jacob for a law,

03:43:40.120 --> 03:43:43.460
and to Israel for an everlasting covenant,

03:43:43.460 --> 03:43:48.120
saying, unto thee will I give the land of Canaan

03:43:48.120 --> 03:43:50.600
the lot of your inheritance.

03:43:51.280 --> 03:43:54.720
When they were but a few men in number,

03:43:54.940 --> 03:43:58.380
yea, very few, and strangers in it,

03:43:58.640 --> 03:44:01.760
when they went from one nation to another,

03:44:02.000 --> 03:44:04.860
from one kingdom to another people,

03:44:05.160 --> 03:44:07.780
he suffered no man to do them wrong,

03:44:08.000 --> 03:44:11.960
yea, he reproved kings for their sakes,

03:44:11.960 --> 03:44:16.120
saying, touch not mine anointed,

03:44:16.420 --> 03:44:19.300
and do my prophets no harm.

03:44:19.740 --> 03:44:23.320
Moreover, he called for a famine upon the land.

03:44:23.760 --> 03:44:26.540
He break the whole staff of bread.

03:44:27.320 --> 03:44:31.220
He sent a man before them, even Joseph,

03:44:31.740 --> 03:44:34.000
who was sold for a servant,

03:44:34.540 --> 03:44:36.720
whose feet they hurt with fetters.

03:44:37.000 --> 03:44:40.720
He was laid in iron until the time

03:44:40.720 --> 03:44:43.020
that his word came,

03:44:43.360 --> 03:44:46.420
the word of the Lord tried him.

03:44:46.980 --> 03:44:49.180
The king sent and loosed him,

03:44:49.540 --> 03:44:51.680
even the ruler of the people,

03:44:52.280 --> 03:44:54.160
and let him go free.

03:44:54.780 --> 03:44:57.320
He made him lord of his house,

03:44:57.660 --> 03:45:00.240
and ruler of all his substance,

03:45:00.920 --> 03:45:03.680
to bind his princes at his pleasure,

03:45:04.000 --> 03:45:06.420
and teach his senators wisdom.

03:45:06.420 --> 03:45:10.720
Israel also came into Egypt,

03:45:11.320 --> 03:45:15.080
and Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham.

03:45:15.700 --> 03:45:18.600
And he increased his people greatly,

03:45:19.100 --> 03:45:22.220
and made them stronger than their enemies.

03:45:22.780 --> 03:45:25.460
He turned their heart to hate his people,

03:45:25.700 --> 03:45:28.600
to deal subtly with his servants.

03:45:29.180 --> 03:45:30.920
He sent Moses his servant,

03:45:31.380 --> 03:45:33.420
and Aaron whom he had chosen.

03:45:33.420 --> 03:45:36.600
They showed his signs among them,

03:45:36.940 --> 03:45:39.280
and wonders in the land of Ham.

03:45:39.920 --> 03:45:42.420
He sent darkness and made it dark,

03:45:42.760 --> 03:45:45.720
and they rebelled not against his word.

03:45:46.320 --> 03:45:48.840
He turned their waters into blood,

03:45:49.300 --> 03:45:50.480
and slew their fish.

03:45:50.920 --> 03:45:54.140
Their land brought forth frogs in abundance,

03:45:54.520 --> 03:45:56.740
and the chambers of their kings.

03:45:57.500 --> 03:46:00.060
He spake, and there came divers,

03:46:00.060 --> 03:46:01.420
and there came all sorts of flies,

03:46:01.800 --> 03:46:05.240
and lice in all their coasts.

03:46:05.460 --> 03:46:07.200
He gave them hail for rain,

03:46:07.720 --> 03:46:09.680
and flaming fire in their land.

03:46:10.080 --> 03:46:12.380
He smoked their vines also,

03:46:12.660 --> 03:46:13.960
and their fig trees,

03:46:14.260 --> 03:46:17.120
and break the trees of their coast.

03:46:17.620 --> 03:46:19.740
He spake, and the locusts came,

03:46:20.060 --> 03:46:23.920
and caterpillars, and that without number,

03:46:23.920 --> 03:46:28.060
and did eat up all the herbs in their land,

03:46:28.480 --> 03:46:30.520
and devoured the fruit of their ground.

03:46:30.860 --> 03:46:34.480
He smoked also all the first born in their land,

03:46:34.980 --> 03:46:37.740
the chief of all their strength.

03:46:38.260 --> 03:46:40.300
He brought them forth also

03:46:40.300 --> 03:46:42.620
with silver and gold,

03:46:42.900 --> 03:46:45.200
and there was not one feeble person

03:46:45.720 --> 03:46:47.280
among their tribes.

03:46:48.060 --> 03:46:50.240
Egypt was glad when they departed,

03:46:50.240 --> 03:46:53.860
for the fear of them fell upon them.

03:46:54.320 --> 03:46:56.840
He spread a cloud for a covering,

03:46:57.360 --> 03:46:59.800
and fire to give light in the night.

03:47:00.420 --> 03:47:03.260
The people asked, and he brought quails,

03:47:03.700 --> 03:47:05.720
and satisfied them with

03:47:05.720 --> 03:47:07.680
the bread of heaven.

03:47:08.260 --> 03:47:12.120
He opened the rock, and the waters gushed out.

03:47:12.400 --> 03:47:14.520
They ran in the dry places

03:47:14.820 --> 03:47:16.340
like a river.

03:47:16.340 --> 03:47:19.540
For he remembered his holy promise,

03:47:20.400 --> 03:47:22.800
and Abraham his servant.

03:47:23.780 --> 03:47:25.900
And he brought forth his people

03:47:25.900 --> 03:47:28.340
with joy, and his chosen

03:47:28.340 --> 03:47:31.480
with gladness, and gave them

03:47:31.480 --> 03:47:34.020
the lands of the heathen,

03:47:34.120 --> 03:47:37.000
and they inherited the labor of the people,

03:47:37.640 --> 03:47:40.200
that they might observe his statutes,

03:47:40.440 --> 03:47:42.420
and keep his laws.

03:47:42.420 --> 03:47:47.280
Praise ye the Lord!

03:47:48.240 --> 03:47:53.520
End of Psalms 97-105

03:47:55.520 --> 03:47:59.280
Psalm 106-115.

03:48:12.230 --> 03:48:14.080
The Book of Psalms.

03:48:14.320 --> 03:48:16.040
King James Version.

03:48:16.400 --> 03:48:18.900
Psalm 106.

03:48:19.480 --> 03:48:20.780
Praise ye the LORD!

03:48:21.100 --> 03:48:23.760
O give thanks unto the LORD!

03:48:23.760 --> 03:48:28.420
For he is good, for his mercy endureth forever.

03:48:29.660 --> 03:48:32.360
Who can utter the mighty acts of the LORD?

03:48:33.120 --> 03:48:35.700
Who can show forth all his praise?

03:48:36.720 --> 03:48:39.040
Blessed are they that keep judgment,

03:48:39.780 --> 03:48:42.880
And he that doeth righteousness at all times.

03:48:43.800 --> 03:48:49.240
Remember me, O LORD, with the favor that thou bearest unto thy people.

03:48:49.740 --> 03:48:52.200
O visit me with thy salvation,

03:48:52.200 --> 03:48:56.120
That I may see the good of thy chosen,

03:48:56.680 --> 03:49:00.180
That I may rejoice in the gladness of thy nation,

03:49:00.600 --> 03:49:03.440
That I may glory with thine inheritance.

03:49:04.560 --> 03:49:06.620
We have sinned with our fathers,

03:49:06.980 --> 03:49:08.820
We have committed iniquity,

03:49:09.380 --> 03:49:11.200
We have done wickedly.

03:49:11.980 --> 03:49:15.240
Our fathers understood not thy wonders in Egypt,

03:49:15.620 --> 03:49:18.980
They remembered not the multitude of thy mercies,

03:49:18.980 --> 03:49:23.060
But provoked him at the sea, even at the Red Sea.

03:49:23.920 --> 03:49:28.060
Nevertheless, he saved them for his name's sake,

03:49:28.680 --> 03:49:31.960
That he might make his mighty power to be known.

03:49:33.060 --> 03:49:37.400
He rebuked the Red Sea also, and it was dried up,

03:49:37.640 --> 03:49:41.760
So he led them through the depths, as through the wilderness.

03:49:42.340 --> 03:49:46.600
And he saved them from the hand of him that hated them,

03:49:46.600 --> 03:49:50.520
And redeemed them from the hand of the enemy,

03:49:52.020 --> 03:49:54.280
And the waters covered their enemies.

03:49:55.960 --> 03:49:58.260
There was not one of them left,

03:49:59.000 --> 03:50:03.140
Then believed they his words, they sang his praise,

03:50:04.200 --> 03:50:06.120
They soon forgot his works,

03:50:06.720 --> 03:50:09.340
They waited not for his counsel,

03:50:09.700 --> 03:50:12.240
But lusted exceedingly in the wilderness,

03:50:12.680 --> 03:50:14.640
And tempted God in the desert,

03:50:15.340 --> 03:50:17.360
And he gave them their request,

03:50:18.180 --> 03:50:20.900
But sent leanness into their soul,

03:50:21.480 --> 03:50:24.040
They envied Moses also in the camp,

03:50:24.380 --> 03:50:26.540
And Aaron the saint of the Lord.

03:50:27.580 --> 03:50:30.820
The earth opened, and swallowed up Dathan,

03:50:31.180 --> 03:50:33.220
And covered the company of Abiram,

03:50:33.780 --> 03:50:36.140
And a fire was kindled in their company,

03:50:36.660 --> 03:50:39.360
The flame burned up the wicked.

03:50:40.440 --> 03:50:42.360
They made a calf in Horeb,

03:50:42.360 --> 03:50:44.920
And worshipped the molten image,

03:50:45.720 --> 03:50:47.560
Thus they changed their glory,

03:50:47.960 --> 03:50:51.240
Into the similitude of an ox that eateth grass,

03:50:51.740 --> 03:50:53.800
They forgot God their Saviour,

03:50:54.620 --> 03:50:57.200
Which had done great things in Egypt,

03:50:57.580 --> 03:51:00.220
Wondrous works in the land of Ham,

03:51:00.580 --> 03:51:03.260
And terrible things by the Red Sea.

03:51:04.140 --> 03:51:07.100
Therefore he said that he would destroy them,

03:51:07.580 --> 03:51:11.420
Had not Moses his chosen stood before him in the breach,

03:51:11.420 --> 03:51:15.320
To turn away his wrath, lest he should destroy them.

03:51:15.980 --> 03:51:19.100
Yea, they despised the pleasant land,

03:51:19.340 --> 03:51:21.140
They believed not his word,

03:51:21.760 --> 03:51:23.460
But murmured in their tents,

03:51:23.560 --> 03:51:26.420
And hearkened not unto the voice of the Lord.

03:51:27.060 --> 03:51:29.320
Therefore he lifted up his hand against them,

03:51:29.540 --> 03:51:31.600
To overthrow them in the wilderness,

03:51:31.980 --> 03:51:36.180
To overthrow their seed also among the nations,

03:51:36.280 --> 03:51:38.220
And to scatter them in the lands.

03:51:39.000 --> 03:51:42.320
They joined themselves also unto Balpior,

03:51:42.940 --> 03:51:45.160
And ate the sacrifices of the dead,

03:51:45.520 --> 03:51:49.140
Thus they provoked him to anger with their inventions,

03:51:49.860 --> 03:51:52.540
And the plague break in upon them,

03:51:52.900 --> 03:51:56.220
Then stood up Phineas, and executed judgment,

03:51:56.760 --> 03:51:58.420
And so the plague was stayed,

03:51:58.840 --> 03:52:01.480
And that was counted unto him for righteousness,

03:52:01.760 --> 03:52:04.300
Unto all generations for evermore.

03:52:05.220 --> 03:52:09.280
They angered him also at the waters of Strife,

03:52:10.000 --> 03:52:12.750
So that it went ill with Moses for their sakes,

03:52:13.520 --> 03:52:16.100
Because they provoked his spirit,

03:52:16.460 --> 03:52:19.980
So that he spake unadvisedly with his lips.

03:52:21.040 --> 03:52:25.320
They did not destroy the nations concerning whom the Lord commanded them,

03:52:25.600 --> 03:52:28.020
But were mingled among the heathen,

03:52:28.200 --> 03:52:29.600
And learned their works,

03:52:29.980 --> 03:52:31.860
And they served their idols,

03:52:32.100 --> 03:52:33.780
Which were a snare unto them,

03:52:33.780 --> 03:52:38.360
Yea, they sacrificed their sons and their daughters unto devils,

03:52:38.620 --> 03:52:40.180
And shed innocent blood,

03:52:40.480 --> 03:52:43.460
Even the blood of their sons and of their daughters,

03:52:43.760 --> 03:52:47.020
Whom they sacrificed unto the idols of Canaan,

03:52:48.100 --> 03:52:50.240
And the land was polluted with blood,

03:52:51.180 --> 03:52:54.440
Thus were they defiled with their own works,

03:52:55.280 --> 03:52:58.600
And went a-whoring with their own inventions.

03:52:59.560 --> 03:53:03.320
Therefore was the wrath of the Lord kindled against his people,

03:53:03.320 --> 03:53:06.440
In so much that he abhorred his own inheritance,

03:53:07.340 --> 03:53:10.640
And he gave them into the hand of the heathen,

03:53:10.980 --> 03:53:14.480
And they that hated them ruled over them,

03:53:14.860 --> 03:53:16.960
Their enemies also oppressed them,

03:53:17.500 --> 03:53:20.920
And they were brought into subjection under their hand.

03:53:21.840 --> 03:53:24.300
Many times did he deliver them,

03:53:24.440 --> 03:53:26.740
But they provoked him with their counsel,

03:53:27.240 --> 03:53:29.780
And were brought low for their iniquity.

03:53:30.780 --> 03:53:33.120
Nevertheless he regarded their affliction,

03:53:33.120 --> 03:53:34.900
When he heard their cry,

03:53:35.420 --> 03:53:37.740
And he remembered for them his covenant,

03:53:38.280 --> 03:53:41.820
And repented according to the multitude of his mercies.

03:53:43.060 --> 03:53:48.540
He made them also to be pitied of all those that carried them captives.

03:53:49.240 --> 03:53:51.040
Save us, O Lord our God,

03:53:51.760 --> 03:53:54.940
And gather us from among the heathen,

03:53:55.160 --> 03:53:57.020
To give thanks unto thy holy name,

03:53:57.080 --> 03:53:59.120
And to triumph in thy praise.

03:54:00.140 --> 03:54:03.060
Blessed be the Lord God of Israel,

03:54:03.260 --> 03:54:05.540
From everlasting to everlasting,

03:54:06.400 --> 03:54:08.780
And let all the people say Amen,

03:54:09.580 --> 03:54:10.900
Praise ye the Lord.

03:54:13.160 --> 03:54:14.600
Psalm 107

03:54:15.120 --> 03:54:17.540
O give thanks unto the Lord,

03:54:17.640 --> 03:54:18.780
For he is good,

03:54:19.340 --> 03:54:22.160
For his mercy endureth for ever.

03:54:22.980 --> 03:54:25.140
Let the redeemed of the Lord say so,

03:54:26.040 --> 03:54:29.000
Whom he hath redeemed from the hand of the enemy,

03:54:29.640 --> 03:54:31.780
And gathered them out of the lands,

03:54:31.880 --> 03:54:32.760
From the east,

03:54:33.240 --> 03:54:34.360
And from the west,

03:54:34.680 --> 03:54:35.440
From the north,

03:54:35.480 --> 03:54:36.800
And from the south.

03:54:37.760 --> 03:54:40.940
They wandered in the wilderness in a solitary way,

03:54:41.340 --> 03:54:43.740
They found no city to dwell in,

03:54:44.020 --> 03:54:45.360
Hungry and thirsty,

03:54:45.820 --> 03:54:47.700
Their soul fainted in them.

03:54:48.220 --> 03:54:50.860
Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble,

03:54:50.940 --> 03:54:53.920
And he delivered them out of their distresses.

03:54:54.880 --> 03:54:57.860
And he led them forth by the right way,

03:54:58.440 --> 03:55:02.240
That they might go to a city of habitation.

03:55:03.500 --> 03:55:06.640
O that men would praise the Lord for his goodness,

03:55:07.200 --> 03:55:10.740
And for his wonderful works to the children of men,

03:55:11.520 --> 03:55:14.480
For he satisfieth the longing soul,

03:55:14.960 --> 03:55:18.140
And filleth the hungry soul with goodness.

03:55:19.720 --> 03:55:21.760
Such as sit in darkness,

03:55:21.920 --> 03:55:23.380
And in the shadow of death,

03:55:23.820 --> 03:55:26.100
Being bound in affliction and iron,

03:55:26.100 --> 03:55:29.380
Because they rebelled against the words of God,

03:55:30.080 --> 03:55:33.020
And condemned the council of the Most High.

03:55:33.620 --> 03:55:36.280
Therefore he brought down their heart with labor,

03:55:36.900 --> 03:55:38.240
They fell down,

03:55:38.640 --> 03:55:40.240
And there was none to help.

03:55:41.200 --> 03:55:43.300
Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble,

03:55:43.420 --> 03:55:45.780
And he saved them out of their distresses.

03:55:47.300 --> 03:55:49.500
He brought them out of darkness,

03:55:50.000 --> 03:55:51.380
And the shadow of death,

03:55:51.700 --> 03:55:54.080
And break their bands in sunder.

03:55:54.780 --> 03:55:58.400
O that men would praise the Lord for his goodness,

03:55:59.120 --> 03:56:02.740
And for his wonderful works to the children of men,

03:56:03.580 --> 03:56:06.380
For he hath broken the gates of brass,

03:56:06.940 --> 03:56:09.660
And cut the bars of iron and sunder.

03:56:10.780 --> 03:56:12.980
Fools, because of their transgression,

03:56:13.080 --> 03:56:16.140
And because of their iniquities, are afflicted,

03:56:16.420 --> 03:56:19.620
Their soul abhorreth all manner of meat,

03:56:20.160 --> 03:56:23.240
And they draw near unto the gates of death.

03:56:24.080 --> 03:56:26.940
Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble,

03:56:27.180 --> 03:56:29.840
And he saveth them out of their distresses.

03:56:30.080 --> 03:56:32.480
He sent his word, and healed them,

03:56:32.660 --> 03:56:35.400
And delivered them from their destructions.

03:56:36.080 --> 03:56:39.980
O that men would praise the Lord for his goodness,

03:56:40.580 --> 03:56:43.680
And for his wonderful works to the children of men,

03:56:44.280 --> 03:56:47.720
And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving,

03:56:48.320 --> 03:56:51.300
And declare his works with rejoicing.

03:56:51.810 --> 03:56:54.640
They that go down to the sea in ships,

03:56:55.080 --> 03:56:57.220
That do business in the great waters,

03:56:58.420 --> 03:57:00.700
These see the works of the Lord,

03:57:01.300 --> 03:57:03.280
And his wonders in the deep.

03:57:04.400 --> 03:57:08.040
For he commandeth and raiseth the stormy wind,

03:57:08.420 --> 03:57:10.820
Which lifteth up the waves thereof.

03:57:11.600 --> 03:57:13.440
They mount up to the heaven.

03:57:14.400 --> 03:57:16.860
They go down again to the depths,

03:57:17.080 --> 03:57:20.320
Their soul is melted because of trouble.

03:57:20.320 --> 03:57:25.100
They reel to and fro, and stagger like a drunken man,

03:57:25.420 --> 03:57:27.220
And are at their wit's end.

03:57:27.920 --> 03:57:30.340
Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble,

03:57:30.500 --> 03:57:32.880
And he bringeth them out of their distresses.

03:57:33.880 --> 03:57:36.060
He maketh the storm a calm,

03:57:36.520 --> 03:57:39.260
So that the waves thereof are still.

03:57:40.600 --> 03:57:43.260
Then they are glad because they be quiet.

03:57:44.300 --> 03:57:47.840
So he bringeth them unto their desired haven.

03:57:48.400 --> 03:57:52.120
O that men would praise the Lord for his goodness,

03:57:52.720 --> 03:57:56.280
And for his wonderful works to the children of men,

03:57:56.840 --> 03:58:00.640
Let them exalt him also in the congregation of the people,

03:58:01.100 --> 03:58:04.420
And praise him in the assembly of the elders.

03:58:05.300 --> 03:58:07.400
He turneth rivers into a wilderness,

03:58:08.280 --> 03:58:11.240
And the water springs into dry ground,

03:58:11.800 --> 03:58:14.380
A fruitful land into barrenness.

03:58:14.900 --> 03:58:17.400
For the wickedness of them that dwell therein,

03:58:17.400 --> 03:58:21.380
He turneth the wilderness into a standing water,

03:58:21.660 --> 03:58:24.280
And dry ground into water springs.

03:58:25.500 --> 03:58:27.880
And there he maketh the hungry to dwell,

03:58:28.420 --> 03:58:31.420
That they may prepare a city for habitation,

03:58:32.060 --> 03:58:35.000
And sow the fields and plant vineyards,

03:58:35.340 --> 03:58:37.620
Which may yield fruits of increase.

03:58:38.600 --> 03:58:40.520
He blesseth them also,

03:58:40.960 --> 03:58:43.400
So that they are multiplied greatly,

03:58:43.880 --> 03:58:46.620
And suffereth not their cattle to decrease.

03:58:47.180 --> 03:58:49.480
Again they are minnished,

03:58:49.740 --> 03:58:51.660
And brought low through oppression,

03:58:52.120 --> 03:58:53.480
Affliction and sorrow.

03:58:54.260 --> 03:58:57.120
He poureth contempt upon princes,

03:58:57.840 --> 03:59:00.500
And causeth them to wander in the wilderness

03:59:00.500 --> 03:59:02.020
Where there is no way.

03:59:02.600 --> 03:59:06.040
Yet setteth he the poor on high from affliction,

03:59:06.520 --> 03:59:09.480
And maketh him families like a flock.

03:59:10.320 --> 03:59:12.860
The righteous shall see it and rejoice,

03:59:13.360 --> 03:59:16.460
And all iniquity shall stop her mouth.

03:59:17.320 --> 03:59:21.180
Whoso is wise and will observe these things,

03:59:21.560 --> 03:59:25.760
Even they shall understand the loving kindness of the Lord.

03:59:27.660 --> 03:59:28.820
Psalm 108

03:59:29.460 --> 03:59:31.840
O God, my heart is fixed,

03:59:32.120 --> 03:59:35.980
I will sing and give praise even with my glory.

03:59:36.760 --> 03:59:38.580
Awake, sultry and harp,

03:59:38.960 --> 03:59:41.200
I myself will awake early.

03:59:41.700 --> 03:59:44.820
I will praise thee, O Lord, among the people,

03:59:44.820 --> 03:59:48.900
And I will sing praises unto thee among the nations.

03:59:49.540 --> 03:59:52.340
For thy mercy is great above the heavens,

03:59:52.920 --> 03:59:56.280
And thy truth reacheth unto the clouds.

03:59:57.180 --> 03:59:59.960
Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens,

04:00:00.620 --> 04:00:03.380
And thy glory above all the earth,

04:00:04.120 --> 04:00:06.400
That thy beloved may be delivered,

04:00:07.160 --> 04:00:09.860
Save with thy right hand and answer me.

04:00:11.080 --> 04:00:13.240
God hath spoken in his holiness,

04:00:13.240 --> 04:00:16.660
I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem,

04:00:17.220 --> 04:00:19.660
And meet out the valley of Sukkoth.

04:00:20.620 --> 04:00:23.620
Gilead is mine, Manasseh is mine,

04:00:23.980 --> 04:00:27.540
Ephraim also is the strength of mine head,

04:00:27.960 --> 04:00:29.800
Judah is my law-giver,

04:00:30.420 --> 04:00:32.340
Moab is my wash-pot,

04:00:32.980 --> 04:00:36.180
Over Edom will I cast out my shoe,

04:00:36.620 --> 04:00:38.800
Over Philistia will I triumph.

04:00:39.560 --> 04:00:42.100
Who will bring me into the strong city?

04:00:42.700 --> 04:00:45.080
Who will lead me into Edom?

04:00:46.180 --> 04:00:49.420
Wilt not thou, O God, who hast cast us off,

04:00:49.720 --> 04:00:53.640
And wilt not thou, O God, go forth with our hosts?

04:00:55.140 --> 04:00:56.680
Give us help from trouble,

04:00:57.380 --> 04:00:59.820
For vain is the help of man.

04:01:01.000 --> 04:01:03.260
Through God we shall do valiantly,

04:01:03.820 --> 04:01:07.640
For he it is that shall tread down our enemies.

04:01:09.280 --> 04:01:10.720
Psalm 109

04:01:10.720 --> 04:01:15.100
Hold not thy peace, O God, of my praise,

04:01:16.060 --> 04:01:19.840
For the mouth of the wicked and the mouth of the deceitful

04:01:19.840 --> 04:01:21.560
Are opened against me.

04:01:22.140 --> 04:01:25.520
They have spoken against me with a lying tongue.

04:01:26.380 --> 04:01:30.020
They compassed me about also with words of hatred,

04:01:30.780 --> 04:01:33.280
And fought against me without a cause.

04:01:34.600 --> 04:01:37.320
For my love they are my adversaries,

04:01:37.320 --> 04:01:40.320
But I give myself unto prayer,

04:01:40.940 --> 04:01:45.560
And they have rewarded me evil for good and hatred for my love.

04:01:46.640 --> 04:01:48.660
Set thou a wicked man over him,

04:01:49.400 --> 04:01:52.240
And let Satan stand at his right hand.

04:01:53.180 --> 04:01:55.980
When he shall be judged let him be condemned,

04:01:56.860 --> 04:01:59.060
And let his prayer become sin.

04:01:59.840 --> 04:02:01.480
Let his days be few,

04:02:01.900 --> 04:02:03.920
And let another take his office.

04:02:04.560 --> 04:02:06.880
Let his children be fatherless,

04:02:07.320 --> 04:02:08.900
And his wife a widow.

04:02:09.880 --> 04:02:14.040
Let his children be continually vagabonds and beg.

04:02:14.660 --> 04:02:18.840
Let them seek their bread also out of their desolate places.

04:02:20.120 --> 04:02:23.540
Let the extortioner catch all that he hath,

04:02:24.400 --> 04:02:27.460
And let the stranger spoil his labor.

04:02:28.600 --> 04:02:31.860
Let there be none to extend mercy unto him,

04:02:32.060 --> 04:02:35.740
Neither let there be any to favor his fatherless children.

04:02:36.300 --> 04:02:38.960
Let his posterity be cut off,

04:02:39.200 --> 04:02:43.760
And in the generation following let their name be blotted out.

04:02:45.060 --> 04:02:49.360
Let the iniquity of his fathers be remembered with the Lord,

04:02:50.040 --> 04:02:53.300
And let not the sin of his mother be blotted out.

04:02:53.840 --> 04:02:56.500
Let them be before the Lord continually,

04:02:57.060 --> 04:03:00.320
That he may cut off the memory of them from the earth,

04:03:00.580 --> 04:03:03.640
Because that he remembered not to show mercy,

04:03:03.640 --> 04:03:07.160
But persecuted the poor and needy man,

04:03:07.680 --> 04:03:10.840
That he might even slay the broken in heart.

04:03:12.240 --> 04:03:13.480
As he loved cursing,

04:03:14.380 --> 04:03:15.980
So let it come unto him.

04:03:16.340 --> 04:03:18.180
As he delighted not in blessing,

04:03:19.020 --> 04:03:21.000
So let it be far from him.

04:03:22.020 --> 04:03:25.980
As he clothed himself with cursing like as with his garment,

04:03:26.440 --> 04:03:29.760
So let it come into his bowels like water,

04:03:30.140 --> 04:03:32.360
And like oil into his bones.

04:03:33.640 --> 04:03:36.960
Let it be unto him as the garment which covereth him,

04:03:37.480 --> 04:03:41.020
And for a girdle wherewith he is girded continually.

04:03:42.020 --> 04:03:45.820
Let this be the reward of mine adversaries from the Lord,

04:03:46.460 --> 04:03:50.100
And of them that speak evil against my soul.

04:03:50.700 --> 04:03:54.660
But do thou for me, O God the Lord, for thy name's sake,

04:03:55.180 --> 04:03:58.240
Because thy mercy is good, deliver thou me.

04:03:58.860 --> 04:04:03.540
For I am poor and needy, and my heart is wounded within me.

04:04:04.420 --> 04:04:08.240
I am gone like the shadow when it declineeth,

04:04:08.540 --> 04:04:11.640
I am tossed up and down as the locust,

04:04:12.000 --> 04:04:14.880
My knees are weak through fasting,

04:04:15.860 --> 04:04:18.280
And my flesh faileth of fatness.

04:04:19.240 --> 04:04:21.940
I became also a reproach unto them,

04:04:22.400 --> 04:04:25.280
When they looked upon me they shaked their heads.

04:04:26.120 --> 04:04:28.080
Help me, O Lord my God,

04:04:28.460 --> 04:04:31.320
O save me according to thy mercy,

04:04:31.980 --> 04:04:35.740
That they may know that this is thy hand,

04:04:35.900 --> 04:04:38.000
That thou, Lord, hast done it.

04:04:38.900 --> 04:04:41.340
Let them curse, but bless thou.

04:04:42.280 --> 04:04:45.500
When they arise, let them be ashamed,

04:04:46.180 --> 04:04:48.240
But let thy servant rejoice.

04:04:49.340 --> 04:04:52.280
Let mine adversaries be clothed with shame,

04:04:53.380 --> 04:04:58.460
And let them cover themselves with their own confusion as with a mantle.

04:05:00.300 --> 04:05:03.860
I will greatly praise the Lord with my mouth,

04:05:04.140 --> 04:05:07.540
Yea, I will praise him among the multitude,

04:05:08.140 --> 04:05:11.220
For he shall stand at the right hand of the poor,

04:05:11.360 --> 04:05:15.560
To save him from those that condemn his soul.

04:05:18.620 --> 04:05:19.980
Psalm 110

04:05:21.000 --> 04:05:23.500
The Lord said unto my Lord,

04:05:23.980 --> 04:05:26.000
Sit thou at my right hand,

04:05:26.380 --> 04:05:28.440
Until I make thine enemies thy footstool,

04:05:29.280 --> 04:05:33.560
The Lord shall send the rod of thy strength out of Zion,

04:05:34.180 --> 04:05:36.900
Rule thou in the midst of thine enemies,

04:05:37.700 --> 04:05:40.640
Thy people shall be willing in the day of thy power,

04:05:41.060 --> 04:05:44.320
In the beauties of holiness from the womb of the morning,

04:05:44.760 --> 04:05:46.700
Thou hast the dew of thy youth.

04:05:48.060 --> 04:05:50.920
The Lord hath sworn, and will not repent,

04:05:51.600 --> 04:05:55.120
Thou art a priest forever after the order of Melchizedek.

04:05:55.120 --> 04:06:01.420
The Lord at thy right hand shall strike through kings in the day of his wrath,

04:06:02.420 --> 04:06:04.360
He shall judge among the heathen,

04:06:04.620 --> 04:06:07.680
He shall fill the places with the dead bodies,

04:06:08.500 --> 04:06:11.420
He shall wound the heads over many countries,

04:06:12.540 --> 04:06:14.760
He shall drink of the brook in the way,

04:06:15.180 --> 04:06:17.280
Therefore shall he lift up the head.

04:06:20.240 --> 04:06:21.520
Psalm 111

04:06:21.520 --> 04:06:23.140
Praise ye the Lord,

04:06:23.140 --> 04:06:26.480
I will praise the Lord with my whole heart,

04:06:26.880 --> 04:06:30.180
In the assembly of the upright, and in the congregation.

04:06:31.100 --> 04:06:33.000
The works of the Lord are great,

04:06:33.520 --> 04:06:36.340
Sought out of all them that have pleasure therein.

04:06:36.840 --> 04:06:39.060
His work is honorable and glorious,

04:06:39.800 --> 04:06:42.120
And his righteousness endureth for ever.

04:06:42.940 --> 04:06:46.000
He hath made his wonderful works to be remembered.

04:06:47.360 --> 04:06:50.680
The Lord is gracious and full of compassion,

04:06:50.680 --> 04:06:53.980
He hath given meat unto them that fear him,

04:06:54.380 --> 04:06:57.060
He will ever be mindful of his covenant,

04:06:57.920 --> 04:07:01.380
He hath showed his people the power of his works,

04:07:01.940 --> 04:07:04.960
That he may give them the heritage of the heathen.

04:07:06.640 --> 04:07:10.600
The works of his hands are verity and judgment,

04:07:11.100 --> 04:07:13.160
All his commandments are sure,

04:07:13.660 --> 04:07:16.180
They stand fast for ever and ever,

04:07:16.460 --> 04:07:19.140
And are done in truth and uprightness.

04:07:19.820 --> 04:07:22.400
He sent redemption unto his people,

04:07:22.680 --> 04:07:25.460
He hath commanded his covenant for ever,

04:07:26.200 --> 04:07:28.660
Holy and reverend is his name.

04:07:29.520 --> 04:07:32.800
The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom,

04:07:33.580 --> 04:07:37.820
A good understanding have all they that do his commandments,

04:07:38.460 --> 04:07:40.880
His praise endureth for ever.

04:07:42.360 --> 04:07:43.880
Psalm 112

04:07:44.900 --> 04:07:46.580
Praise ye the Lord,

04:07:46.580 --> 04:07:50.320
Blessed is the man that feareth the Lord,

04:07:50.840 --> 04:07:53.160
That delighteth greatly in his commandments,

04:07:53.920 --> 04:07:56.840
His seed shall be mighty upon earth,

04:07:57.620 --> 04:08:00.640
The generation of the upright shall be blessed,

04:08:01.380 --> 04:08:04.460
Wealth and riches shall be in his house,

04:08:05.100 --> 04:08:07.640
And his righteousness endureth for ever.

04:08:08.580 --> 04:08:11.860
Unto the upright there ariseth light in the darkness,

04:08:12.520 --> 04:08:16.700
He is gracious and full of compassion and righteous,

04:08:17.860 --> 04:08:20.540
A good man showeth favor and lendeth,

04:08:21.220 --> 04:08:24.100
He will guide his affairs with discretion,

04:08:25.100 --> 04:08:27.880
Surely he shall not be moved for ever,

04:08:28.440 --> 04:08:31.980
The righteous shall be in everlasting remembrance,

04:08:32.400 --> 04:08:35.060
He shall not be afraid of evil tidings,

04:08:35.420 --> 04:08:38.480
His heart is fixed, trusting in the Lord,

04:08:38.980 --> 04:08:40.540
His heart is established,

04:08:40.540 --> 04:08:45.200
He shall not be afraid until he see his desire upon his enemies,

04:08:45.820 --> 04:08:49.420
He hath dispersed, he hath given to the poor,

04:08:49.880 --> 04:08:52.140
His righteousness endureth for ever,

04:08:52.620 --> 04:08:55.100
His horn shall be exalted with honor,

04:08:55.620 --> 04:08:58.220
The wicked shall see it and be grieved,

04:08:58.640 --> 04:09:02.460
He shall gnash with his teeth and melt away,

04:09:03.080 --> 04:09:05.980
The desire of the wicked shall perish.

04:09:06.800 --> 04:09:07.900
Psalm 113

04:09:08.600 --> 04:09:12.920
Praise ye the Lord, praise, O ye servants of the Lord,

04:09:13.300 --> 04:09:15.540
Praise the name of the Lord!

04:09:16.120 --> 04:09:18.080
Blessed be the name of the Lord,

04:09:18.680 --> 04:09:21.440
From this time forth and for evermore,

04:09:21.960 --> 04:09:24.720
From the rising of the sun unto the going down

04:09:24.720 --> 04:09:28.320
Of the same the Lord's name is to be praised.

04:09:29.280 --> 04:09:31.380
The Lord is high above all nations,

04:09:31.860 --> 04:09:34.220
And his glory above the heavens,

04:09:34.940 --> 04:09:37.560
Who is like unto the Lord our God,

04:09:37.760 --> 04:09:39.140
Who dwelleth on high,

04:09:39.820 --> 04:09:43.000
Who humbleth himself to behold the things

04:09:43.000 --> 04:09:45.400
That are in heaven and in the earth,

04:09:46.280 --> 04:09:48.980
He raiseth up the poor out of the dust,

04:09:49.440 --> 04:09:52.500
And lifteth the needy out of the dung-hill,

04:09:53.200 --> 04:09:55.280
That he may set him with princes,

04:09:55.820 --> 04:09:58.080
Even with the princes of his people,

04:09:58.980 --> 04:10:01.960
He maketh the barren woman to keep house,

04:10:02.580 --> 04:10:05.520
And to be a joyful mother of children.

04:10:06.100 --> 04:10:07.880
Praise ye the Lord!

04:10:08.360 --> 04:10:10.140
Psalm 114

04:10:10.140 --> 04:10:12.560
When Israel went out of Egypt,

04:10:12.920 --> 04:10:16.620
The house of Jacob from a people of strange language,

04:10:17.200 --> 04:10:18.820
Judah was his sanctuary,

04:10:19.220 --> 04:10:21.140
And Israel his dominion,

04:10:21.540 --> 04:10:23.020
The sea sawed and fled,

04:10:23.580 --> 04:10:25.320
Jordan was driven back,

04:10:25.800 --> 04:10:28.280
The mountains skipped like rams,

04:10:28.760 --> 04:10:30.680
And the little hills like lambs.

04:10:31.500 --> 04:10:35.040
What ailed thee, O thou sea, that thou flettest,

04:10:35.740 --> 04:10:39.640
Thou Jordan, that thou wast driven back,

04:10:40.680 --> 04:10:43.320
Ye mountains that ye skipped like rams,

04:10:43.580 --> 04:10:45.840
And ye little hills like lambs,

04:10:46.560 --> 04:10:49.700
Tremble thou earth at the presence of the Lord,

04:10:50.220 --> 04:10:52.520
At the presence of the God of Jacob,

04:10:53.180 --> 04:10:55.940
Which turned the rock into a standing water,

04:10:56.520 --> 04:10:59.580
The flint into a fountain of waters.

04:11:00.720 --> 04:11:02.040
Psalm 115

04:11:02.700 --> 04:11:06.140
Not unto us, O Lord, not unto us,

04:11:06.200 --> 04:11:08.400
But unto thy name give glory,

04:11:08.860 --> 04:11:11.540
For thy mercy and for thy truth's sake.

04:11:12.480 --> 04:11:14.200
Wherefore should the heathen say,

04:11:14.720 --> 04:11:16.380
Where is now their God?

04:11:17.340 --> 04:11:18.980
But our God is in the heavens,

04:11:19.400 --> 04:11:22.180
He hath done whatsoever he hath pleased.

04:11:23.280 --> 04:11:25.260
Their idols are silver and gold,

04:11:25.400 --> 04:11:27.080
The work of men's hands.

04:11:27.900 --> 04:11:30.460
They have mouths, but they speak not,

04:11:30.920 --> 04:11:33.980
Eyes have they, but they see not,

04:11:34.340 --> 04:11:37.120
They have ears, but they hear not,

04:11:37.860 --> 04:11:40.940
Noses have they, but they smell not,

04:11:41.520 --> 04:11:43.820
They have hands, but they handle not,

04:11:44.160 --> 04:11:46.860
Feet have they, but they walk not,

04:11:47.000 --> 04:11:49.520
Neither speak they through their throat.

04:11:50.320 --> 04:11:52.820
They that make them are like unto them,

04:11:53.540 --> 04:11:56.220
So is every one that trusteth in them.

04:11:56.860 --> 04:11:59.740
O Israel, trust thou in the Lord,

04:12:00.740 --> 04:12:03.160
He is their help and their shield.

04:12:03.960 --> 04:12:06.740
O house of Aaron, trust in the Lord,

04:12:07.240 --> 04:12:09.380
He is their help and their shield.

04:12:10.400 --> 04:12:13.740
Ye that fear the Lord, trust in the Lord,

04:12:13.960 --> 04:12:16.820
He is their help and their shield.

04:12:17.720 --> 04:12:20.020
The Lord hath been mindful of us,

04:12:20.220 --> 04:12:21.460
He will bless us,

04:12:21.660 --> 04:12:23.740
He will bless the house of Israel,

04:12:24.060 --> 04:12:26.080
He will bless the house of Aaron.

04:12:26.220 --> 04:12:28.860
He will bless them that fear the Lord,

04:12:29.040 --> 04:12:30.420
Both small and great,

04:12:31.060 --> 04:12:33.880
The Lord shall increase you more and more,

04:12:34.120 --> 04:12:35.520
You and your children.

04:12:36.940 --> 04:12:38.960
Ye are blessed of the Lord,

04:12:39.340 --> 04:12:40.800
Which made heaven and earth,

04:12:41.340 --> 04:12:43.900
The heaven, even the heavens are the Lord's,

04:12:44.700 --> 04:12:48.100
But the earth hath he given to the children of men.

04:12:49.100 --> 04:12:50.860
The dead praise not the Lord,

04:12:51.640 --> 04:12:54.240
Neither any that go down into silence,

04:12:54.820 --> 04:12:56.680
But we will bless the Lord,

04:12:56.900 --> 04:12:59.560
From this time forth and for evermore.

04:13:00.140 --> 04:13:01.340
Praise the Lord.

04:13:26.280 --> 04:13:31.280
Psalm 116 I love the Lord, because he hath heard my

04:13:31.280 --> 04:13:33.120
voice and my supplications.

04:13:33.600 --> 04:13:39.440
Because he hath inclined his ear unto me, therefore will I call upon him as long as

04:13:39.440 --> 04:13:39.940
I live.

04:13:40.500 --> 04:13:46.240
The sorrows of death compassed me, and the pains of hell gath hold upon me.

04:13:46.520 --> 04:13:48.580
I found trouble and sorrow.

04:13:49.300 --> 04:13:56.120
Then called I upon the name of the Lord, O Lord, I beseech thee, deliver my soul.

04:13:56.760 --> 04:14:01.600
Gracious is the Lord, and righteous, yea, our God is merciful.

04:14:02.220 --> 04:14:04.120
The Lord preserveth the simple.

04:14:04.660 --> 04:14:07.020
I was brought low, and he helped me.

04:14:07.740 --> 04:14:13.060
Return unto thy rest, O my soul, for the Lord hath dealt bountifully with thee.

04:14:13.600 --> 04:14:19.460
For thou hast delivered my soul from death, mine eyes from tears, and my feet from falling.

04:14:20.460 --> 04:14:23.800
I will walk before the Lord in the land of the living.

04:14:24.320 --> 04:14:26.740
I believed, therefore have I spoken.

04:14:27.220 --> 04:14:28.920
I was greatly afflicted.

04:14:29.160 --> 04:14:32.240
I said in my haste, All men are liars.

04:14:32.740 --> 04:14:36.840
What shall I render unto the Lord for all his benefits toward me?

04:14:37.300 --> 04:14:41.700
I will take the cup of salvation, and call upon the name of the Lord.

04:14:42.380 --> 04:14:47.280
I will pay my vows unto the Lord, now in the presence of all his people.

04:14:48.200 --> 04:14:51.780
Precious in the sight of the Lord is the death of his saints.

04:14:52.520 --> 04:14:55.300
O Lord, truly I am thy servant.

04:14:55.800 --> 04:14:58.700
I am thy servant, and the son of thine handmaid.

04:14:58.900 --> 04:15:00.400
Thou hast loosed my bonds.

04:15:01.260 --> 04:15:06.660
I will offer to thee the sacrifice of thanksgiving, and will call upon the name of the Lord.

04:15:07.300 --> 04:15:12.240
I will pay my vows unto the Lord, now in the presence of all his people.

04:15:12.520 --> 04:15:18.720
In the courts of the Lord's house, in the midst of thee, O Jerusalem, praise ye the

04:15:18.720 --> 04:15:19.300
Lord.

04:15:22.020 --> 04:15:23.370
Psalm 117

04:15:23.820 --> 04:15:27.380
O praise the Lord, all ye nations!

04:15:27.820 --> 04:15:30.120
Praise him, all ye people!

04:15:30.540 --> 04:15:37.320
For his merciful kindness is great toward us, and the truth of the Lord endureth for

04:15:37.320 --> 04:15:37.680
ever.

04:15:38.240 --> 04:15:40.380
Praise ye the Lord.

04:15:43.360 --> 04:15:45.160
Psalm 118

04:15:45.690 --> 04:15:52.420
O give thanks unto the Lord, for he is good, because his mercy endureth for ever.

04:15:53.080 --> 04:15:57.220
Let Israel now say, that his mercy endureth for ever.

04:15:57.580 --> 04:16:02.920
Let the house of Aaron now say, that his mercy endureth for ever.

04:16:03.540 --> 04:16:08.480
Let them now that fear the Lord say, that his mercy endureth for ever.

04:16:08.960 --> 04:16:11.300
I called upon the Lord in distress.

04:16:11.300 --> 04:16:15.160
The Lord answered me, and set me in a large place.

04:16:15.680 --> 04:16:19.260
The Lord is on my side, I will not fear.

04:16:19.680 --> 04:16:21.740
What can man do unto me?

04:16:22.340 --> 04:16:28.880
The Lord taketh my part with them that help me, therefore shall I see my desire upon them

04:16:28.880 --> 04:16:29.800
that hate me.

04:16:30.560 --> 04:16:34.840
It is better to trust in the Lord than to put confidence in man.

04:16:35.480 --> 04:16:40.860
It is better to trust in the Lord than to put confidence in princes.

04:16:42.080 --> 04:16:47.600
All nations compassed me about, but in the name of the Lord will I destroy them.

04:16:48.440 --> 04:16:54.220
They compassed me about, yea they compassed me about, but in the name of the Lord I will

04:16:54.220 --> 04:16:55.360
destroy them.

04:16:57.220 --> 04:17:03.420
They compassed me about like bees, they are quenched as the fire of thorns, for in the

04:17:03.420 --> 04:17:06.280
name of the Lord I will destroy them.

04:17:06.760 --> 04:17:12.100
Thou hast thrust soar at me that I might fall, but the Lord helped me.

04:17:12.600 --> 04:17:17.140
The Lord is my strength and song, and is become my salvation.

04:17:17.920 --> 04:17:22.940
The voice of rejoicing and salvation is in the tabernacles of the righteous.

04:17:23.480 --> 04:17:26.440
The right hand of the Lord doeth valiantly.

04:17:27.080 --> 04:17:33.100
The right hand of the Lord is exalted, the right hand of the Lord doeth valiantly.

04:17:33.920 --> 04:17:38.200
I shall not die, but live, and declare the works of the Lord.

04:17:38.740 --> 04:17:43.500
The Lord hath chastened me sore, but he hath not given me over unto death.

04:17:44.600 --> 04:17:50.620
Open to me the gates of righteousness, I will go into them, and I will praise the Lord.

04:17:51.170 --> 04:17:57.320
This gate of the Lord into which the righteous shall enter, I will praise thee for thou hast

04:17:57.320 --> 04:17:59.980
heard me, and art become my salvation.

04:18:00.640 --> 04:18:05.280
The stone which the builders refused is become the headstone of the corner.

04:18:06.080 --> 04:18:10.420
This is the Lord's doing, it is marvelous in our eyes.

04:18:11.120 --> 04:18:15.980
This is the day which the Lord hath made, we will rejoice and be glad in it.

04:18:16.600 --> 04:18:23.420
Save now, I beseech thee, O Lord, O Lord, I beseech thee, send now prosperity.

04:18:24.840 --> 04:18:30.140
Blessed be he that cometh in the name of the Lord, we have blessed you out of the house

04:18:30.140 --> 04:18:30.860
of the Lord.

04:18:31.540 --> 04:18:37.760
God is the Lord which hath showed us light, bind the sacrifice with cords, even unto the

04:18:37.760 --> 04:18:38.760
horns of the altar.

04:18:39.960 --> 04:18:46.100
Thou art my God, and I will praise thee, Thou art my God, I will exalt thee.

04:18:46.900 --> 04:18:53.660
O give thanks unto the Lord, for he is good, for his mercy endureth for ever.

04:18:58.980 --> 04:19:04.300
Blessed are the undefiled in the way, who walk in the law of the Lord.

04:19:04.900 --> 04:19:09.920
Blessed are they that keep his testimonies, and that seek him with the whole heart.

04:19:10.660 --> 04:19:14.500
They also do no iniquity, they walk in his ways.

04:19:15.340 --> 04:19:18.580
Thou hast commanded us to keep thy precepts diligently.

04:19:19.580 --> 04:19:22.980
O that my ways were directed to keep thy statutes.

04:19:23.920 --> 04:19:28.880
Then shall I not be ashamed, when I have respect unto all thy commandments.

04:19:29.500 --> 04:19:35.780
I will praise thee with uprightness of heart, when I shall have learned thy righteous judgments.

04:19:36.720 --> 04:19:40.680
I will keep thy statutes, O forsake me not utterly.

04:19:41.780 --> 04:19:44.360
Wherewithal shall a young man cleanse his way?

04:19:44.940 --> 04:19:47.980
By taking heed thereto according to thy word.

04:19:48.840 --> 04:19:54.580
With my whole heart have I sought thee, O let me not wander from thy commandments.

04:19:55.400 --> 04:20:00.720
Thy word have I hid in mine heart, that I might not sin against thee.

04:20:01.660 --> 04:20:05.320
Blessed art thou, O Lord, teach me thy statutes.

04:20:05.880 --> 04:20:10.060
With my lips have I declared all the judgments of thy mouth.

04:20:10.940 --> 04:20:15.860
I have rejoiced in the way of thy testimonies, as much as in all riches.

04:20:16.580 --> 04:20:21.020
I will meditate in thy precepts, and have respect unto thy ways.

04:20:21.580 --> 04:20:26.400
I will delight myself in thy statutes, I will not forget thy word.

04:20:27.200 --> 04:20:32.020
Deal bountifully with thy servant, that I may live and keep thy word.

04:20:32.740 --> 04:20:36.980
Open thou mine eyes, that I may behold wondrous things out of thy law.

04:20:37.520 --> 04:20:41.780
I am a stranger in the earth, hide not thy commandments from me.

04:20:42.260 --> 04:20:47.540
My soul breaketh for the longing that it hath unto thy judgments at all times.

04:20:48.160 --> 04:20:53.620
Thou hast rebuked the proud that are cursed, which do err from thy commandments.

04:20:54.700 --> 04:20:59.660
Remove from me reproach and contempt, for I have kept thy testimonies.

04:21:00.560 --> 04:21:07.080
Princes also did sit and speak against me, but thy servant did meditate in thy statutes.

04:21:07.900 --> 04:21:11.920
Thy testimonies also are my delight and my counsellors.

04:21:12.400 --> 04:21:17.380
My soul cleaveth unto the dust, quicken thou me according to thy word.

04:21:18.480 --> 04:21:23.740
I have declared my ways, and thou hurtest me, teach me thy statutes.

04:21:24.760 --> 04:21:30.520
Make me to understand the way of thy precepts, so shall I talk of thy wondrous works.

04:21:31.320 --> 04:21:36.900
My soul melteth for heaviness, strengthen thou me according unto thy word.

04:21:37.700 --> 04:21:42.200
Remove from me the way of lying, and grant me thy law graciously.

04:21:43.160 --> 04:21:47.520
I have chosen the way of truth, thy judgments have I laid before me.

04:21:48.560 --> 04:21:53.300
I have stuck unto thy testimonies, O Lord, put me not to shame.

04:21:54.400 --> 04:21:58.860
I will run the way of thy commandments, when thou shalt enlarge my heart.

04:21:59.540 --> 04:22:04.400
Teach me, O Lord, the way of thy statutes, and I shall keep it unto the end.

04:22:05.120 --> 04:22:11.300
Give me understanding, and I shall keep thy law, yea, I shall observe it with my whole heart.

04:22:12.120 --> 04:22:16.660
Make me to go in the path of thy commandments, for therein do I delight.

04:22:17.740 --> 04:22:22.020
Incline my heart unto thy testimonies, and not to covetousness.

04:22:22.980 --> 04:22:27.780
Turn away mine eyes from beholding vanity, and quicken thou me in thy way.

04:22:28.500 --> 04:22:32.400
Establish thy word unto thy servant, who is devoted to thy fear.

04:22:32.960 --> 04:22:37.220
Turn away my reproach, which I fear, for thy judgments are good.

04:22:38.040 --> 04:22:43.080
Behold, I have longed after thy precepts, quicken me in thy righteousness.

04:22:44.200 --> 04:22:50.680
Let thy mercies come also unto me, O Lord, even thy salvation according to thy word.

04:22:51.320 --> 04:22:57.260
So shall I have wherewith to answer him that reproacheth me, for I trust in thy word.

04:22:57.260 --> 04:23:03.900
And take not the word of truth utterly out of my mouth, for I have hoped in thy judgments.

04:23:05.040 --> 04:23:10.920
So shall I keep thy law continually for ever and ever, and I will walk at liberty,

04:23:11.220 --> 04:23:18.020
for I seek thy precepts. I will speak of thy testimonies also before kings, and will not be

04:23:18.020 --> 04:23:24.980
ashamed. And I will delight myself in thy commandments, which I have loved. My hands

04:23:24.980 --> 04:23:31.040
also will I lift up unto thy commandments, which I have loved, and I will meditate in thy statutes.

04:23:31.420 --> 04:23:36.640
Remember the word unto thy servant, upon which thou hast caused me to hope.

04:23:37.220 --> 04:23:41.760
This is my comfort in my affliction, for thy word hath quickened me.

04:23:42.180 --> 04:23:48.020
The proud have had me greatly in derision, yet have I not declined from thy law.

04:23:48.700 --> 04:23:53.460
I remembered thy judgments of old, O Lord, and have comfort in myself.

04:23:54.240 --> 04:23:59.220
Horror hath taken hold upon me because of the wicked that forsake thy law.

04:24:00.240 --> 04:24:04.540
Thy statutes have been my songs in the house of my pilgrimage.

04:24:05.220 --> 04:24:09.940
I have remembered thy name, O Lord, in the night, and have kept thy law.

04:24:10.680 --> 04:24:13.980
This I had because I kept thy precepts.

04:24:14.680 --> 04:24:19.080
Thou art my portion, O Lord, I have said that I would keep thy words.

04:24:19.080 --> 04:24:25.360
I entreated thy favor with my whole heart. Be merciful unto me according to thy word.

04:24:26.160 --> 04:24:30.440
I thought on my ways and turned my feet unto thy testimonies.

04:24:30.820 --> 04:24:33.940
I made haste and delayed not to keep thy commandments.

04:24:34.860 --> 04:24:39.200
The bands of the wicked have robbed me, but I have not forgotten thy law.

04:24:39.600 --> 04:24:44.640
At midnight I will rise to give thanks unto thee because of thy righteous judgments.

04:24:45.280 --> 04:24:51.080
I am a companion of all them that fear thee and of them that keep thy precepts.

04:24:51.760 --> 04:24:56.760
The earth, O Lord, is full of thy mercy. Teach me thy statutes.

04:24:57.240 --> 04:25:01.600
Thou hast dealt well with thy servant, O Lord, according unto thy word.

04:25:02.220 --> 04:25:06.300
Teach me good judgment and knowledge, for I have believed thy commandments.

04:25:07.400 --> 04:25:12.520
Before I was afflicted, I went astray, but now have I kept thy word.

04:25:13.080 --> 04:25:17.120
Thou art good, and doest good. Teach me thy statutes.

04:25:17.880 --> 04:25:23.560
The proud have forged a lie against me, but I will keep thy precepts with my whole heart.

04:25:24.960 --> 04:25:29.420
Their heart is as fat as grease, but I delight in thy law.

04:25:29.960 --> 04:25:34.520
It is good for me that I have been afflicted, that I might learn thy statutes.

04:25:35.200 --> 04:25:40.480
The law of thy mouth is better unto me than thousands of gold and silver.

04:25:41.200 --> 04:25:47.440
Thy hands have made me and fashioned me. Give me understanding that I may learn thy commandments.

04:25:48.740 --> 04:25:53.700
They that fear thee will be glad when they see me, because I have hoped in thy word.

04:25:54.240 --> 04:26:00.780
I know, O Lord, that thy judgments are right, and that thou in faithfulness hast afflicted me.

04:26:01.640 --> 04:26:06.720
Let, I pray thee, thy merciful kindness be for my comfort, according to thy word,

04:26:06.720 --> 04:26:14.100
unto thy servant. Let thy tender mercies come unto me, that I may live, for thy law is my delight.

04:26:15.140 --> 04:26:20.300
Let the proud be ashamed, for they dealt perversely with me without a cause,

04:26:20.660 --> 04:26:26.840
but I will meditate in thy precepts. Let those that fear thee turn unto me,

04:26:27.100 --> 04:26:33.300
and those that have known thy testimonies. Let my heart be sound in thy statutes,

04:26:33.300 --> 04:26:39.580
that I be not ashamed. My soul fainteth for thy salvation, but I hope in thy word.

04:26:40.260 --> 04:26:46.280
Mine eyes fail for thy word, saying, When wilt thou comfort me? For I am become

04:26:46.280 --> 04:26:53.380
like a bottle in the smoke, yet do I not forget thy statutes. How many are the days of thy servant,

04:26:53.920 --> 04:26:59.960
when wilt thou execute judgment on them that persecute me? The proud have digged pits for me,

04:26:59.960 --> 04:27:04.120
which are not after thy law. All thy commandments are faithful,

04:27:04.580 --> 04:27:11.600
they persecute me wrongfully, help thou me. They had almost consumed me upon earth,

04:27:12.000 --> 04:27:17.020
but I forsook not thy precepts. Cook in me after thy loving kindness,

04:27:17.440 --> 04:27:24.260
so shall I keep the testimony of thy mouth. Forever, O Lord, thy word is settled in heaven.

04:27:24.260 --> 04:27:30.800
Thy faithfulness is unto all generations. Thou hast established the earth, and it abideth.

04:27:31.280 --> 04:27:35.960
They continue this day according to thine ordinances, for all are thy servants.

04:27:36.640 --> 04:27:41.940
Unless thy law had been my delights, I should then have perished in mine affliction.

04:27:42.500 --> 04:27:47.520
I will never forget thy precepts, for with them thou hast quickened me.

04:27:48.240 --> 04:27:54.620
I am thine, save me, for I have sought thy precepts. The wicked have waited for me to

04:27:54.620 --> 04:28:00.560
destroy me, but I will consider thy testimonies. I have seen an end of all perfection,

04:28:01.060 --> 04:28:08.100
but thy commandment is exceeding broad. O how I love thy law, it is my meditation

04:28:08.100 --> 04:28:14.020
all the day. Thou through thy commandments has made me wiser than mine enemies,

04:28:14.020 --> 04:28:19.020
for they are ever with me. I have more understanding than all my teachers,

04:28:19.360 --> 04:28:24.420
for thy testimonies are my meditation. I understand more than the ancients,

04:28:24.760 --> 04:28:31.740
because I keep thy precepts. I have refrained my feet from every evil way that I might keep thy

04:28:31.740 --> 04:28:39.360
word. I have not departed from thy judgments, for thou hast taught me. How sweet are thy words

04:28:39.360 --> 04:28:46.840
unto my taste, yea, sweeter than honey to my mouth. Through thy precepts I get understanding,

04:28:47.340 --> 04:28:54.920
therefore I hate every false way. Thy word is a lamp unto my feet and a light unto my path.

04:28:55.860 --> 04:29:00.680
I have sworn, and I will perform it, that I will keep thy righteous judgments.

04:29:01.380 --> 04:29:06.500
I am afflicted very much. Quicken me, O Lord, according unto thy word.

04:29:07.160 --> 04:29:13.800
Accept, I beseech thee, the freewill offerings of my mouth, O Lord, and teach me thy judgments.

04:29:14.540 --> 04:29:21.840
My soul is continually in my hand, yet do I not forget thy law. The wicked have laid a snare for

04:29:21.840 --> 04:29:29.400
me, yet I erred not from thy precepts. Thy testimonies have I taken as an heritage forever,

04:29:29.760 --> 04:29:35.860
for they are the rejoicing of my heart. I have inclined my heart to perform thy statutes all way,

04:29:35.860 --> 04:29:44.280
even unto the end. I hate vain thoughts, but thy law do I love. Thou art my hiding place and my

04:29:44.280 --> 04:29:52.040
shield. I hope in thy word. Depart from me, ye evildoers, for I will keep thy commandments of my

04:29:52.040 --> 04:29:59.720
God. Uphold me according unto thy word, that I may live, and let me not be ashamed of my hope.

04:29:59.720 --> 04:30:05.960
Hold thou me up, and I shall be safe, and I will have respect unto thy statutes continually.

04:30:06.900 --> 04:30:14.420
Thou hast trodden down all them that err from thy statutes, for their deceit is falsehood. Thou puttest

04:30:14.420 --> 04:30:21.260
away all the wicked of the earth like dross, therefore I love thy testimonies. My flesh

04:30:21.260 --> 04:30:27.960
trembleth for fear of thee, and I am afraid of thy judgments. I have done judgment and justice.

04:30:27.960 --> 04:30:35.580
Leave me not to mine oppressors. Be surety for thy servant, for good. Let not the proud oppress me.

04:30:36.060 --> 04:30:39.820
Mine eyes fail for thy salvation, and for the word of thy righteousness.

04:30:40.860 --> 04:30:47.760
Deal with thy servant according unto thy mercy, and teach me thy statutes. I am thy servant.

04:30:48.060 --> 04:30:53.040
Give me understanding that I may know thy testimonies. It is time for thee,

04:30:53.040 --> 04:31:00.480
Lord, to work, for they have made void thy law. Therefore I love thy commandments above gold,

04:31:01.140 --> 04:31:08.260
yea, above fine gold. Therefore I esteem all thy precepts concerning all things to be right,

04:31:08.540 --> 04:31:15.380
and I hate every false way. Thy testimonies are wonderful. Therefore doth my soul keep them.

04:31:15.760 --> 04:31:21.280
The entrance of thy words giveth light. It giveth understanding unto the simple.

04:31:21.790 --> 04:31:28.640
I opened my mouth and panted, for I longed for thy commandments. Look thou upon me,

04:31:28.720 --> 04:31:35.600
and be merciful unto me, as thou use'st to do unto those that love thy name. Order my steps in thy

04:31:35.600 --> 04:31:41.960
word, and let not any iniquity have dominion over me. Deliver me from the oppression of man,

04:31:42.280 --> 04:31:47.440
so will I keep thy precepts. Make thy face to shine upon thy servant,

04:31:47.440 --> 04:31:54.940
and teach me thy statutes. Rivers of waters run down mine eyes, because they keep not thy law.

04:31:55.640 --> 04:31:59.440
Righteous art thou, O Lord, and upright are thy judgments.

04:32:00.000 --> 04:32:06.460
Thy testimonies that thou hast commanded are righteous and very faithful. My zeal hath consumed

04:32:06.460 --> 04:32:13.480
me, because mine enemies have forgotten thy words. Thy word is very pure. Therefore thy servant

04:32:13.480 --> 04:32:21.380
loveth it. I am small and despised, yet do not I forget thy precepts. Thy righteousness is an

04:32:21.380 --> 04:32:27.900
everlasting righteousness, and thy law is the truth. Trouble and anguish have taken hold on me,

04:32:28.020 --> 04:32:33.920
yet thy commandments are my delights. The righteousness of thy testimonies is everlasting.

04:32:34.520 --> 04:32:39.160
Give me understanding, and I shall live. I cried with my whole heart,

04:32:39.160 --> 04:32:46.600
Hear me, O Lord, I will keep thy statutes. I cried unto thee, save me, and I shall keep thy

04:32:46.600 --> 04:32:53.120
testimonies. I prevented the dawning of the morning, and cried, I hoped in thy word.

04:32:54.080 --> 04:33:00.700
Mine eyes prevent the night watches that I might meditate in thy word. Hear my voice according

04:33:00.700 --> 04:33:07.520
unto thy loving kindness. O Lord, quicken me according to thy judgment. They draw nigh that

04:33:07.520 --> 04:33:13.900
follow after mischief. They are far from thy law. Thou art near, O Lord, and all thy

04:33:13.900 --> 04:33:20.700
commandments are truth. Concerning thy testimonies, I have known of old that thou hast founded them

04:33:20.700 --> 04:33:28.120
for ever. Consider mine affliction, and deliver me, for I do not forget thy law. Plead my cause,

04:33:28.220 --> 04:33:34.700
and deliver me. Quicken me according to thy word. Salvation is far from the wicked, for they seek

04:33:34.700 --> 04:33:40.920
not thy statutes. Great are thy tender mercies, O Lord. Quicken me according to thy judgments.

04:33:41.620 --> 04:33:47.180
Many are my persecutors and mine enemies, yet do I not decline from thy testimonies.

04:33:47.820 --> 04:33:54.640
I beheld the transgressors, and was grieved, because they kept not thy word. Consider how I

04:33:54.640 --> 04:34:01.200
love thy precepts. Quicken me, O Lord, according to thy loving kindness. The word is true from

04:34:01.200 --> 04:34:06.760
the beginning, and every one of thy righteous judgments endureth for ever. Princes have

04:34:06.760 --> 04:34:14.940
persecuted me without a cause, but my heart standeth in awe of thy word. I rejoice at thy word as one

04:34:14.940 --> 04:34:23.400
that findeth great spoil. I hate and abhor lying, but thy law do I love. Seven times a day do I

04:34:23.400 --> 04:34:30.060
praise thee because of thy righteous judgments. Great peace have they which love thy law, and

04:34:30.060 --> 04:34:36.760
nothing shall offend them. Lord, I have hoped for thy salvation and done thy commandments.

04:34:37.480 --> 04:34:45.100
My soul hath kept thy testimonies, and I love them exceedingly. I have kept thy precepts and

04:34:45.100 --> 04:34:51.980
thy testimonies, for all my ways are before thee. Let my cry come near before thee, O Lord.

04:34:52.340 --> 04:34:58.500
Give me understanding according to thy word. Let my supplication come before thee.

04:34:58.500 --> 04:35:06.020
Deliver me according to thy word. My lips shall utter praise when thou hast taught me thy statutes.

04:35:06.840 --> 04:35:11.300
My tongue shall speak of thy word, for all thy commandments are righteousness.

04:35:12.320 --> 04:35:16.360
Let thine hand help me, for I have chosen thy precepts.

04:35:16.920 --> 04:35:24.220
I have longed for thy salvation, O Lord, and thy law is my delight. Let my soul live,

04:35:24.220 --> 04:35:31.440
and it shall praise thee, and let thy judgments help me. I have gone astray like a lost sheep.

04:35:32.180 --> 04:35:36.760
Seek thy servant, for I do not forget thy commandments.

04:36:00.680 --> 04:36:06.460
Psalm 120 In my distress I cried unto the Lord, and

04:36:06.460 --> 04:36:12.960
he heard me. Deliver my soul, O Lord, from lying lips, and from a deceitful tongue.

04:36:13.720 --> 04:36:19.880
What shall be given unto thee, or what shall be done unto thee, thou false tongue? Sharp

04:36:19.880 --> 04:36:27.340
arrows of the mighty, with coals of juniper. Woe is me that I sojourn in Misak, that I

04:36:27.340 --> 04:36:34.680
dwell in the tents of Kedar. My soul hath long dwelt with him that hateth peace. I am

04:36:34.680 --> 04:36:45.340
for peace, but when I speak they are for war. Psalm 121 I will lift up mine eyes unto the

04:36:45.340 --> 04:36:52.420
hills, from whence cometh my help. My help cometh from the Lord, which made heaven and

04:36:52.420 --> 04:37:00.940
earth. He will not suffer thy foot to be moved. He that keepeth thee will not slumber. Behold,

04:37:00.940 --> 04:37:08.080
he that keepeth Israel shall neither slumber nor sleep. The Lord is thy keeper. The Lord

04:37:08.080 --> 04:37:14.260
is thy shade upon thy right hand. The sun shall not smite thee by day, nor the moon

04:37:14.260 --> 04:37:21.580
by night. The Lord shall preserve thee from all evil. He shall preserve thy soul. The

04:37:21.580 --> 04:37:27.600
Lord shall preserve thy going out, and thy coming in, from this time forth, and even

04:37:27.600 --> 04:37:37.180
for evermore. Psalm 122 I was glad when they said unto me, Let us go into the house of

04:37:37.180 --> 04:37:43.520
the Lord. Our feet shall stand within thy gates, O Jerusalem. Jerusalem is billed as

04:37:43.520 --> 04:37:48.760
a city that is compact together whither the tribes go up, the tribes of the Lord, unto

04:37:48.760 --> 04:37:55.420
the testimony of Israel, to give thanks unto the name of the Lord. For there are set thrones

04:37:55.420 --> 04:38:02.120
of judgment, the thrones of the house of David. Pray for the peace of Jerusalem. They shall

04:38:02.120 --> 04:38:08.700
prosper that love thee. Peace be within thy walls, and prosperity within thy palaces.

04:38:09.340 --> 04:38:16.600
For my brethren and my companions' sake, I will now say, Peace be within thee. Because

04:38:16.600 --> 04:38:21.100
of the house of the Lord, our God, I will seek thy good.

04:38:23.720 --> 04:38:32.700
Psalm 123 Unto thee lift I up mine eyes, O thou that dwellest in the heavens. Behold,

04:38:33.080 --> 04:38:38.760
as the eyes of servants look unto the hand of their masters, and as the eyes of a maiden

04:38:38.760 --> 04:38:45.640
unto the hand of her mistress, so our eyes wait upon the Lord our God, until that he

04:38:45.640 --> 04:38:53.800
have mercy upon us. Have mercy upon us, O Lord, have mercy upon us, for we are exceedingly

04:38:53.800 --> 04:39:00.240
filled with contempt. Our soul is exceedingly filled with the scorning of those that are

04:39:00.240 --> 04:39:10.200
at ease, and with the contempt of the proud. Psalm 124 If it had not been the Lord who

04:39:10.200 --> 04:39:16.560
was on our side, now may Israel say, If it had not been the Lord who was on our side

04:39:16.560 --> 04:39:22.800
when men rose up against us, then they had swallowed us up quick when their wrath was

04:39:22.800 --> 04:39:30.040
kindled against us. Then the waters had overwhelmed us, the stream had gone over our soul. Then

04:39:30.040 --> 04:39:36.740
the proud waters had gone over our soul. Blessed be the Lord who hath not given us as a prey

04:39:36.740 --> 04:39:43.340
to their teeth. Our soul is escaped as a bird out of the snare of the fowlers. The snare

04:39:43.340 --> 04:39:50.560
is broken, and we are escaped. Our help is in the name of the Lord who made heaven and

04:39:50.560 --> 04:39:58.600
earth. Psalm 125 They that trust in the Lord shall be as

04:39:58.600 --> 04:40:05.520
Mount Zion, which cannot be removed, but abideth for ever. As the mountains are round about

04:40:05.520 --> 04:40:12.320
Jerusalem, so the Lord is round about his people from henceforth even for ever. For

04:40:12.320 --> 04:40:17.520
the rod of the wicked shall not rest upon the lot of the righteous, lest the righteous

04:40:17.520 --> 04:40:24.880
put forth their hands unto iniquity. Do good, O Lord, unto those that be good, and to them

04:40:24.880 --> 04:40:31.480
that are upright in their hearts. As for such as turn aside unto their crooked ways, the

04:40:31.480 --> 04:40:37.120
Lord shall lead them forth with the workers of iniquity, but peace shall be upon Israel.

04:40:40.900 --> 04:40:45.100
Psalm 126 When the Lord turned again the captivity of

04:40:45.100 --> 04:40:52.000
Zion, we were like them that dream. Then was our mouth filled with laughter and our tongue

04:40:52.000 --> 04:40:58.260
with singing. Then said they among the heathen, The Lord hath done great things for them.

04:40:58.980 --> 04:41:04.400
The Lord hath done great things for us, whereof we are glad.

04:41:05.140 --> 04:41:12.080
Turn again our captivity, O Lord, as the streams in the south. They that sow in tears shall

04:41:12.080 --> 04:41:19.140
reap in joy. He that goeth forth and weepeth, bearing precious seed, shall doubtless come

04:41:19.140 --> 04:41:22.920
again with rejoicing, bringing his sheaves with him.

04:41:25.620 --> 04:41:31.200
Psalm 127 Except the Lord build the house, they labor

04:41:31.200 --> 04:41:37.740
in vain that build it. Except the Lord keep the city, the watchman waketh but in vain.

04:41:38.620 --> 04:41:44.660
It is vain for you to rise up early, to sit up late, to eat the bread of sorrows, for

04:41:44.660 --> 04:41:51.440
so he giveth his beloved sleep. Lo, children are an heritage of the Lord, and the fruit

04:41:51.440 --> 04:41:57.640
of the womb is his reward. As arrows are in the hand of a mighty man,

04:41:57.900 --> 04:42:03.960
so are children of the youth. Happy is the man that hath his quiver full of them. They

04:42:03.960 --> 04:42:08.260
shall not be ashamed, but they shall speak with the enemies in the gate.

04:42:11.060 --> 04:42:15.980
Psalm 128 Blessed is every one that feareth the Lord,

04:42:15.980 --> 04:42:22.280
that walketh in his ways. For thou shalt eat the labor of thine hands, happy shalt thou

04:42:22.280 --> 04:42:28.860
be, and it shall be well with thee. Thy wife shall be as a fruitful vine by the sides of

04:42:28.860 --> 04:42:33.680
thine house, thy children like olive plants round about thy table.

04:42:34.880 --> 04:42:41.100
Behold, that thus shall the man be blessed that feareth the Lord. The Lord shall bless

04:42:41.100 --> 04:42:47.560
thee out of Zion, and thou shalt see the good of Jerusalem all the days of thy life. Yea,

04:42:47.600 --> 04:42:51.580
thou shalt see thy children's children, and peace upon Israel.

04:42:55.120 --> 04:42:59.500
Psalm 129 Many a time have they afflicted me from my

04:42:59.500 --> 04:43:06.200
youth. May Israel now say, Many a time have they afflicted me from my youth, yet they

04:43:06.200 --> 04:43:12.460
have not prevailed against me. The plowers plowed upon my back, they made long their

04:43:12.460 --> 04:43:18.720
furrows. The Lord is righteous, he hath cut asunder the cords of the wicked. Let them

04:43:18.720 --> 04:43:25.160
all be confounded and turned back that hate Zion. Let them be as the grass upon the housetops,

04:43:25.440 --> 04:43:31.460
which withereth afore it groweth up, wherewith the mower filth not his hand, nor he that

04:43:31.460 --> 04:43:37.800
findeth sheaves his bosom. Neither do they which go by say, The blessing of the Lord

04:43:37.800 --> 04:43:41.260
be upon you, we bless you in the name of the Lord.

04:43:43.640 --> 04:43:48.500
Psalm 130 Out of the depths have I cried unto thee, O

04:43:48.500 --> 04:43:54.440
Lord. Lord, hear my voice, let thine ears be attentive to the voice of my supplications.

04:43:55.110 --> 04:44:04.080
If thou, Lord, shouldst mark iniquities, O Lord, who shall stand? But there is forgiveness

04:44:04.080 --> 04:44:11.560
with thee, that thou mayest be feared. I wait for the Lord, my soul doth wait, and in his

04:44:11.560 --> 04:44:17.720
word do I hope. My soul waiteth for the Lord, more than they that watch for the morning.

04:44:17.720 --> 04:44:24.920
I say, more than they that watch for the morning. Let Israel hope in the Lord, for with the

04:44:24.920 --> 04:44:31.820
Lord there is mercy, and with him is plenteous redemption, and he shall redeem Israel from

04:44:31.820 --> 04:44:33.160
all his iniquities.

04:44:36.140 --> 04:44:42.120
Psalm 131 Lord, my heart is not haughty, nor mine eyes

04:44:42.120 --> 04:44:49.560
lofty. Neither do I exercise myself in great matters, or in things too high for me. Surely

04:44:49.560 --> 04:44:56.500
I have behaved and quieted myself as a child that is weaned of his mother. My soul is even

04:44:56.500 --> 04:45:03.180
as a weaned child. Let Israel hope in the Lord from henceforth and for ever.

04:45:06.380 --> 04:45:11.720
Psalm 132 Lord, remember David, and all his afflictions,

04:45:11.980 --> 04:45:18.000
how he swear unto the Lord, and vowed unto the mighty God of Jacob. Surely I will not

04:45:18.000 --> 04:45:23.800
come into the tabernacle of my house, nor go up into my bed. I will not give sleep to

04:45:23.800 --> 04:45:30.420
mine eyes, or slumber to mine eyelids, until I find out a place for the Lord, and habitation

04:45:30.420 --> 04:45:37.140
for the mighty God of Jacob. Lo, we heard of it at Ephrata. We found it in the fields

04:45:37.140 --> 04:45:42.860
of the wood. We will go into his tabernacles. We will worship at his footstool.

04:45:43.720 --> 04:45:50.260
Arise, O Lord, into thy rest, thou and the ark of thy strength. Let thy priests be clothed

04:45:50.260 --> 04:45:56.340
with righteousness, and let thy saints shout for joy. For thy servant David's sake, turn

04:45:56.340 --> 04:46:02.700
not away the face of thine anointed. The Lord hath sworn in truth unto David. He will not

04:46:02.700 --> 04:46:09.900
turn from it. Of the fruit of thy body will I set upon thy throne. If thy children will

04:46:09.900 --> 04:46:15.060
keep my covenant, and my testimony that I shall teach them, their children shall also

04:46:15.060 --> 04:46:21.300
sit upon thy throne for evermore. For the Lord hath chosen Zion. He hath desired it

04:46:21.300 --> 04:46:29.220
for his habitation. This is my rest for ever. Here will I dwell, for I have desired it.

04:46:29.780 --> 04:46:36.580
I will abundantly bless her provision. I will satisfy her poor with bread. I will also clothe

04:46:36.580 --> 04:46:43.000
her priests with salvation, and her saints shall shout aloud for joy. There will I make

04:46:43.000 --> 04:46:48.920
the horn of David to bud. I have ordained a lamp for mine anointed. His enemies will

04:46:48.920 --> 04:47:00.880
lie clothed with shame, but upon himself shall his crown flourish. Psalm 133. Behold, how

04:47:00.880 --> 04:47:07.960
good and how pleasant it is for brethren to dwell together in unity! It is like the precious

04:47:07.960 --> 04:47:14.520
ointment upon the head, that ran down upon the beard, even Aaron's beard, that went down

04:47:14.520 --> 04:47:20.080
to the skirts of his garments. As the dew of Hermon, and as the dew that descended upon

04:47:20.080 --> 04:47:26.260
the mountains of Zion, for there the Lord commanded the blessing, even life for evermore.

04:47:29.740 --> 04:47:37.060
Psalm 134. Behold, bless ye the Lord, all ye servants of the Lord, which by night stand

04:47:37.060 --> 04:47:42.800
in the house of the Lord. Lift up your hands in the sanctuary, and bless the Lord, the

04:47:42.800 --> 04:47:46.900
Lord that made heaven and earth. Bless thee out of Zion.

04:47:49.700 --> 04:47:57.820
Psalm 135. Praise ye the Lord! Praise ye the name of the Lord! Praise him, oh ye servants

04:47:57.820 --> 04:48:03.520
of the Lord! Ye that stand in the house of the Lord, in the courts of the house of our

04:48:03.520 --> 04:48:10.880
God! Praise the Lord, for the Lord is good. Sing praises unto his name, for it is pleasant.

04:48:11.440 --> 04:48:18.000
For the Lord hath chosen Jacob unto himself, and Israel for his peculiar treasure. For

04:48:18.000 --> 04:48:22.840
I know that the Lord is great, and that our Lord is above all gods.

04:48:23.720 --> 04:48:29.580
Whatsoever the Lord pleased, that he did in heaven, and in earth, in the seas, and all

04:48:29.580 --> 04:48:35.540
deep places. He causeth the vapors to ascend from the ends of the earth. He maketh lightnings

04:48:35.540 --> 04:48:38.760
for the rain. He bringeth the wind out of his treasuries.

04:48:39.420 --> 04:48:45.580
Who smote the firstborn of Egypt, both of man and beast? Who sent tokens and wonders

04:48:45.580 --> 04:48:52.160
into the midst of thee, oh Egypt, upon Pharaoh, and upon all his servants? Who smote great

04:48:52.160 --> 04:48:59.060
nations, and slew mighty kings? Sihon, king of the Amorites, and all king of Bashan, and

04:48:59.060 --> 04:49:04.620
all the kingdoms of Canaan, and gave their land for inheritance, and heritage unto Israel

04:49:04.620 --> 04:49:11.320
his people. Thy name, oh Lord, endureth for ever, and thy memorial, oh Lord, throughout

04:49:11.320 --> 04:49:17.660
all generations. For the Lord will judge his people, and he will repent himself concerning

04:49:17.660 --> 04:49:21.940
his servants. The idols of the heathen are silver and gold,

04:49:22.240 --> 04:49:28.940
the work of men's hands. They have mouths, but they speak not. Eyes have they, but they

04:49:28.940 --> 04:49:34.340
see not. They have ears, but they hear not, neither is there any breath in their mouths.

04:49:35.080 --> 04:49:40.380
They that make them are like unto them, so is every one that trusteth in them.

04:49:41.200 --> 04:49:46.660
Bless the Lord, oh house of Israel! Bless the Lord, oh house of Aaron!

04:49:47.200 --> 04:49:53.460
Bless the Lord, oh house of Levi! Ye that fear the Lord, bless the Lord!

04:49:54.100 --> 04:50:00.420
Blessed be the Lord out of Zion, which dwelleth at Jerusalem. Praise ye the Lord!

04:50:03.880 --> 04:50:09.120
Psalm 136 O give thanks unto the Lord, for he is good,

04:50:09.420 --> 04:50:15.740
for his mercy endureth for ever. O give thanks unto the God of gods, for his

04:50:15.740 --> 04:50:21.280
mercy endureth for ever. O give thanks to the Lord of lords, for his

04:50:21.280 --> 04:50:27.340
mercy endureth for ever. To him who alone doth great wonders, for his

04:50:27.340 --> 04:50:32.680
mercy endureth for ever. To him that by wisdom made the heavens, for

04:50:32.680 --> 04:50:37.140
his mercy endureth for ever. To him that stretched out the earth above

04:50:37.140 --> 04:50:44.420
the waters, for his mercy endureth for ever. To him that made great lights, for his mercy

04:50:44.420 --> 04:50:50.100
endureth for ever. The sun to rule by day, for his mercy endureth

04:50:50.100 --> 04:50:56.340
The moon and stars to rule by night, For his mercy endureth for ever.

04:50:56.960 --> 04:51:02.660
To him that smote Egypt in their first born, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:51:02.900 --> 04:51:07.600
And brought out Israel from among them, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:51:07.920 --> 04:51:13.700
With a strong hand and with a stretched out arm, For his mercy endureth for ever.

04:51:14.220 --> 04:51:20.640
To him which divided the Red Sea into parts, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:51:21.180 --> 04:51:26.500
And made Israel to pass through the midst of it, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:51:26.980 --> 04:51:33.000
But overthrew Pharaoh and his host in the Red Sea, For his mercy endureth for ever.

04:51:33.400 --> 04:51:39.700
To him which led his people through the wilderness, For his mercy endureth for ever.

04:51:39.700 --> 04:51:45.000
To him which smote great kings, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:51:45.400 --> 04:51:50.220
And slew famous kings, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:51:50.840 --> 04:51:55.320
Sihon king of the Amorites, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:51:55.720 --> 04:52:00.520
And Og the king of Bashan, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:52:00.840 --> 04:52:05.920
And gave their land for an heritage, For his mercy endureth for ever.

04:52:05.920 --> 04:52:11.980
Even an heritage unto Israel, his servant, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:52:12.400 --> 04:52:17.940
Who remembered us in our low estate, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:52:18.520 --> 04:52:23.160
And hath redeemed us from our enemies, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:52:23.680 --> 04:52:28.520
Who giveth food to all flesh, For his mercy endureth for ever,

04:52:29.110 --> 04:52:36.100
O give thanks unto the God of heaven, For his mercy endureth for ever.

04:52:39.960 --> 04:52:41.440
Psalm 137

04:52:42.110 --> 04:52:49.540
By the rivers of Babylon, there we sat down, Yea, we wept, when we remembered Sihon.

04:52:50.000 --> 04:52:53.700
We hanged our harps upon the willows, in the midst thereof,

04:52:54.000 --> 04:52:58.860
For there they that carried us away captive, Required of us a song,

04:52:59.260 --> 04:53:06.160
And they that wasted us, required of us mirth, Saying, Sing us one of the songs of Sihon.

04:53:06.980 --> 04:53:10.860
How shall we sing the Lord's song in a strange land?

04:53:11.820 --> 04:53:16.700
If I forget thee, O Jerusalem, let my right hand forget her cunning.

04:53:17.560 --> 04:53:22.480
If I do not remember thee, let my tongue cleave to the roof of my mouth.

04:53:22.780 --> 04:53:26.920
If I prefer not Jerusalem above my chief joy.

04:53:27.720 --> 04:53:32.420
Remember O Lord, the children of Edom, in the day of Jerusalem,

04:53:32.840 --> 04:53:37.460
Who said, Raise it, raise it, even to the foundation thereof.

04:53:38.120 --> 04:53:45.060
O daughter of Babylon, who art to be destroyed, Happy shall he be that rewardeth thee as thou

04:53:45.060 --> 04:53:46.180
hast served us.

04:53:47.240 --> 04:53:53.100
Happy shall he be that taketh and dasheth thy little ones against the stones.

04:53:55.880 --> 04:53:57.400
Psalm 138

04:53:57.400 --> 04:54:01.240
I will praise thee with my whole heart.

04:54:01.620 --> 04:54:05.260
Before the gods will I sing praise unto thee.

04:54:05.760 --> 04:54:11.200
I will worship toward thy holy temple, And praise thy name for thy loving kindness,

04:54:11.200 --> 04:54:16.800
And for thy truth, for thou hast magnified Thy word above all thy name.

04:54:17.660 --> 04:54:24.660
In the day when I cried, thou answerest me, And strengthenest me with strength in my soul.

04:54:25.300 --> 04:54:30.900
All the kings of the earth shall praise thee, O Lord, When they hear the words of thy mouth.

04:54:31.680 --> 04:54:37.500
Yea, they shall sing in the ways of the Lord, For great is the glory of the Lord.

04:54:37.500 --> 04:54:42.700
Though the Lord be high, yet hath he respect unto the lowly,

04:54:43.120 --> 04:54:45.500
But the proud he knoweth afar off.

04:54:46.480 --> 04:54:50.540
Though I walk in the midst of trouble, thou wilt revive me,

04:54:50.780 --> 04:54:54.340
Thou shalt stretch forth thine hand against the wrath of mine enemies,

04:54:54.820 --> 04:54:57.020
And thy right hand shall save me.

04:54:57.760 --> 04:55:01.200
The Lord will perfect that which concerneth me.

04:55:01.200 --> 04:55:04.440
Thy mercy, O Lord, endureth forever.

04:55:04.860 --> 04:55:07.600
Forsake not the works of thine own hands.

04:55:31.960 --> 04:55:37.960
Psalm 139 O Lord, thou hast searched me and known me.

04:55:37.960 --> 04:55:50.800
Thou knowest my down-sitting and mine uprising. Thou understandest my thought afar off. Thou compassest my path and my lying down, and are acquainted with all my ways.

04:55:51.400 --> 04:55:57.300
For there is not a word in my tongue, but lo, O Lord, thou knowest it altogether.

04:55:57.300 --> 04:56:09.940
Thou hast beset me behind and before, and laid thine hand upon me. Such knowledge is too wonderful for me. It is high. I cannot attain unto it.

04:56:10.520 --> 04:56:23.420
Whither shall I go from thy spirit, or whither shall I flee from thy presence? If I ascend up into heaven, thou art there. If I make my bed in hell, behold, thou art there.

04:56:23.420 --> 04:56:33.760
If I take the wings of the morning and dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea, even there shall thy hand lead me, and thy right hand shall hold me.

04:56:34.300 --> 04:56:40.720
If I say, Surely the darkness shall cover me, even the night shall be light about me.

04:56:40.720 --> 04:56:50.020
Yea, the darkness hideeth not from thee, but the night shineth as the day. The darkness and the light are both alike to thee.

04:56:50.600 --> 04:57:00.440
For thou hast possessed my reigns, thou hast covered me in my mother's womb. I will praise thee, for I am fearfully and wonderfully made.

04:57:00.440 --> 04:57:13.560
Marvelous are thy works, and that my soul knoweth right well. My substance was not hid from thee, when I was made in secret and curiously wrought in the lowest parts of the earth.

04:57:14.260 --> 04:57:27.280
Thine eyes did see my substance, yet being unperfect, and in thy book all my members were written, which in continuance were fashioned, when as yet there was none of them.

04:57:27.280 --> 04:57:41.560
How precious also are thy thoughts unto me, O God! How great is the sum of them! If I should count them, they are more in number than the sand. When I awake, I am still with thee.

04:57:42.500 --> 04:57:53.440
Surely thou wilt slay the wicked, O God! Depart from me, therefore ye bloody men, for they speak against thee wickedly, and thine enemies take thy name in vain.

04:57:53.440 --> 04:58:06.720
Do not I hate them, O Lord, that hate thee? And am not I grieved with those that rise up against thee? I hate them with perfect hatred. I count them, mine enemies.

04:58:07.740 --> 04:58:19.200
Search me, O God, and know my heart. Try me, and know my thoughts. And see if there be any wicked way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.

04:58:24.100 --> 04:58:35.580
Deliver me, O Lord, from the evil man. Preserve me from the violent man. Which imagined mischiefs in their heart, continually are they gathered together for war.

04:58:36.340 --> 04:58:41.120
They have sharpened their tongues like a serpent. Adder's poison is under their lips.

04:58:51.440 --> 04:58:52.840
Sila.

04:59:11.120 --> 04:59:23.380
As for my salvation, thou hast covered my head in the day of battle. Grant not, O Lord, the desires of the wicked. Further not his wicked device, lest they exalt themselves.

04:59:24.460 --> 04:59:25.080
Sila.

04:59:41.120 --> 04:59:47.220
Let not an evil speaker be established in the earth. Evil shall hunt the violent man to overthrow him.

04:59:47.960 --> 04:59:59.560
I know that the Lord will maintain the cause of the afflicted, and the right of the poor. Surely the righteous shall give thanks unto thy name. The upright shall dwell in thy presence.

05:00:02.740 --> 05:00:03.980
Psalm 141

05:00:03.980 --> 05:00:18.780
Lord, I cry unto thee. Make haste unto me. Give ear unto my voice when I cry unto thee. Let my prayer be set forth before thee as incense, and the lifting up of my hands as the evening sacrifice.

05:00:19.440 --> 05:00:34.080
Set a watch, O Lord, before my mouth. Keep the door of my lips. Incline not my heart to any evil thing to practice wicked works with men that work iniquity, and let me not eat of their dainties.

05:00:34.960 --> 05:00:47.700
Let the righteous smite me. It shall be a kindness. And let him reprove me. It shall be an excellent oil, which shall not break my head. For yet my prayer also shall be in their calamities.

05:00:47.700 --> 05:01:01.360
When their judges are overthrown in stony places, they shall hear my words, for they are sweet. Our bones are scattered at the grave's mouth, as when one cutteth and cleaveth wood upon the earth.

05:01:01.360 --> 05:01:21.000
But mine eyes are unto thee, O God, the Lord. In thee is my trust. Leave not my soul destitute. Keep me from the snares which they have laid for me, and the jinns of the workers of iniquity. Let the wicked fall into their own nets, whilst that I withal escape.

05:01:24.180 --> 05:01:25.300
Psalm 142

05:01:25.300 --> 05:01:43.340
I cried unto the Lord with my voice. With my voice unto the Lord did I make my supplication. I poured out my complaint before him. I showed before him my trouble. When my spirit was overwhelmed within me, then thou knewest my path.

05:01:43.340 --> 05:01:57.580
In the way wherein I walked have they privily laid a snare for me. I looked on my right hand and beheld, but there was no man that would know me. Refuge failed me. No man cared for my soul.

05:01:57.580 --> 05:02:23.500
I cried unto thee, O Lord. I said, Thou art my refuge and my portion in the land of the living. Attend unto my cry, for I am brought very low. Deliver me from my persecutors, for they are stronger than I. Bring my soul out of prison, that I may praise thy name. The righteous shall compass me about, for thou shalt deal bountifully with me.

05:02:25.580 --> 05:02:26.860
Psalm 143

05:02:26.860 --> 05:02:52.760
Hear my prayer, O Lord. Give ear to my supplications. In thy faithfulness answer me, and in thy righteousness. And enter not into judgment with thy servant, for in thy sight shall no man living be justified. For the enemy hath persecuted my soul. He hath smitten my life down to the ground. He hath made me to dwell in darkness as those that have been long dead.

05:02:52.760 --> 05:03:13.120
Therefore is my spirit overwhelmed within me. My heart within me is desolate. I remember the days of old. I meditate on all thy works. I muse on the work of thy hands. I stretch forth my hands unto thee. My soul thirsteth after thee, as a thirsty land. See law.

05:03:13.860 --> 05:03:34.720
Hear me speedily, O Lord. My spirit faileth. Hide not thy face from me, lest I be like unto them that go down into the pit. Cause me to hear thy loving kindness in the morning, for in thee do I trust. Cause me to know the way wherein I should walk, for I lift up my soul unto thee.

05:03:35.540 --> 05:03:56.460
Deliver me, O Lord, from mine enemies. I flee unto thee to hide me. Teach me to do thy will, for thou art my God. Thy spirit is good. Lead me into the land of uprightness. Quicken me, O Lord, for thy name's sake, for thy righteousness' sake. Bring my soul out of trouble.

05:03:56.460 --> 05:04:04.680
And of thy mercy cut off mine enemies, and destroy all them that afflict my soul, for I am thy servant.

05:04:07.020 --> 05:04:08.420
Psalm 144

05:04:09.460 --> 05:04:26.720
Blessed be the Lord my strength, which teacheth my hands to war, and my fingers to fight. My goodness, and my fortress, my high tower, and my deliverer, my shield, and he in whom I trust, who subdueeth my people under me.

05:04:26.720 --> 05:04:40.900
Lord, what is man that thou takest knowledge of him, or the son of man that thou makest account of him? Man is like to vanity, his days are as a shadow that passeth away.

05:04:41.620 --> 05:05:07.440
Bow thy heavens, O Lord, and come down. Touch the mountains, and they shall smoke. Cast forth lightning, and scatter them. Shoot out thine arrows, and destroy them. Send thine hand from above. Rid me, and deliver me, out of great waters, from the hand of strange children, whose mouth speaketh vanity, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood.

05:05:07.440 --> 05:05:23.720
I will sing a new song unto thee, O God. Upon a psaltery, and an instrument of ten strings, will I sing praises unto thee. It is he that giveth salvation unto kings, who delivereth David his servant from the hurtful sword.

05:05:23.720 --> 05:05:43.120
Rid me, and deliver me, from the hand of strange children, whose mouth speaketh vanity, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood. That our sons may be as plants grown up in their youth, that our daughters may be as cornerstones, polished after the similitude of a palace.

05:05:43.120 --> 05:06:01.080
That our garners may be full, affording all manner of store, that our sheep may bring forth thousands and ten thousands in our streets, that our oxen may be strong to labor, that there be no breaking in nor going out, that there be no complaining in our streets.

05:06:01.760 --> 05:06:09.420
Happy is that people that is in such a case, yea, happy is that people whose God is the Lord.

05:06:11.940 --> 05:06:13.300
Psalm 145

05:06:13.300 --> 05:06:25.500
I will extol thee, my God, O King, and I will bless thy name for ever and ever. Every day will I bless thee, and I will praise thy name for ever and ever.

05:06:25.500 --> 05:06:43.540
Great is the Lord, and greatly to be praised, and his greatness is unsearchable. One generation shall praise thy works to another and shall declare thy mighty acts. I will speak of the glorious honor of thy majesty and of thy wondrous works.

05:06:43.540 --> 05:06:55.680
And men shall speak of the might of thy terrible acts, and I will declare thy greatness. They shall abundantly utter the memory of thy great goodness and shall sing of thy righteousness.

05:06:56.440 --> 05:07:15.580
The Lord is gracious and full of compassion, slow to anger, and of great mercy. The Lord is good to all, and his tender mercies are over all his works. All thy works shall praise thee, O Lord, and thy saints shall bless thee.

05:07:15.580 --> 05:07:33.120
They shall speak of the glory of thy kingdom and talk of thy power, to make known to the sons of men his mighty acts and the glorious majesty of his kingdom. Thy kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, and thy dominion endureth throughout all generations.

05:07:33.120 --> 05:07:50.180
The Lord upholdeth all that fall, and raiseth up all those that be bowed down. The eyes of all wait upon thee, and thou givest them their meat in due season. Thou openest thine hand, and satisfiest the desire of every living thing.

05:07:50.180 --> 05:08:09.880
The Lord is righteous in all his ways, and holy in all his works. The Lord is nigh unto all them that call upon him, to all that call upon him in truth. He will fulfill the desire of them that fear him. He also will hear their cry, and will save them.

05:08:09.880 --> 05:08:24.940
The Lord preserveth all them that love him, but all the wicked will he destroy. My mouth shall speak the praise of the Lord, and let all flesh bless his holy name for ever and ever.

05:08:28.480 --> 05:08:54.360
Psalm 146 Praise ye the Lord! Praise the Lord, O my soul! While I live, will I praise the Lord. I will sing praises unto my God, while I have any being. Put not your trust in princes, nor in the son of man, in whom there is no help. His breath goeth forth, he returneth to his earth. In that very day his thoughts perish.

05:08:54.360 --> 05:09:21.860
Happy is he that hath the God of Jacob, for his help, whose hope is in the Lord his God, which made heaven and earth, the sea and all that therein is, which keepeth truth for ever, which executeth judgment for the oppressed, which giveth food to the hungry. The Lord luceth the prisoners, the Lord openeth the eyes of the blind, the Lord raiseth them that are bowed down, the Lord loveth the righteous.

05:09:21.860 --> 05:09:38.700
The Lord preserveth the strangers, he relieveth the fatherless and widow, but the way of the wicked he turneth upside down. The Lord shall reign for ever, even thy God, O Zion, unto all generations. Praise ye the Lord!

05:09:38.700 --> 05:09:42.700
Psalm 147

05:10:11.420 --> 05:10:22.300
The Lord lifteth up the meek, he casteth the wicked down to the ground. Sing unto the Lord with thanksgiving, sing praise upon the harp unto our God.

05:10:38.700 --> 05:10:56.220
The Lord taketh not pleasure in the legs of a man, the Lord taketh pleasure in them that fear him, in those that hope in his mercy. Praise the Lord, O Jerusalem, praise thy God, O Zion, for he hath strengthened the bars of thy gates.

05:10:56.220 --> 05:11:10.420
He hath blessed thy children within thee, he maketh peace in thy borders, and filleth thee with the finest of the wheat. He sendeth forth his commandment upon earth, his word runneth very swiftly.

05:11:10.420 --> 05:11:29.340
He giveth snow like wool, he scattereth the hoarfrost like ashes, he casteth forth his ice like morsels, who can stand before his cold. He sendeth out his word, and melteth them, he causeth his wind to blow, and the waters flow.

05:11:29.340 --> 05:11:44.800
He showeth his word unto Jacob, his statutes, and his judgments unto Israel. He hath not dealt, so with any nation, and as for his judgments, they have not known them. Praise ye the Lord!

05:11:47.900 --> 05:11:49.260
Psalm 148

05:11:49.260 --> 05:12:14.600
Praise ye the Lord! Praise ye the Lord from the heavens! Praise him in the heights! Praise ye him all his angels! Praise ye him all his hosts! Praise ye him sun and moon! Praise him all ye stars of light! Praise him ye heavens of heavens, and ye waters that be above the heavens!

05:12:14.600 --> 05:12:28.220
Let them praise the name of the Lord, for he commanded, and they were created. He hath also established them for ever and ever. He hath made a decree which shall not pass.

05:12:28.220 --> 05:12:50.460
Praise the Lord from the earth! Ye dragons and all deeps! Fire and hail, snow and vapors, stormy wind fulfilling his word! Mountains and all hills, fruitful trees and all cedars! Bees and all cattle, creeping things and flying fowl!

05:12:50.460 --> 05:13:08.140
Kings of the earth and all people, princes and all judges of the earth, both young men and maidens, old men and children, let them praise the name of the Lord, for his name alone is excellent, his glory is above the earth and heaven.

05:13:08.140 --> 05:13:20.840
He also exalted the horn of his people, the praise of all his saints, even of the children of Israel, a people near unto him. Praise ye the Lord!

05:13:23.720 --> 05:13:40.100
Psalm 149 Praise ye the Lord! Sing unto the Lord a new song, and his praise in the congregation of saints! Let Israel rejoice in him that made him! Let the children of Zion be joyful in their king!

05:13:40.100 --> 05:13:59.140
Let them praise his name in the dance, let them sing praises unto him with the timbrel and harp! For the Lord taketh pleasure in his people, he will beautify the meek with salvation! Let the saints be joyful in glory, let them sing aloud upon their beds!

05:14:00.080 --> 05:14:25.040
Let the high praises of God be in their mouth, and a two-edged sword in their hand, to execute vengeance upon the heathen and punishments upon the people, to bind their kings with chains and their nobles with fetters of iron, to execute upon them the judgment written, This honor have all his saints! Praise ye the Lord!

05:14:25.920 --> 05:14:28.340
Psalm 150

05:14:29.260 --> 05:14:57.320
Praise ye the Lord! Praise God in his sanctuary! Praise him in the firmament of his power! Praise him for his mighty acts! Praise him according to his excellent greatness! Praise him with the sound of the trumpet! Praise him with the psaltery and harp! Praise him with the timbrel and dance! Praise him with stringed instruments and organs!

05:14:57.320 --> 05:15:12.240
Praise him upon the loud cymbals! Praise him upon the high sounding cymbals! Let everything that hath breath praise the Lord! Praise ye the Lord!

05:15:13.500 --> 05:15:16.360
End of Psalms 139-150

05:15:17.520 --> 05:15:21.320
End of the Book of Psalms, King James Version
